#: result.py:1
msgid "* I arrive at the apartment and find only Magdalena, who informs me that Beryl is at the library."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:2
msgid "* The walk pulls me from the warm pockets of community into cold streets hedged with husks of buildings long abandoned."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3
msgid "* I stop at the most ornate one, which has a big, faded word chiseled over the stone doorway: LIBRARY."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:4
msgid "* Beryl must've heard the hinges creak when I opened the front doors. Her voice echoes through the shelves. The set of doors that lead into the lobby are missing, so I can hear her clearly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:5
msgid "Beryl: HC! O-over here!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:6
msgid "* I wind through the ancient stone shelves to the back of the library. Beryl is sitting in a small alcove she's decorated with a few trinkets."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:7
msgid "Beryl: Hey, HC! Welcome to the, uh, library. It's...cool right? * She looks away, blushing and smiling."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:8
msgid "It's massive! And... At risk of collapsing?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:9
msgid "Beryl: Y-yeah, it's one of the older buildings in Pira. L-luckily, Decima checks out the s... structural integrity quite often."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:10
msgid "Beryl: It's my little second home. * She smiles, takes a deep breath. * Want a t-tour?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11 result.py:612 result.py:6555 result.py:17563 result.py:19283
msgid "Sure."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12 result.py:14233
msgid "Maybe some other time."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13
msgid "* Beryl squeaks with pleasure as she darts from the alcove, leading me through countless rows of colossal, dusty shelves filled with a few books and a lot of digital media, most of it obsolete."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14
msgid "* Every time we pass a shelf, Beryl slows down and hovers around certain shelves, like she wants to stop and show me a book or holocard or something, but she keeps going."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:15
msgid "Beryl: It's hard n-not to get distracted w-walking past all this history!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:16
msgid "* We finally reach the back, stopping at a mural spanning at least twenty feet. * Everyone that worked here added a little to it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:17
msgid "* It's ancient, pale and smokey with decay on the left, slowly becoming more vibrant and less ornate as it progreses, until the very end..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:18
msgid "Beryl: Look! It's me! * She points to a tiny drawing on the end of the right side. Presumably the most recent addition."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:19
msgid "Beryl: I decided on a little self portrait! Cool... right? * She smiles at me. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:20
msgid "It's really good."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:21
msgid "How many people painted this?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:22
msgid "Beryl: No clue! P-probably hundreds, honestly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:23
msgid "Beryl: Just goes to show you how long p-people have been keeping this place running."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:24
msgid "Beryl: Makes me feel like I'm a part of something."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:25
msgid "This is so cool, Beryl. Seems like you're doing important work."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:26
msgid "Beryl: Th-thanks! Hm...come on, I've got something else to show you. * She scurries off toward the back of the chamber."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:27
msgid "Beryl: That's ok; let's just go hang out in back, then. * She leads me to a door, a vague outline with a handle cut in one of the massive walls. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:28
msgid "* We stop in some kind of gutted control room. On a table running its length are several heavy-looking trays, each emitting a soft green glow. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:29
msgid "Beryl: Ch-check it out. People used to grow little... world simulations in eggs and then steal their technology. * She touches the egg, situated on a small metal tray. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:30
msgid "* It doesn't react. Its surface is scratched and coarse. If not for the hum of the incubation tray, I might have guessed this was nothing more than ancient, inert stone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:31
msgid "Beryl: This is just a clone, the r-real ones are all gone, but the library has cultivated her for a super long time. She's my friend now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:32
msgid "Beryl: I'm like a little mom. * Tenderly, she strokes the large egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:33
msgid "That's really cute."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:34
msgid "* Touch the egg. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:35
msgid "* Beryl lets out a panicky laugh. * Uh... y-you too. I mean, you're cute... or..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:36
msgid "* She takes a breath. * Oof, I am... so awkward. Sorry."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:37
msgid "* She looks down at her egg, gives it a pat. * Anyway, I s-should be getting back to my ap-partment..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:38
msgid "Beryl: I g-gotta stop by the Rust Pup compound to get some m-mushrooms for dinner!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:39
msgid "Beryl: They j-just got back from a scavenging mission, so the haul is gonna be... decent."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:40
msgid "* She leaves the library with me and we part ways at the old dilapidated school where the Rust Pups are headquartered."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:41
msgid "Beryl: F-feel free to stop by the library w-whenever!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:42
msgid "* I wave, and walk back through the industrial wasteland to my apartment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:43
msgid "* I place my hand next to Beryl's on the egg. Beryl's fingertips brush against mine. She looks up at me and giggles. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:44
msgid "It's warm... * I start to feel overcome by a tingling sensation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:45
msgid "Beryl: Y-you can feel the life, c-can't you? That staticy feeling... T-that's it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:46
msgid "* I have to rip my hand away before I get too sucked in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:47
msgid "Beryl: It's... It's a lot. I should have warned you!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:48
msgid "* Beryl's nook is empty today, but I can hear echoing, tight voices, not from the huge warehouse but from one of the rooms around its perimeter."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:49
msgid "* I follow the wall towards Beryl's usual hangouts. There's a faint glow coming from one of the otherwise black doorways. I peer in. Two lamp-lit silhouettes are huddled together, hunched over something."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:50
msgid "Voice: It's probably just too... dry or something, Bear. * Must be Mags. I consider sneaking right back out until I remember that Beryl wanted to hang out with me today."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:51
msgid "* I take a deep, slow breath, filling my nostrils with dusty old book debris, and head into the back room."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:52
msgid "Beryl is leaning over the broad stone altar into which her eggs are placed, each slotted safe into a scoop in the cement and kept living under heat lamp. She seems to be studying one in particular."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:53
msgid "Beryl: I... I ap-appreciate you trying to make me... make me feel better. But it's h-happening..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:54
msgid "* Mags kneels down beside Beryl. * I'm serious, though! I thought these things were supposed to last hundreds of years?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:55
msgid "Beryl: Y-yeah... But for all I know, they might have! * The two of them stare at the glossy exterior of the egg. * I mean, they've been in the care of the Library for long before I worked here... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:56
msgid "Is something wrong with the eggs? * They look towards me in tandem, startled out of an intense moment..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:57
msgid "* Beryl smiles. * Not wrong, necessarily. J-just... well... Come and look. * Her gentle palm is flat against the surface of the egg, as it always is. Second nature. Habit. She really does have mom energy."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:58
msgid "* I stand behind them. Mags sighs and scoots over. * Sit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:59
msgid "Oh, thanks. Ok... * I kneel in between them, let the egg take up my field of vision. * I can't see a diff--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:60
msgid "Beryl: Just wait. * She holds a hand up and I freeze. Wait..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:61
msgid "* Against the dull green of the egg, an almost imperceptible strand of phosphorescence glows."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:62
msgid "* Did I miss it? Or did it just appear? I look close, and in the hairline crack, flickering beads of green energy pulse."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:63
msgid "Beryl: There! A new crack! They're kinda hard to see, but they've been appearing since yesterday."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:64
msgid "Mags: That's cool, but Beryl? I've been staring at this bitch for hours. You're passionate, it's great. I honestly love that for you. * She waits for Beryl to talk, but she's just staring at the egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:65
msgid "Mags: But this will probably take like ten years! Really, lemme take you somewhere and get you some food. Maybe take a walk or something? I promise you aren't gonna miss anything."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:66
msgid "* Mags stretches her arm out in front of me, strokes Beryl's thigh, gazes into her eyes..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:67
msgid "Right... So... * I scoot my way out of this intimate sandwich, let them touch. Beryl closes the gap, wraps an arm around Mags without removing her other hand from the egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:68
msgid "Beryl: I'm ok. Really. This was b-bound to happen. I'm sad but... I also want to see w-what happens when it hatches, you know? Feel like I've been watching over this little guy forever..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:69
msgid "Mags: Of course, Bear. I suppose I can stay up a little longer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:70
msgid "Beryl: Mags, you are too sweet, but really, go home. You can warm the... warm the b-bed up for me!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:71
msgid "Beryl: I j-just wanna stay here a little bit longer. * She gives the egg a little hug."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:72
msgid "Mags: You sure?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:73
msgid "Beryl: Yeah! Seriously. I'll be ok."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:74
msgid "* Mags squeezes Beryl tightly and kisses the top of her head. * Ok."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:75
msgid "* She waves at me as she leaves. Beryl keeps her eyes on the egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:76
msgid "Beryl: Sorry... This probably isn't going to be the funnest hangout..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:77
msgid "* I notice how tired she looks now that it's just us. Her smile doesn't extend to her eyes as it usually does. Her eyelids look heavy, with dark circles underneath."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:78
msgid "It's fine."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:79
msgid "You should get some sleep."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:80
msgid "That's totally fine! This is important to you, so it's important to me. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:81
msgid "Beryl: It is important. * She leans against me, rubs her face against my chest. * Thanks."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:82
msgid "Are you sure you wanna stay here? Mags has a point... You look exhausted."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:83
msgid "* Beryl looks up at me and I see a flash of frustration. * Of C-c... OF COURSE I'M SURE!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:84
msgid "* She takes a breath, lets out a small laugh. * Oh man, sorry... You're right. I'm tired but I just can't miss this, Ok?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:85
msgid "* She walks back to her egg and leans over it. * I think it'll hatch soon. See, look. * She points at the egg as the network of cracks is hit with another wave of green light."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:86
msgid "Beryl: When the flickering s-started... Like a day ago? It happened pretty infrequently. Once every couple hours."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:87
msgid "* She waits for it to flicker again. * See. That c-couldn't have been more than... a minute?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:88
msgid "Are you sure that this means it's hatching? Maybe it's... I don't know. Broken?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:89
msgid "* Beryl giggles. * I do have books on this, you know! T-this one in... in particular..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:90
msgid "* She pries her eyes away from the egg long enough to lean over and grab me a dusty spiral-bound booklet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:91
msgid "* It's flimsy, non-archival, maybe 200 pages. Yellowed and torn around the edges. 'World Egg: A Comprehensive Manual'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:92
msgid "Beryl: This guide was a t-textbook, I think. Found it in the school. It's been really helpful. Flip to page, Uh... one forty two, I think?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:93
msgid "Beryl: That's the part about hatching. * With one hand on the egg, she picks up a pen and starts doodling on the concrete tables surface."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:94
msgid "* She's right. The chapter is labeled, 'End Game: Hatching and Knowledge Extraction.' Looks like most of the other pages are either too mildewy to be legible or straight torn out. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:95
msgid "Beryl: Ignore the extracting data section. Just the hatching p-part. See. * She flips a page forward."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:96
msgid "* 'What To Expect. As cracks begin to form and light becomes visible, your world egg may seem in danger. Relax. Your egg is preparing to enter the hatching phase.'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:97
msgid "* 'At the end of its simu-gestation cycle you will likely notice a few events, the first of which is clarity of color.'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:98
msgid "* 'Based on random branches in the simulations early timeline, your world egg's glow may appear blue, green, or even yellow, all of which are perfectly natural.'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:99
msgid "* The chapter continues to describe the process, making reference to a ton of expensive-sounding scientific apparatus that we obviously don't have. Concerning."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:100
msgid "* Despite that, the booklet does seem to indicate that the egg is behaving as it should when it hatches, and none of the equipment seems super necessary. Seems like Beryl is right."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:101
msgid "Beryl: See. It's all happening... * She looks down at her feet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:102
msgid "Beryl: I wish I... I wish I had a more l-logical m-mind. L-like Decima. Or Olivia. Th-they wouldn't attach so many emotions to this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:103
msgid "Beryl: Tens of thousands years of history, simulated in a few hundred. They'd see this as a learning experience. Like it was supposed to be."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:104
msgid "* She picks it up gently, cradles it in her arms. * Every f-flicker just reminds me of a... Of a death rattle. The last twitches of life..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:105
msgid "Beryl: I... I wonder if whatever world is in there... If they know t-that the end is near. * Her eyes are still affixed to the egg, her face shimmering with green light."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:106
msgid "Beryl: I hope not..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:107
msgid "Beryl: It never really bothered me before that this was just a cloned egg. That it wouldn't make it past this part. But now that it's about to happen?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:108
msgid "* She shakes her head and smiles. * Getting t-too sentimental! S-sorry. I'm a sensitive little succulent."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:109
msgid "It's totally ok to be a... sensitive little succulent! Especially now. This is really intense. * I put an arm around her and she leans into me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:110
msgid "Beryl: It is intense! N-not knowing when it will happen is s-stressful!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:111
msgid "Maybe we should take our minds off it for a bit? Do something distracting?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:112
msgid "Beryl: Well, as long as I c-can k-keep an eye on it. * She looks around the heavy, concrete room. A few signs of life are stuffed between what looks like janitorial storage."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:113
msgid "* Above the altar, a pair of faded posters try their best to make the ruined structure feel homey. Combined with a little shelf lined with books and old computer parts, they almost make it work."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:114
msgid "Beryl: I can't distract myself! I d-don't know anything other than this egg!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:115
msgid "* Her eyebrows scrunch together and she closes her eyes tight. * Think, you little succulent!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:116
msgid "Beryl: Oh! I c-can show you this... this dumb little game I found! Some kind of retro console. Cadence told me what it was called when I asked her, but I forget..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:117
msgid "Beryl: Anyway, watch the egg while I go get it. Y-yell if anything happens!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:118
msgid "* With that, she turns on her toes and sprints out the door. I set my gaze on the egg, just me and it. That glowing green oval..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:119
msgid "* I walk closer, finding myself more transfixed by it now that we are alone together. Like a lidded eye which will soon awaken."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:120
msgid "* I lean in, inspect my blurred reflection on its waxy exterior. It's so still, but so animate. Like a creature in wait."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:121
msgid "* touch the egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:122
msgid "* back up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:123
msgid "* I reach my hand forward slowly, allowing just the tips of my fingers to glide along the egg. It feels warm and fuzzy with static electricity."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:124
msgid "* I place my palm over the top and close my eyes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:125
msgid "* The warmth radiates through me, as if I'm touching a living creature... I'm completely still now, focusing all of my attention on the smooth, vegetable texture of the egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:126
msgid "* And then I can feel it moving under me. Like a heartbeat. Maybe it's just a hiccup in my own system, but I swear I can feel it pulsing..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:127
msgid "Beryl: Is... is something w-wrong? D-did something happen? * Her voice startles me out of my trance and I pull my hand away."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:128
msgid "No! No, I just wanted to... feel it? * I blush, feeling incredibly stupid all of a sudden."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:129
msgid "Beryl: Oh! * She giggles. * I understand. It gets weird being alone with the egg. K-kind of trippy, actually."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:130
msgid "* I look at the egg until it starts to freak me out and I have to look away."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:131
msgid "* I do my best to ignore it, busying myself by looking at the expanse of doodles on the tabletop. She really has spent a lot of time in here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:132
msgid "Beryl: Here it is! * She hurries in and plunks down a large metal brick of a gaming console, With a circular controller in hand, she takes a seat next to me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:133
msgid "Beryl: Anyway, Check this out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:134
msgid "* She plunks down a large brick of a gaming console."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:135
msgid "* She presses a red button on the side and the screen takes minutes to boot up. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:136
msgid "Beryl: This thing is ridiculous... Just warning y-you. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:137
msgid "* Finally, two smiling cartoon characters greet us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:138
msgid "Montgomery: Nice to meet you! I'm Montgomery the Manners Man! And this here is--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:139
msgid "Dale: And I'm Dale the Discourteous Dude!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:140
msgid "Montgomery: And right away we have an example of BAD MANNERS! But don't panic! By the end of this journey, you will have learned how to avoid situations like this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:141
msgid "Dale: Or maybe you'll lighten up a bit and join me on the fun train headed straight to Rude Town!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:142
msgid "Montgomery: I must insist that you not listen to Dale. He is here just to lead you astray, friend! Come, join me for our first lesson in the wonderful world of Appropriate Conduct For A Civilized and Tasteful Society!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:143
msgid "Montgomery: ACFACTS for short!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:144
msgid "Dale: More like ACFUC-- * The screen cuts away to a scene in a park where Dale and Montgomery are having a picnic."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:145
msgid "* I look at Beryl. She has a huge smile on her face. * D-did't say it was a g-good game!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:146
msgid "Beryl: I'm pretty sure this was one of F-fossicults genius ideas to m-make their citizens more... obedient? upstanding? I don't know..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:147
msgid "Montgomery: Oh Hello again, friend! Please, join us for a fun ACFACTS learning lunch!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:148
msgid "Montgomery: I was just playing a fun question game with Dale, but he is not taking this seriously."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:149
msgid "Montgomery: Maybe you'd like to play! Answer this question for me: Say I have these twenty homemade double chocolate cookies. * A plate of cookies pops up in his hands."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:150
msgid "Montgomery: I share them with you and Dale and I say, 'take as many as you want!'. What do you do?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:151
msgid "* Take none."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:152
msgid "* Take one."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:153
msgid "* Take one, eat it, insult it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:154
msgid "* Take twenty."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:155 result.py:159 result.py:161
msgid "Montgomery: WRONG ANSWER!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:156
msgid "Montgomery: Let me explain. If you refuse my cookies, it is what we call at ACFACTS, an 'indirect insult' to my baking."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:157
msgid "CORRECT!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:158
msgid "Montgomery: Taking one cookie is the only way to show appropriate respect! and here at ACFACTS, that is what we strive for!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:160
msgid "Montgomery: Let me explain. Although you were right to eat the cookie, insulting the cookie is what we call at ACFACTS a 'direct insult.'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:162
msgid "Montgomery: Let me explain. Although it may seem a polite gesture to my baking skills, taking all twenty cookies is what we call at ACFACTS an 'aggressively polite abuse of power'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:163
msgid "Montgomery: Congratulations, friend! You have gained one Montgomery point!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:164
msgid "Montgomery: Now, Dale and I are going to catch a movie at the ACFACTS theater. Come join us!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:165
msgid "Dale: Congratulations! You have gained one Dale point!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:166
msgid "Montgomery: And you have lost one Montgomery point. Do not fear, friend. You have more than enough time to get back on my team!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:167
msgid "Montgomery: In fact, Dale and I are going to catch a movie at the ACFACTS theater. Come join us!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:168
msgid "Beryl: That is pretty much how the entire game goes... I guess you can either become like Montgomery or Dale? I have no idea if there is an end to the game, though..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:169
msgid "Is this whole cube just for that game?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:170
msgid "Beryl: Yep! Kind of a waste of space... A-although I have to ad-admit... I p-played it for HOURS t-the other day."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:171
msgid "Beryl! * I laugh. * You must be an ACFACTS master."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:172
msgid "Beryl: I may have ended up on D-Dales team..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:173
msgid "* I play for a bit longer, and then we spend what seems like hours talking, playing games, cuddling."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:174
msgid "* Beryl ends up cradled in my arms as we relax against the wall. It's a cold night, so we move the heat lamp and the couple of soft blankets we can find to the corner, hold the egg between us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:175
msgid "* I stroke her hair as she sleeps, keeping an eye on the egg as I know she wants me to. Her breathing slows as she descends into a deeper sleep."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:176
msgid "* I am in a meditative state for an hour, strangely peaceful in this crumbling little room, with Beryl in my arms..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:177
msgid "* Then, and I can't tell at first if it's in my mind, but there it is. The egg is twitching. It's flickering once every thirty seconds now, and twitching back and forth."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:178
msgid "* I look down at Beryl, wanting to let her sleep, but I need to wake her up. * Beryl... Hey. * I whisper as I brush back her hair. She blinks her eyes open slowly, looks up at me with a gentle smile."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:179
msgid "Beryl: Was... Did I fall asleep? * She rubs her eyes, still a bit disoriented, then jerks up. * The egg! What happened!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:180
msgid "It's ok! It just is doing something different. It's moving around. At least, I think it is? I've been staring at it for so long I might just be imagining it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:181
msgid "* She lifts her hands out from under the blanket and plants them on either side of the egg, moves in real close. * It is. Oh, w-wow. Yeah..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:182
msgid "* She glances at me. * This is... this is the end of this stage."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:183
msgid "* She looks sleepy and happy and present. No thoughts of what comes next. No mourning the simulations end. Just pride in her little buddy doing its thing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:184
msgid "* We watch the egg quietly, holding our breath at every flicker, every twitch."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:185
msgid "Beryl: D-do you see that? * She points towards a nexus of bright cracks."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:186
msgid "* I lean in closer, * Oh, yeah. * A bit of the waxy membrane has dissolved to reveal a pinprick of rainbow brilliance, barely visible until it casts its beam on something close."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:187
msgid "Beryl: This is it. * She grabs my arm and squeezes it hard. I don't mind, though. I've become emotionally invested in this egg just seeing how it makes Beryl feel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:188
msgid "Beryl: Oh, wow! it's... it's beautiful."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:189
