msgid "* She empties the snacks into the center, then lifts a corner of the blanket and shoves the empty plastic bag underneath."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:393
msgid "* With a bit of fussing, she crumples the corner and the bag into a tuft soft enough to hold the egg, then she carefully unzips the hoodie."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:394
msgid "* The egg looks even more fragile in the exterior light. Its blemished surface is still a delicate semi-satin material. Something that should be sheltered."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:395
msgid "* Beryl sets the egg on the crumpled corner, and I place the sunhat on its top. * Aww.."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:396
msgid "Beryl: I know, right? What a handsome little supercomputer. * She gives its dome a loving pat."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:397
msgid "Shall we? * I gesture towards the pile."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:398
msgid "Beryl: He-heck yes! * She lifts a bottle of Berryglug and starts unscrewing the top."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:399
msgid "* I scan the mess of snacks. Just a few options... Wonder what I should pick?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:400
msgid "Puffles and Cheesewash"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:401
msgid "That Old Chocobar"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:402
msgid "Fudge-nut Kibble"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:403
msgid "* I unseal the vaccum bag of gray, semi-transparent slices of dried meat. They're salty, impossibly chewy, and otherwise unflavored. The power of slug is that it's a perfect vessel for other flavors."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:404
msgid "* I rip open the bag of crunchy corn-puffs and dump in the orange powdered wash. Tangy, and kinda good? For sure a better texture than flavor, though."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:405
msgid "* Beryl goes for some Slug Jerky, which is far crunchier than I'd have guessed based on the name."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:406
msgid "* A few shiny black pellets rattle out of the tube and into my palm. The candy coating melts onto my tongue, unleashes a concentrated rush of chocolatey, nutty flavor. Addictive. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:407
msgid "* First snack of the day oughta be the first snack we found. I grab the yellowed wrapper and peel it back, revealing a bar warped by countless melt-cycles. Yum."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:408
msgid "* I try to look on the bright side, focus on the pleasant taste while my teeth grapple with the rock-hard nougat. Quite a workout for the jaw."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:409
msgid "* Beryl goes for the Puffies and Cheesewash, opens the bag of crunchy balls and dumps in the orange powdered wash."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:410
msgid "* As we munch, we stare at the smattering of lights across the sinkhole. * Hey, is that your place? * I point to a dark, distant building with only a few windows lit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:411
msgid "Beryl: Yeah! I think so, right? It'll b-be embarrassing if I'm wrong though... * She points with me. * That'd b-be my room right there. Third light up, t-two lights in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:412
msgid "I'm not trying to fact check you. You know the city better than I do. * I pause, take in the landscape. * Looks so small from out here..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:413
msgid "Beryl: Yeah... * She does some more crunching and we enjoy the gentle tone of the wind around the chasm."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:414
msgid "* I reach a palmful of crumbled snacks toward the egg. * You hungry? * We both laugh and lean against each other."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:415
msgid "So, how long has this guy been... Gestating? * I straighten the sunhat."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:416
msgid "Beryl: D-dunno for sure, but since the original brood of eggs went extinct around 300 years ago, and most of the cloning started 100 years before that, I'd say.... Somewhere between 400 and 200 years."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:417
msgid "Huh. Weird that there's not more information available."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:418
msgid "Beryl: Yeah. Before the whole cloning process turned out to be a bust, people were really protective of the eggs. Sometimes I wonder about who's hands this one has passed though."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:419
msgid "Dang, yeah. There must be a ton of history here. And we don't even know how old it is. It could be its birthday for all we know."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:420
msgid "Beryl: Yeah, maybe it is! What if... * She smiles super wide. * This was a birthday picnic!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:421
msgid "Yeah, oh my gosh that's adorable! Too bad we don't have a cake! Or, wait. Would an egg birthday even include a cake?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:422
msgid "Beryl: P-probably not. What's important is that its friends are here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:423
msgid "* Beryl starts to sing, and I merrily join in, but when the birthday tune and our giggles end, the overwhelming nothingness of the void takes their place."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:424
msgid "* We pause for a while, feeling small against the terrain. I wonder what the egg is sensitive to. Beryl's warm palm? The bright sky? Petrichor tainted with the acrid smell of the pollution swamp?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:425
msgid "* A smile reassumes its places on Beryl's lips. * Maybe it would enjoy a story..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:426
msgid "Oh, good idea! I think I'd enjoy one, too. * I lean back and focus on the dust particles dancing in the tiny streaks of sunlight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:427
msgid "* Beryl scoots closer to the egg and softens her voice. * Once there was a city called Pira."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:428
msgid "That's where you're from, little eggie!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:429
msgid "* Beryl giggles. * Well, no, actually. It's probably from somewhere a bit more upper-class than Pira ever was."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:430
msgid "* She resumes, her voice gentle and soothing, * Pira city was a magical place, full of elves and goblins and hot, hard, transgirl dick..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:431
msgid "* We both laugh, then she continues spinning a nonsense tale about me and Mags and the rest of her friends."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:432
msgid "* When she gets to the part where I grow bat-wings and carry the egg from the clutches of a breakfast-hungry chef, we notice the sun begin to sink."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:433
msgid "* Beryl glances at me from across the pile of empty snack-wrappers. * D-dang! It's starting to get late."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:434
msgid "And things were just getting good!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:435
msgid "* Beryl giggles. * We both know that you'd have saved the day, in the end."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:436
msgid "* She pulls me towards her and we lay together on either side of the egg, staring at the veil of noble gasses that obscure the sky."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:437
msgid "Think it liked the story?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:438
msgid "* She giggles again. * I'm g-gonna tell myself it d-did."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:439
msgid "Beryl: N-not that it matters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:440
msgid "I'm sure whoever's in there appreciates how caring you are?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:441
msgid "Beryl: Oh, n-no. If there are s-sentient beings in there, they have no idea about me.."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:442
msgid "Beryl: I d-do sometimes wish that I could just peek in, you know?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:443
msgid "* She traces her fingers along the shell, * Make sure everyone's ok in there..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:444
msgid "* She stares at it for a few more seconds, then shakes her head."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:445
msgid "Beryl: S-sorry, I get so distracted around this little guy."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:446
msgid "Beryl: We gotta get going before it gets too d-dark. This p-place is s-super dangerous at night!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:447
msgid "* Beryl scoops up her egg and packs it tightly in the blanket and we head back into the city and she splits off to her apartment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:448
msgid "* I wave, but she just smiles. Arms full of picnic goodies and a hoodie full of egg. What a cutie."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:449
msgid "* I wander through the industrial district to the library to meet Beryl. Magdalena told me she'd be here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:450
msgid "* She isn't tucked into her usual cozy, candle-lit refuge among the concrete wreckage of the library. Probably in the back with her egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:451
msgid "* I peek my head in the back room and look around. No Beryl. And the egg is gone from its cradle."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:452
msgid "Beryl? * My voice cracks. I'm trying to make it more of a whisper yell, trying to make myself visible only to her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:453
msgid "* No response... I shuffle back through the shelves, walking more urgently now.."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:454
msgid "It's HC! * Amplified enough to echo off the metal struts. I wait, silent... until."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:455
msgid "* A rustling comes from a staircase to my left which appears to lead to an underground level. * Ok, Beryl... * I take a breath and head into the dark hole."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:456
msgid "* It better be you down there, Beryl! * I take the first step down, quietly as possible. More rustling noises. I hop down the rest of the narrow steps and slip on the final stair, just barely steadying myself."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:457
msgid "* The glowing silhouette of a door in front of me breaks the abysmal darkness of the hallway. I creep to it, reminding myself that with droid strength and reflexes, I should be ok... Right?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:458
msgid "* I reach the door and peer around it, heart thumping, breath held, ready to act."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:459
msgid "* But I shouldn't have worried. She's here, back to the door and head in a pile of metal crates, furiously tossing out random components and bits of techno garbage."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:460
msgid "* I clear my throat loudly, then call her name to gently get her attention without startling her. * Hey, uh, Beryl?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:461
msgid "* She swings around fast and I put my hands up. * Just me! Don't worry!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:462
msgid "* Beryl is frozen with a bulb of metal and plastic in her hand, a battery cell maybe. She lowers it and blushes * J-j-jeez! Almost threw the whole basement at you!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:463
msgid "* She rushes over and gives me a quick hug. * Sorry... G-glad you're here, though. It gets kinda c-creepy down here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:464
msgid "I didn't even know there was a basement! * I glance around the room. A pale LED lantern hangs from a hook above her, conjuring creepy shadows from the calthemites and bundles of wire clinging to the ceiling."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:465
msgid "* I can only see one of the walls peeping through a stack of mismatched crates of various sizes. The rest are bathed in darkness."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:466
msgid "* Beryl sees me looking around. * Yeah, it's falling apart a b-bit. * She smiles. * Adds a little character, though!!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:467
msgid "That's certainly one way to look at it! What are you doing down here, anyway?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:468
msgid "Beryl: I'm looking for an... * She throws aside a book. * Old * Shifts a rusty metal bench. * Camera!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:469 result.py:9273
msgid "For what?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:470
msgid "Beryl: Security!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:471
msgid "Beryl: I got a b-bit of a scare last night."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:472
msgid "Beryl: I... I'll tell you w-what happened... Upstairs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:473
msgid "* She digs through a junk box, rustling through papers and electrical equipment... * Found it!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:474
msgid "* She lifts up a brick of plastic and dark metal, scored and filthy, embossed with lettering that's surprisingly still legible. It reads 'GEL SECURE'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:475
msgid "Beryl: Used to belong to Gelcorp, back when it was easier for people to goof off at work, I guess."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:476
msgid "So, how's a camera gonna help?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:477
msgid "Beryl: W-well, there's a monitor upstairs that it used to work with. If I hook it up, I might be able to see people before they enter..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:478
msgid "Beryl: It's... not much. I n-need to block off other entrances, too. And... get a self defense object."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:479
msgid "Uh... like a weapon?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:480
msgid "Beryl: N-no... Well, technically yes. B-but just for intimidation!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:481
msgid "How about..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:482
msgid "A gun"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:483
msgid "A bat"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:484
msgid "A blowhorn"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:485
msgid "Beryl: Oh, jeez, no! I don't t-trust anyone with a gun. Even myself! * She giggles. * E-especially myself!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:486
msgid "Beryl: Maybe... I w-wonder if anyone would be scared of me with a bat..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:487
msgid "Uh, actually... Probably not. You're kinda tiny."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:488
msgid "* She smiles and pokes my arm. * Hey! I am n-- Ok, I am..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:489
msgid "Beryl: What... What would that do?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:490
msgid "Scare them with noise! It'd work on me..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:491
msgid "Beryl: Oh, yeah!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:492
msgid "Beryl: Actually, I found something the other day. Been k-keeping it hidden. * She's looking at the far side of the basement, which looks just as bleak as the rest of the place."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:493
msgid "* I hold my breath as she skips over electrical debris, dips hanging wires and dodges piles of books. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:494
msgid "What are you even looking for? * She just smiles and carefully slides out from under a workbench."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:495
msgid "Beryl: More Gelcorp tech. I think this is even older than the camera, actually."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:496
msgid "* I watch as she opens the crate and lifts out a truly fucked up looking piece of tech."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:497
msgid "* The chunky television screen flashes on and projects a cursed looking smiling face."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:498
msgid "Excuse me, but what the fuck is that?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:499
msgid "* Beryl laughs. * These were used to prevent workers from hanging out in break rooms and stuff when they were supposed to be working. * She lifts it and walks back to the center of the room."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:500
msgid "* After turning it over a few times, she finds the on-switch and flips it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:501
msgid "* The mouth opens and closes and a barely audible voice flares to life. * REM-EM-brrrrrr rr...."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:502
msgid "Beryl: Hmm, power must be... low. I wonder if I can charge it with the lantern. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:503
msgid "* She unhooks it and plugs it into the face."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:504
msgid "* The lantern immediately blinks out, plunging us into absolute darkness. Before I have a chance to react, two orbs of pure red Ignite in front of me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:505
msgid "* Then it flashes on again, and screeching, saccharine voice blares unevenly out of the screen:"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:506
msgid "------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:507
msgid "Ok... That's terrifying..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:508
msgid "* Then the sharp teeth separate and the maw stretches open, revealing a glowing red light."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:509
msgid "What is this!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:510
msgid "---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:511
msgid "Uhhhh.... BERYL!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:512
msgid "* Beryl smashes the emergency off button and unplugs the machine before it can do whatever it was programmed to do..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:513
msgid "Beryl: Sorry bout t-that!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:514
msgid "Beryl: However, nothing better than microwaves for clearing a break room!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:515
msgid "Yeah, this thing is menacing! You're gonna be scaring the hell out of intruders!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:516
msgid "Beryl: That's the hope. Um, so could you help me get the camera up and running?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:517
msgid "Of course. * I follow Beryl's lead back over to the equipment and carry the chunk of a camera up behind her. I notice that her gait seems much more confident and I can't help but grin."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:518
msgid "* Beryl shows me where she wants the camera and the face to be put up. * Oh, and here! * She hands me a tool belt. * So you can be a real, uh, fixer... person?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:519
msgid "Close enough... So, * I swing the belt on and check out the screwdrivers and measuring tape. A few things I don't even recognize. * How do I look?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:520
msgid "Beryl: Very adorable! * I can't help but blush, but she changes the subject before I can respond. * Batteries!!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:521
msgid "* She digs in her pockets and scoops out a couple of tiny plastic squares. * These should work. * She takes a screwdriver from my belt and unscrews the panel, then flips a switch and a small red light blinks on."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:522
msgid "Beryl: P-perfect! Ok, the door is high up so... * She finds me a ladder and I get to work installing the new camera, teetering precariously on the end of the top rung to screw a camera over the front door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:523
msgid "* I head back over to Beryl. She's setting up a monitor in her nook. * This is supposed to just.... like, connect? Wirelessly... *  she pushes a few buttons. * Ah! There it is!! "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:524
msgid "* I pop my head over her shoulder and see a grainy view of the gravelly entrance. Bad quality, but it'll do the job. I take a seat next to her and we watch it for a bit.."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:525
msgid "So, what happened?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:526
msgid "* Beryl pries her attention away from the monitor. * Oh yeah."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:527
msgid "Beryl: You're g-gonna think I'm an idiot..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:528
msgid "That isn't something I'd ever think, Beryl!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:529
msgid "Beryl: Just w-wait..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:530
msgid "Beryl: S-so, last night I w-was hanging out in my n-nook, reading a book about... * She hesistates..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:531
msgid "Beryl: About vintage... fashion? Anway, that's not important."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:532
msgid "Beryl: I h-hear a thud coming from the back room. I hear..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:533
msgid "* She whispers. * Footsteps!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:534
msgid "Beryl: And... F-for a second I thought my egg h-had sprouted feet!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:535
msgid "Beryl: Obviously n-not thinking st-straight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:536
msgid "Beryl: I run super f-fast, like... way too fast. I'm kind of out of shape! * She giggles."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:537
msgid "Beryl: I r-really didn't expect to see someone but... But right as I get to the back, through the little window on the door..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:538
msgid "* She shudders. * I see someone! A stranger!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:539
msgid "Beryl: I d-dont know what happened to me, HC. B-but I think my motherly instincts kicked in!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:540
msgid "Beryl: Cause all I'm t-thinking about is protecting my lil' egg!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:541
msgid "Beryl: So I run in! * She sighs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:542
msgid "Beryl: I know, this is where I sound so s-stupid."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:543
msgid "Beryl: I don't know how I would have fought this guy... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:544
msgid "Who was it?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:545
msgid "Beryl: No idea! Just some muscly bro."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:546
msgid "Oh, shit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:547
msgid "Beryl: He was rummaging around... And then he sees me, and we are just staring at each other."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:548
msgid "Beryl: I tell him to take anything but my egg. I don't think he knew what it was... Just thought it was an old egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:549
msgid "Did he take anything?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:550
msgid "* Beryl nods. * Uh, yeah. He gets all in my face, tells me to get him my most valuable thing in here or he'd crack the egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:551
msgid "Beryl: I gave him an old painting of the Fossicult founder... I t-think it actually is t-the most valuable thing here..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:552
msgid "Beryl: Besides this little guy. * She hugs her egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:553
msgid "Beryl: I just l-looked down at the egg for w-what seemed like. I don't even know! An hour?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:554
msgid "Beryl: The only thing I could t-think of was how awful a m-mom I am... * She tears up, looking down at her egg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:555
msgid "* She wipes a tear away and giggles. * Oh my goodness. I c-could never be a mom! I c-can't even deal with this egg!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:556
msgid "Beryl: This beautiful little egg..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:557
msgid "Beryl, that's terrifying. I'm just glad you're ok!..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:558
msgid "Beryl: I know! The t-thing is, I always felt safe here cause The Rust Pups are right next door at the school."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:559
msgid "* She smiles. * They're super nice to me... I t-told them what happened and th-they said they'd keep close watch."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:560
msgid "Beryl: Anyway, I'm just glad to have a bit more security. * She wanders back over to me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:561
msgid "Beryl: I feel so much safer, HC. * She looks up at me, pulls my face close to hers and we kiss. Her hands wander up my chest, across my shoulder blades, her fingers tickles the hairs on my neck."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:562
msgid "* I find a comfy position and let her rest her head on my chest. The library is usually a little chilly, but we keep each other warm with cuddles and kisses for a while."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:563
msgid "* Beryl sits up after a while. * All right, Mags is probably wondering where I'm at... Wanna walk back to my apartment?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:564
msgid "* I stretch my arms, help Beryl up, and we walk back into the city."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:565
msgid "I wave at the camera looking down at me from the front door, just in case Beryl's watching."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:566
msgid "* Beryl yells from inside. * WHO GOES THERE! * Then an echoing laughter that leads me to her comfy candle-lit nook."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:567
msgid "* She's sitting cross legged with a book open on her lap, the pages barely illuminated in the dancing candlelight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:568
msgid "* I imagine that Beryl comes in every morning and lights them first thing, just to make the place a little more hospitable."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:569
msgid "* I lean against the cold wall next to her and check out the security system screen. * Seen anything weird?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:570
msgid "Beryl: Nope. Just some m-movement near a storm drain, and what might have been a p-possum. * She looks at the screen * I did see a person, and I got super f-freaked out. * She looks up at me, eyes wide."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:571
msgid "Beryl: B-b-barricaded the doors, got my robot f-face all ready to microwave them!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:572
msgid "* She drops her shoulders and shifts her gaze back to the screen. * But then they reached into their pocket and whipped out three balls and did some juggling..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:573
msgid "Oh, didn't expect that..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:574
msgid "Beryl: It was actually pretty impressive. I almost went out and asked them to teach me! Uh, b-but they could have been a j-juggling killer... so, I didn't."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:575
msgid "Oh, yeah. Never trust a juggler. They could juggle you right out a window."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:576
msgid "So, whatcha readin?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:577
msgid "* Beryl closes the book on her thumb, saving her place, and rotates to the front cover: Housewife Handbook"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:578
msgid "Beryl: It's vintage. Found it while I was scrounging around in the basement. I t-think it's even before Gelcorp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:579
msgid "* She opens it back up and flips around. * Look at this! * She finds a page towards the beginning and hands it to me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:580
msgid "Make sure your man is happy! * The title is bouncy, purple lettering, placed above a drawing of a man in a tuxedo, briefcase in hand leaning in for a kiss from an apron clad lady, big puff of hair, plump red lips. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:581
msgid "Beryl: It's kind of a hilarious read. Like, a whole chapter on how to be presentable for your husband when he returns from his hard day at work... Never let him see you without your makeup!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:582
msgid "So this is how things used to be? * I was programmed with a general knowledge of history but there's a lot I don't know."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:583
msgid "* Beryl flips through the pages. * I think so? But this book is kind of ancient. Honestly, I th-think I prefer the wasteland over whatever this is..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:584
msgid "* She turns to a page with the corner folded. * This outfit is super cute though..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:585
msgid "* She points to a drawing of a woman with a fitted red dress under a yellow apron, tied around her torso. She's posing with a big platter of pink cake."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:586
msgid "Beryl: I mean, it's next to an article about how to make the perfect dessert to satisfy your husband, but it's still super cute."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:587
msgid "* She shuts the book and shifts over to let me slide in next to her. * Anyway, sorry to disturb you with this trash! * She looks uncomfortable, like she's regretting showing me the book."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:588
msgid "* I reach over her and grab it. Flip through the pages looking for the yellow apron. * I don't know... * I hold up the book just under her neck and close one eye. * You'd be adorable. I'd have to get a suit to match."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:589
msgid "* Beryl steals the book back and slams it shut. She blushes. * No way!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:590
msgid "* She looks defiantly up at me. I just smile at her, letting her think for a minute before I open the book back up to the page. She holds my gaze for a second longer and then breaks."
