msgid "Sparky: Acknowledged. Does anyone else - require my assistance?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3463
msgid "* After an awkward pause, Magdelena, clearly not eager to address another droid while in my presence, speaks up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3464
msgid "Magdalena: No, we're ok..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3465
msgid "* The discomfort of the interaction hangs over the table for a bit. My mind races but I don't know what to say."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3466
msgid "Magdalena: Uh, anyway, we should probably roll up a character for you..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3467
msgid "* Cadence bounces on the booth bench. * Ohh! Me! Imma do it! * She slides the books and dice toward her and pulls out a pencil."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3468
msgid "* She flips to the cleric page. * Ok, so you're gonna--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3469
msgid "Magdalena: Oh my god, let her pick her own class."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3470
msgid "* Cadence whispers loudly. * Don't ruin this for me! I need a healer so bad! * She finds a blank character sheet and places it far from Magdalena."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3471
msgid "Cadence: Anyway, cleric. You'll love it. Just chill out, be pious, and solve problems. * She scribbles some stuff on the character sheet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3472
msgid "Cadence: Ok, excellent. Any thoughts on what race you wanna be?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3473
msgid "...I don't know."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3474
msgid "Are there any droid races?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3475
msgid "Cadence: No worries, let's stay classic. You're a human cleric."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3476
msgid "* Cadence frowns. * Hmmm, no. Not in this book, anyway. Imma just stay classic. You're a human cleric."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3477
msgid "* She writes, rolls some dice, then writes a bit more. * Ok, cool! Just one last thing. What do you wanna be named?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3478 result.py:13968
msgid "I... I can't..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3479
msgid "Cadence: Oh, sorry! I forgot that you can't call yourself a different name... Can you just say, 'my characters name is?'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3480
msgid "* Oh, yeah, I think I can do that! Hmmmm, what should I name my character..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3481
msgid "* Beryl smiles. * $. That's a lovely name."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3482
msgid "Cadence: Yes! Good job, HC! Character accomplished!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3483
msgid "Magdalena: Yeah, good work. Next week we'll try and have our shit together. We should probably go now though. See ya!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3484
msgid "Beryl: Yeah, it was really nice seeing you again!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3485
msgid "Cadence: Bye, HC!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3486 result.py:16430
msgid "Bye!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3487
msgid "* I stay and mull the situation over in my head a bit. I'm grateful I've made friends so quickly, but I kinda reflexively distrust them. I don't want that."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3488
msgid "* The usual chime dings as I walk through the door of the Acorn. The group looks like they're already playing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3489
msgid "* Magdalena pauses in her speech and acknowledges me. * I've got a plan to bring you in, don't worry."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3490
msgid "Cadence: Hey, HC! I've got your character sheet! * She thrusts it toward me then turns back to the game. I take a seat next to her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3491
msgid "* Magdalena leans over the crude grid-paper dungeon map before her and lowers her voice. * The door finally gives way and you all tumble into the room."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3492
msgid "Magdalena: Oh, HC. So, the story so far is that the group has been tasked by a very rich business person, Doctor Devlin, to find and defeat a vicious hypnotizing monster."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3493
msgid "Magdalena: She's offering a hefty reward for its defeat, but she wants you to cut out and bring her the heart for confirmation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3494
msgid "Decima: EASY! I was born to rip hearts out of monsters and deliver them to mystery people with lots of money!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3495
msgid "Beryl: What an oddly specific thing to be b-born for."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3496
msgid "Magdalena: Seriously, Decima. So, you've followed Devlin's instructions and entered the underground tunnel system that weaves under the city."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3497
msgid "Magdalena: Now you've entered an old refectory, and you see what appears to be a group of kobolds sitting around a fire."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3498
msgid "Magdalena: Combat time! Roll for initiative."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3499
msgid "* There's a little clatter as everyone starts rolling dice. Cadence whispers at me. * Don't worry, you didn't miss much. This is like the fourth session."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3500
msgid "* Beryl speaks up, excitedly. * Oh my gosh! I'm first? Nice! Wait, d-dang."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3501
msgid "Magdalena: Yes, the initiative is you, Kobolds, Decima, Cadence. Whatcha gonna do?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3502
msgid "Beryl: Ok, hmm... I g-get to my feet, dust off a bit and say, 'Hi, friends!' in, uhhh, Draconian?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3503
msgid "Magdalena: The kobolds kinda hesitate and glance around at each other. A weird, tense calm comes over the room. Decima?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3504
msgid "* Decima lets out a low, throaty cackle and stands up. * I am blessed! * She announces loudly, then takes an obvious dramatic pause."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3505
msgid "Decima: Even here, in this dank sepulcher, the warm light of my god reaches me, bolsters my spirit, grants me the fearlessness to face any foe."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3506
msgid "* Magdalena sighs. * Um, these are Koblolds, but ok. So what do you actually d-"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3507
msgid "* Decima interrupts. * I reach to my side, and in one fluid motion, draw my sword from its scabbard and toss my cape over my shoulder. Blue fire engulfs the blade."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3508
msgid "* Magdalena face-palms. * Oh, Jesus Christ..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3509
msgid "* Decima grins sheepishly. * Yeah, and then, I... You know... Give 'em the chop."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3510
msgid "* A combat ensues, in which the party easily kills the creatures. Decima says a prayer, and the group starts poking around the room."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3511
msgid "* Eventually Cadence discovers that beneath a butchering counter at the back of the room is a large kennel. Magdalena looks at me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3512
msgid "Magdalena: Locked in the kennel is an unconsious, humanoid form, shrowded in filthy clerics robes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3513
msgid "Magdalena: $ begins to stir. HC, welcome to the game. You don't remember how you got here, and you have a throbbing headache."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3514
msgid "* Cadence looks excited. * Time for introductions?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3515
msgid "Magdalena: You tell me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3516
msgid "Cadence: Nice! Ok, I'm, uh, Jam. I'm a tiefling druid and I'm ready to kill. And also, to die, apparently. * She lets out a sardonic laugh."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3517
msgid "* Beryl's quiet voice squeaks with excitement. * Hey! I'm Halva, an elf thief on a q-quest for knowledge! And revenge! And t-treasure! * She giggles."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3518
msgid "Decima: And I am Pigly Gerkin! Chosen of Horsehat, God of the Bountiful Harvest! It is for his honor that I squish, just, tons of dudes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3519
msgid "Horsehat?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3520
msgid "My character is..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3521
msgid "* Decima laughs. * Yeah, Horsehat. He's a gnome god who grants health to the crops of those he favors. I am one of his chosen warriors, an elite member of his holy order. And I love my job."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3522
msgid "Makes sense... So, you're a gnome then?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3523
msgid "Decima: Naturally. * She smiles smugly. * So, who are you, HC?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3524
msgid "I'm, uhhh... * I scan my character sheet. * My character is $, human cleric of... Peylug the sun god. I have, uhhh..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3525
msgid "Magdalena: You actually have nothing right now. The kobolds must have taken your gear, if you had any. You just don't remember. Ok, so what are you gonna do?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3526
msgid "Well, I crawl out of the cage, for one. I guess I'll look around the room for my possessions."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3527
msgid "Decima: And I'll loot the bodies."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3528
msgid "Magdalena: Noted. Anyone else?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3529
msgid "Beryl: Oooh! I check to see if any of them were eating bread! * Everyone chuckles."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3530
msgid "Magdalena: Nice. Ok, yeah, you find some bread. Let's say two loaves."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3531
msgid "* Beryl bounces in her seat. * Oh my gosh! Ok, I c-crack them open and smell them and stuff. Ya know, I analyze them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3532
msgid "* She turns to the rest of us. * I'm t-totally gonna learn about k-kobold culture, you guys!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3533
msgid "Magdalena: Hmm, I feel like I should make you make a check for this. Dunno what'd be though. Your choice, Int or Wis, unless you feel like you have an applicable skill..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3534
msgid "Beryl: I wish I had bread skill! Oh my gosh! I'll just do intelligence. * A die clatters across the table. * It's a... ...16!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3535
msgid "Magdalena: They're both stale and a bit moldy. Beyond that, they're inconsistent. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3536
msgid "Magdalena:  One is dark, sour, and crumbly, maybe rye based? Another is more like French bread, but adorned with a fair amount of mud and twigs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3537
msgid "Beryl: Oh, they're stolen. Ok. That makes s-sense. I still learned something, ok! * She laughs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3538
msgid "* Cadence laughs as well. * Good work, Beryl!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3539
msgid "Magdalena: Ok, Decima. You loot the bodies and find the following things: 17 copper pieces. Some greasy wooden cutlery. And, uuuh, a pouch containing a gold tooth."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3540
msgid "Decima: Gross. Ok, I place the coppers on the kobolds eyes and perform the death rites of Horsehat."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3541
msgid "Magdalena: You're seven pieces short."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3542
msgid "Decima: Fuck, ok, well I ensure that every corpse has at least one copper. Or that tooth. Hmmm..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3543
msgid "* Start gouging eyes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3544
msgid "* Pay my respects."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3545
msgid "I hunch down and use my thumb to squish out six kobold eyeballs. And then I say a prayer. * Everyone laughs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3546
msgid "Decima: Nice."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3547
msgid "I join Decima in prayer. Or something..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3548
msgid "* Decima closes her eyes and looks somber. * Thank you, $."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3549
msgid "Cadence: Ok, should we get out of here?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3550
msgid "Wait, is there anything in here I could use as a weapon? A pan in the kitchen, maybe?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3551
msgid "Magdalena: No, these guys weren't really culinarily advanced enough for a pan. They cook on a crude, grill thing made out of a cuirass with a bunch of holes punched in it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3552
msgid "Magdalena: Hmm, you find a single iron skewer, about a foot long."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3553
msgid "Nice, I grab it. Ok, let's go."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3554
msgid "* Magdalena describes our descent through the dungeon in grisly detail. Kobolds aren't great at cleaning."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3555
msgid "* We order some snacks and clear a few more rooms and then start to wind down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3556
msgid "Magdalena: And that's where we'll leave it, for now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3557
msgid "Cadence: Ah, that was so awesome! You played your first D&D, HC! * She claps me on the back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3558
msgid "Beryl: Yeah, thanks for sh-showing up, HC. This was really fun."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3559
msgid "Agreed. Uh, good job running the game, Magdalena. You did really well... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3560
msgid "* She looks away and kinda blushes. * Thanks... Hey, thanks for this, everyone. I'm glad we're playing again."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3561
msgid "* Beryl grabs her hand. * Aww, of course, Mags!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3562
msgid "* We gather up our stuff, say our goodbyes, and leave."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3563
msgid "* I push through the smudged glass door of the Acorn and scan the humid interior. My friends are bunched up in a booth, flipping pages and spinning dice. I approach."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3564
msgid "Magdalena: Take a seat, HC. We haven't started yet. * She pulls a character sheet out of her notebook and slides it towards me as I squeeze onto the bench next to her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3565
msgid "* Across from me, Beryl smiles and arranges her sparkly dice in a careful little stack. Beside her, Cadence and Decima are sharing a menu."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3566
msgid "Decima: So HC, are you ready to risk life and limb to drive back the forces of evil once more?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3567
msgid "Uh, sure, I guess. Those little lizards didn't strike me as particularly evil though. Why were we even in their house?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3568
msgid "* Decima laughs. * They kidnapped you! And tied you up and beat and robbed you! You must wreak your bloody vengeance upon them! Also, it was a dungeon, not a house."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3569
msgid "Magdalena: Don't tell her how to play her character, Decima."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3570
msgid "Cadence: Yeah, you're the only 'bloody vengeance' character! We do not need a second."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3571
msgid "Decima: Psh.. There's no such thing as too much bloody vengeance. * She grins."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3572
msgid "Magdalena: You just thank Horsehat I don't change your alignment. So, does anyone remember where we were?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3573
msgid "Beryl: Yes! We had just made it to the deep antechamber, several floors below the refactory. I found the secret door by following the smell of baked goods, but it turned out to just be ogre deodorant."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3574
msgid "Decima: De-ogre-ant."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3575
msgid "* Magdalena tries to sound stern but can't help cracking a smile. * Yes, we all recall the joke, Decima."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3576
msgid "Magdalena: Ok, so you're in the antechamber, standing in front of a dead ogre, opposite an altar. Solemn faces are carved into the walls and the smells of flour and ogre sweat fill your noses. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3577
msgid "Magdalena: What would you like to do?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3578
msgid "Cadence: I search the body!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3579
msgid "Beryl: Can I tell what kind of craftsmanship any of this is? Like, who wove the Tapestries and carved the symbols and stuff?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3580
msgid "Magdalena: I dunno, make a knowledge check. Cadence, you find four gold pieces tucked inside a sweaty loincloth."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3581
msgid "* Decima talks over the sound of clattering d20's. * Hmm, speaking of flour and sweat, should we get something? * She flicks the menu with her metal hand."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3582
msgid "Cadence: Ooh! We could get a pudding pillar or something, to share?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3583
msgid "Decima: I'm more in the mood for something pungent and fried, but you can snag a pud-pi if you'd like. * She waves across the room. * Hey, Sparky, old chap!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3584
msgid "* While Decima places an order for some kind of hot, fungal dumpling, Magdalena describes the finer details of the items that decorate the room. It's unlikely that they're of kobold make, but who knows."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3585
msgid "Cadence: So, the kobolds are the only followers? How do they maintain this sick churchly aesthetic? They don't even have thumbs I'm pretty sure. Hmm..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3586
msgid "Beryl: Maybe it's dragon magic. HC, you're a cleric, maybe you know something about this altar or something?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3587
msgid "Sure, let's find out. * I roll my knowledge check. It's a 19. Cadence slaps me on the back playfully."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3588
msgid "Magdalena: Nice. Ok, you've heard of the Church of the Dragonpact before, they're mostly human dragon worshipers known for the foolish task of building their temples on top of dragons dens."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3589
msgid "Beryl: Hmm, perhaps they were killed off, and the kolbolds took over."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3590
msgid "Decima: Wait, what do you mean 'on top of dragons dens?' Is there an actual dragon under us? I pull out my sword."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3591
msgid "Beryl: I guess I search the room for secret doors, starting with the altar. There must be a way to get to the dragon."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3592
msgid "* Decima smiles with mock sincerity. * Poor, sweet, innocent Beryl. I'm a paladin. Pretty sure altars are my area of expertise. Stand aside. * She grabs a handful of dice."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3593
msgid "Decima: I... Uh, kick it... * Some dice roll across the table."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3594
msgid "Magdalena: Uh ok. You hit but it's like a stone altar. Nothing happens."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3595
msgid "Decima: Shit. Hmm... Can I maybe scrape it up a bit with the pommel of my sword?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3596
msgid "Magdalena: Sure. The altar is now scuffed, I guess."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3597
msgid "Decima: Ok, fuck it, I piss on the altar."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3598
msgid "* Everyone sighs as Magdalena describes the scene. * ...You zip up your pants, leaving the altar a bit damp..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3599
msgid "Cadence: Ok, cool plan Decima. Who has an actual idea?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3600
msgid "Magdalena: A rumble shakes the floor, then a moment later, a super loud terrifying screech echoes through the chamber. It sounds like it's coming from deep below. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3601
msgid "Decima: Yeah that's right, this bitch knows how to defile! * She gives her chest a quick pound just as the dumplings arrive, which she tucks into victoriously."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3602
msgid "Cadence: Nice, you just awoke the dragon you fucking dingus. I'm your friend and I need to know why you're tryna get vored."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3603
msgid "Decima: Have faith, peasant. Surely that was just an exceptional snore."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3604
msgid "* Magdalena smirks. * The floor begins to collapse into a large natural cave. Everyone roll initiative. And a reflex save, I guess."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3605
msgid "Beryl: Oh, jeez, can we hold up? I need to go to the bathroom."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3606
msgid "Cadence: Me too! Come on, Decima. * She grabs Decima by the vest and pulls her out of the seat behind Beryl, then they all disappear into the bathroom."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3607
msgid "* Magdalena's expression goes cold and her eyes narrow in a very familiar way. She stares at her notepad."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3608 result.py:9662 result.py:17979
msgid "What's wrong?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3609
msgid "So, uh, a dragon, huh?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3610
msgid "Magdalena: ...Nothing. I'm just not feeling this right now... * She keeps her eyes down while talking."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3611
msgid "Come on, I know that's not true?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3612
msgid "I'm sure they'll be back soon."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3613
msgid "Wanna get out of here?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3614
msgid "Magdalena: Yeah, you liked that, huh? You know, I spent a lot of time prepping this game. * She opens the notebook, revealing pages of handwritten notes. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3615
msgid "You did a really good job, as usual... * I'm a little confused, but I take another shot. * I'm excited to get back to the game..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3616
msgid "* She turns and glares at me, her expression cold and hateful. Shit... * What's wrong?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3617
msgid "Magdalena: Yeah. Cool. They're gonna be able to tell, too. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3618 result.py:8611 result.py:9664 result.py:16853 result.py:18378
#: result.py:18743 result.py:19005
msgid "What do you mean?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3619
msgid "Magdalena: They're gonna be able to tell that I'm upset. I'm not gonna be able to DM. I ruined the game."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3620
msgid "Magdalena: Yeah, you're right. They probably didn't even fuck up. Why am I like this..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3621
msgid "Magdalena, it's ok to be upset... You--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3622
msgid "Magdalena: No it isn't. They're gonna think I'm a fucking freak. I'm not gonna be able to DM. I ruined the game."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3623
msgid "You didn't ruin it, for real. You're trying your best to deal with a difficult thing. If you're worried about it, I can talk to them..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3624
msgid "* She glances out the window. * Yeah. Or, I dunno... They're gonna come back and I'll be gone. They'll think I'm mad or something."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3625
msgid "They're your friends, they'll understand."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3626
msgid "Magdalena: If they understood, then... * She goes quiet, staring off. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3627
msgid "* I'm kind of at a loss. I don't want to make things worse... * They really will, Magdalena. If you're worried about it, I can talk to them..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3628
msgid "Magdalena: Nah, think about it. We leave, they think I'm upset. We stay, I can't be happy and social enough to DM right. We... I... * Her breathing accelerates and the muscles in her shoulders tense."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3629
msgid "We can deal with them later."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3630
msgid "* Put a hand on her shoulder."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3631
msgid "* Her body immediately stiffens and her fingers curl around her notebook. I let go, realizing my mistake and trying to calm myself before I start freaking out too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3632
msgid "* Magdalena swallows and remains motionless."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3633
msgid "* I scramble for something to say. Before realizing I'm almost as stiff as she is. I take a deep breath. Oh, that's a good one..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3634
msgid "Breathe, Mags, come on. It's gonna be ok. I promise..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3635
msgid "* She sighs and looks at my hands. Not much, but that's something..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3636
msgid "You're the one feeling bad right now. It's not on you to take care of them. They can deal with it. Seriously, let's go find somewhere more comfortable for you right now. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3637
msgid "* I slide out of the bench, making room for her. In a bit, the tension ebbs, if only slightly, and she scoots out after me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3638
msgid "* I let her pass in front of me, then start following her to the door, but she turns around. Her face is expressionless, but her eyes are brimming with tears and her jaw is tensed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3639
msgid "Magdalena: No. Stay here. Tell them... Something. * She turns and takes a few steps towards the door before pausing. * Thanks, HC. * She mumbles, then leaves the diner."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3640
msgid "* I wait for them, kinda paralyzed. I have no idea what to say, all I know is that it's gonna be uncomfortable. I watch Decima's dumplings cool and wrinkle on her plate for a few minutes before the group returns."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3641
msgid "* I tell them very little. It seems weird to speak for Magdalena. She just left, that's all. They start awkwardly gathering their things. Beryl comments about how she needs to go check on her. The group disbands."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3642
msgid "* I sit there alone, staring out the window for a few minutes, unable to think through the fog of tension. I just hope this hasn't set us back. Set Magdalena back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3643
msgid "* I get up and head out through the dark streets towards home."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3644
msgid "* D&D is at the library today. I think Magdalena wants a quieter place to DM."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3645
msgid "* We all huddle in front of Beryl's little nook. The crumbling concrete walls loom into twisted obsucrity beyond our little ring of candles."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3646
msgid "Decima: Ok, this is legit the best location we've ever played in. I feel like I'm in a goddamn troll cave!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3647
msgid "Beryl: Hey! * She gives Decima a little shove."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3648
msgid "Decima: In the best way possible, B! A cute and magical troll cave!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3649
msgid "Magdalena: All right, everyone ready? We stopped kinda suddenly last time... If you remember. * I do. It's awkward..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3650
msgid "Cadence: We left off at the perfect moment! An intense cliffhanger! A massive hole just opened under us, right?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3651
msgid "Magdalena: Yes, precisely. So now you all have to make a reflex save!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3652
msgid "Beryl: O-oh, HC! I got you a little pack of dice!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:3653
