msgid "Sal: You know... * He walks up to the wall, takes a good, long look. * I think it is."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11286
msgid "* The frame is anything but high-quality, but the resemblance is undeniable."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11287
msgid "Sal: And look at the timestamp. This is days after his wife last saw him. Same day you say the, uh, 'Anomaly' started."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11288
msgid "Sal: That's a lead, if I ever saw one."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11289
msgid "Forcier: You don't look pleased."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11290
msgid "Sal: Pleased that he was last seen at Gelpcorp? 'Fraid not. You did some good sleuthing, but we still ain't ready to wake that particular dragon."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11291
msgid "* He pauses. * Ignoring all that, I have another lead to investigate. An easier one, although not by much."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11292
msgid "Sal: I've been poking around, and it turns out that the wife's last known location was upper Skipnoise Ave. Otter territory."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11293
msgid "* He pauses. * Besides, I have another lead to investigate. An easier one, although not by much."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11294
msgid "Sal: So We've got Greene's last sighting. I've been poking around, and it turns out that the wife's last known location was upper Skipnoise Ave. Otter territory."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11295
msgid "Sal: Follow this up, and I think we can start painting the picture."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11296
msgid "Sal: You know about the Otters, right?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11297
msgid "I know about the Otters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11298
msgid "Refresh my memory?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11299
msgid "Sal: Sure thing. Alright, so there are a few gangs in Pira city. We got the Rust Pups, the Tunnel Girls, and the Otters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11300
msgid "Sal: Now, the Rust Pups will treat you good as long as you ain't a corpo, and the Tunnel Girls keep to themselves..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11301
msgid "Sal: ...But the Otters? They're trouble. * Sal takes another pull. * The kinda trouble that wouldn't mind snipping your digits if ya know what I'm sayin'."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11302
msgid "Sal: Then you know they're trouble. * He takes another pull. * The kinda trouble that wouldn't mind snipping your digits if ya know what I'm sayin'."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11303
msgid "* Decima giggles anxiously. * Um, gulp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11304
msgid "* The room goes still. We kinda look around at each other, hoping, once again, that we haven't gotten in over our collective head. City sounds and Sal's mechanical wheezing are all that stands between us and silence."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11305
msgid "Sal: I'm thinking we oughta pay the Otters a visit. See if they know anything. It's a risk, but I 've already talked to everyone else in the area. They all point to the gang."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11306
msgid "* Sal navigates around the stacked boxes to a dirty ashtray resting on his windowsill, stumps out his only half-smoked cigarette. * I could use some backup. Some muscle, ya know? "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11307
msgid "* He turns back around, faces us. * I can make it worth your while. You need info on Gelcorp, and she and her husband have it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11308
msgid "Olivia: Yeah, yeah. It's mutually beneficial, sure, but why us? There's plenty of better muscle for hire in Pira City."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11309
msgid "Sal: Well, I was hoping the information would be enough payment. Not exactly coming down with coupons, these days. Especially since the wife went missing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11310
msgid "Sal: If there's one thing I've learned in my years on this job, it's that you stick close to anyone on the same trail as you. Especially if that trail leads somewhere bad. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11311
msgid "Sal: So, any of you think you can help?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11312
msgid "* This is starting to feel familiar. A few among the group look my way, but I know that even those who aren't looking expect me to volunteer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11313
msgid "* Another little battle wages in my head. Help, or hurt. Hold together the group with my droid strength, or retreat into futile dreams of true humanity."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11314
msgid "* I focus on my breathing, every movement simulated to disguise the metal in my core."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11315
msgid "* Beryl's quiet voice pulls me out of my little spiral. * Hey, HC? You don't have to do it if you don't wanna. We can figure something else out. No pressure, ok?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11316
msgid "* She's so sweet. Knowing she's here for me is all I need. * It's ok, I can do it. * I turn toward Sal. * I'm strong as hell and I'll totally back you up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11317
msgid "Sal: Good to hear. Alright, the plan is simple. We walk into their restaurant, find the boss, ask him some questions. Things go south, we focus on getting out. That's it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11318
msgid "* Beryl hugs my arm. * I can come with you, if you need me to. Anything you want, HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11319
msgid "Sal: Look, we bring you along, and your friend here is just gonna have another person to worry about. No offense, but you don't look like much of a brawler."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11320
msgid "* Magdalena scoots in closer, and I prepare to endure her wrath. Something about how I'm putting her girlfriend at risk. She looks calmer than I would have expected, though."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11321
msgid "Magdalena: No offense, Bear, but maybe emotional support is best served on the way home. I think I can like, actually have your backs in there."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11322
msgid "Sal: Oh, you do, do you? I wouldn't have pegged you as a heavy either."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11323
msgid "Magdalena: Trust me, HC has got that part covered. What you two are lacking is confidence. * She flips her hair back over her shoulder, cracks a little smile. * And I've got that shit on lock."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11324
msgid "* She turns away. * I mean, however you wanna do it is fine, I'm just saying."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11325
msgid "* We look around at each other. Beryl seems confident in Mags, and ok with either option. I guess it comes down to my choice."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11326
msgid "It's too risky, I'll take Mags."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11327
msgid "Maybe it'd be better if you came, Beryl."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11328
msgid "* Mags cocks her head, kinda smirks at me. She looks pleased."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11329
msgid "* Beryl gives me a quick, understanding nod, then scoots over to Magdalena. I could probably make out their whispering, but instead, I turn my attention back to Sal."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11330
msgid "Sal: Alright, no skin off my ass. Let's just make sure this all goes smooth. * Sal pulls an engraved metallic box out of one of his desk drawers, opens it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11331
msgid "Sal: If you don't mind, I'd like a few more of you to keep the van running, keep eyes on the guards, that kinda thing. You game? * He lifts a small, well-worn velvet pouch out of the box, followed by a sleek black shape."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11332
msgid "* He sets both on the desktop. The sound of them against the wood betrays their considerable weight. A gun, and as he opens the pouch to reveal, bullets."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11333
msgid "* Magdalena's haughty voice sounds first. * Yeah, it's no problem. I'll drive."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11334
msgid "Olivia: I'll keep you company."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11335
msgid "* Decima springs out of her chair. * Me too! I'll man the-- * Sal cuts her off."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11336
msgid "Sal: Two is plenty. Everyone else, just hang back and keep in contact."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11337
msgid "* With a flick of the wrist, a cylinder swings out of the side of the gun. As he begins to load bullets into its eight slots, a yellow LED ignites near the grip."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11338
msgid "* Sal studies the bands of sunlight painting the room, crawling up the back wall. Sun must be getting low. When the gun's loaded, he snaps the cylinder back into place. The LED changes from yellow to orange."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11339
msgid "* There's silence as he sweeps his coat aside to reveal a shoulder holster, tucks the gun away. The weight of the situation begins to rest heavy on our backs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11340
msgid "Sal: Let's meet up again when you're all ready. No point in rushing in. * He takes a seat at the desk, pulls a glass and a bottle of something dark out of the bottom drawer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11341
msgid "* He clears his throat, coughs that static, augmented cough. He hammers a few keys on the keyboard and the still from the security footage starts chugging out of his printer. * Good luck out there. Stay safe. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11342
msgid "* We file out of the apartment and into the hall. Forcier & Olivia don't have far to go, and Beryl and Mags stop off at The Acorn, so I walk home with Decima and Cadence."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11343
msgid "* We share our thoughts, our fears, our hopes for the mission. I guess everyone is pretty aware of the Otters and their reputation.  "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11344
msgid "* Getting inside with Magdalena is gonna be... I dunno, interesting at least. Maybe it'll help her trust me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11345
msgid "* Getting inside with Beryl is gonna be dangerous. I'm thankful for her support, but I hope she doesn't get hurt..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11346
msgid "* Probably not something I should worry about now, though. I part ways with the others and head home."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11347
msgid "* My mission with Sal and the Otters has been on my mind since I woke up. Too many emotions and anxieties. I dunno what to think, so I try not to, instead just mindlessly get dressed and set out for Root St."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11348
msgid "* Only I can't. Before I even make it to the door, I hear a knock. Mags is waiting in the hallway, her furrowed brow and knife-sharp eyeliner piercing my clouded mind and reeling me back into the present."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11349
msgid "Oh, hey, Mags. I thought I was supposed to meet you at Sal's?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11350
msgid "* She sighs. * Ugh, yeah right, like I'm just gonna hang out with that creepy old man till you show up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11351
msgid "That's honestly valid."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11352
msgid "He saved our lives..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11353
msgid "* Mags smiles. * Right? Like, is he aware of the serial killer vibe his apartment is giving off? And that fucking fedora? Um, eww? * Her laughs echo out into the hallway as we depart."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11354 result.py:11362
msgid "* I lead her out and down the ruined streets that border the chasm, imagining a picturesque esplanade overlooking a black sea. Imagining Magdalena."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11355
msgid "* Despite her perpetual pushback during our previous interactions, she seems a little more present today. I try and keep up hope that she'll have my back for this mission. I don't know what'll happen if she doesn't..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11356
msgid "* During our walk I keep the conversation light, aware that if I set her off, that precious hope will be dispelled."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11357
msgid "* She laughs. * Yeah, cause he wants the pleasure of murdering us himself, probably. I mean, who wouldn't want to murder this? * She gestures at her body, outfit, etc."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11358
msgid "Um, I don't know how to answer that question."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11359
msgid "Magdalena: Yeah, that was just a joke, HC. No need to overthink it, or whatever."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11360
msgid "Ok, cool. * I pause. * Wait, so are you actually worried about him, or....."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11361
msgid "* Mags rolls her eyes, like clarity is uncool or something. * Are we going?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11363
msgid "* I wonder about whether or not she was afraid that if her joke needed explanation, it wasn't as good as she thought?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11364
msgid "* Or was I supposed to be confused? At least the lack of rapport between Mags and I keeps my mind off the Otters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11365 result.py:11494
msgid "* We emerge from the clutching rebar fingers of Root Street's concrete-strewn margins into the familiar glow of the Acorn. Next door, Sal is smoking in the stair box of his apartment building."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11366
msgid "* He stubs his cigarette out on the wall when he sees us approach. * You two ready?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11367
msgid "* Before I can answer, Mags cuts in. * We're here, aren't we?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11368
msgid "Sal: I can see that. * There's a pause, then he cracks a little smile. * I'm a private investigator, remember? "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11369
msgid "* He doesn't wait for laughs, fortunately. * I'm gonna pull the van around. Sit tight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11370 result.py:11499
msgid "* He disappears around the corner of the alleyway, then, after a loud crack and some electrical popping, the van turns into the street."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11371 result.py:11500
msgid "* He leans out the window. * Get in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11372
msgid "* I slide the door open for Mags, then join her in the back. It's dark, and similar to his office, packed with cardboard and garbage. Whatever. There's still plenty of space to sit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11373 result.py:11502
msgid "* As the van rumbles off toward Skipnoise Ave, I inquire about the specifics of the plan. * So, what should we expect once we get inside the Otter's Nest?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11374 result.py:11503
msgid "* Sal doesn't tear his eyes from the road. * Dunno. The boss of the Otters should be there, but other than that, no idea."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11375
msgid "Magdalena: Um, excuse me?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11376 result.py:11505
msgid "Sal: Look, kid, I know it doesn't sound right, but in this job, information is everything. We don't know what's in the Otters Nest, but we've got a surefire way of finding out. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11377 result.py:11506
msgid "Sal: Don't worry about it, I've done this kinda thing plenty uh times. Killing is messy. The worst that could happen is we get roughed up a bit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11378
msgid "Magdalena: Whoa, whoa, hold the fuck up. You thought I was worried about being slain? Cause, now I fucking am."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11379
msgid "* She leans into the front of the van, grabs Sal's collar. * And also, roughed up? I don't wanna get roughed up. Tell me I'm not in physical danger, motherfucker!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11380
msgid "* Sal just smiles. * I like you, Kiddo. Ya got balls."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11381
msgid "* Mags and I give each other a knowing, trans-girl glance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11382 result.py:11510
msgid "Sal: I said don't worry. We ain't gonna get hurt. That's why I brought this. * He spreads his trench coat to the side to reveal a fat revolver tucked into a shoulder holster."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11383
msgid "* Mags collapses back into her seat. * Oh, great, our elderly cowboy chaperone brought his big iron. You know it's insane to gunfight the mob, right? * She turns to me. * We're gonna die. Are we gonna die?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11384
msgid "No. We've got me and my droid abilities."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11385
msgid "Wasn't your job supposed to be confidence?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11386
msgid "* She just rests her head against my shoulder and tries to believe in me. I guess we both need to work on our faith in each other. Anxiety swims in my head for the remainder of the silent car ride."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11387
msgid "* Magdalena scowls. * Yeah, that's really not helping, HC. * For the rest of the silent ride, she just stares out the window."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11389 result.py:11517
msgid "* The van chugs to a halt around the corner from the Otter's Nest. We unload, head for the club. Outside, we can see a beefy bouncer in the Otter's signature navy and gold. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11390 result.py:11518
msgid "* Each of my footsteps seems too loud, too offensive to the glaring eyes of the Bouncer. Even keeping my eyes down and walking on would be hard, but stopping? Confronting? Static clouds of panic form in my mind. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11391 result.py:11519
msgid "* Sal stops us in front of the guy, looks up his six and a half foot frame and into his beady, helmeted eyes. * We're here to see Boss Barnes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11392 result.py:11520
msgid "* The bouncer glares at us. * Uh huh. Is he expecting you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11393 result.py:11521
msgid "Sal: No, not... as such. But we're here to see if we can make a deal with him."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11394 result.py:11522
msgid "* The bouncer squares up, which was honestly unnecessary. His thick, meaty bulk was intimidating enough without him getting up in our shit. * Oh yeah? Who even are you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11395
msgid "* Mags pushes between Sal and I and stares the bastard down, her anxiety apparently completely gone. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11396
msgid "Magdalena: Excuse me? But I don't think you heard my friend right. We're here to deal with Him, not with some fucking... * She gestures at him. * Faceless peon."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11397
msgid "Magdalena: Like, who are we? Who the fuck are you? If you can't point us to the boss, maybe you can point us to someone a step up from the entry level of your gang. Someone who actually matters. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11398
msgid "* The bouncer growls. * Entry level? I've been an Otter for almost three years. I--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11399
msgid "* Mags cuts him off. * Oh, honey. That long and he still has you out here on the street? At the Entrance to the club? If that's not entry level, nothing is."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11400
msgid "Bouncer: Enough games, get the fu--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11401
msgid "* Again, Mags interrupts. * These aren't games, my guy. Maybe that attitude is why you're not inside with the real Otters. This is a classy place. I know I wouldn't let you in dressed like that."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11402
msgid "* His scowl droops. * I'm not... Wait, what's wrong with how I dressed?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11403
msgid "* Magdalena laughs, cold and cutting. * God, where to even begin. Honestly, if you can't see it, there's no hope. Just imagine Boss Barnes. Can you picture him giving someone like you the time of day?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11404
msgid "Bouncer: Sh-shut up, you little... Jerk! I have a job to do!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11405
msgid "* Satisfied with the power shift, she closes in for the kill. A foot forward, a hand on his shoulder. * Leave. There's still time. Return when you don't look like utter dogshit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11406
msgid "* He glances around for a moment, conflicted, tears in his eyes, then hoofs it off down Skipnoise Avenue. We're in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11407
msgid "* Sal looks a little amazed. * Well god damn, kid. Good job."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11408
msgid "* When the bouncer makes it out of sight, Mags takes my hand. Her tight grip and damp palm tells me that she's struggling more than she's letting on. I squeeze back as we follow Sal inside."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11409 result.py:11533
msgid "* The heavy double doors swing wide, and we feel a few sets of eyes tear away from their dinner conversations. The jazzy piano music doesn't waver, nor does the din of diatribe."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11410 result.py:11534
msgid "* Most of the guests don't appear affiliated, but some deep purple suits and gold ties are visible through the cigar-haze, as well as the more typical Otter jerseys. Sal scans the room, then nods towards a booth in the back. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11411 result.py:11535
msgid "* In it are several large gentlemen, none larger than the obvious boss. Gleaming golden watch and pinstripe vest aside, he looks like royalty. With all the cybernetics in his head, he might as well be wearing a crown."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11412
msgid "* His hammer-like forehead is polished to chrome, except for one dark imperfection off to the side. A bullet impact, by its look. A scar he musn't want to hide."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11413 result.py:11537
msgid "* We follow Sal towards the booth. It's in a strategically solid position against the back wall."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11414 result.py:11538
msgid "* It has a clear view of everything, including the stage, upon which a gorgeous droid, dressed in hologram streamers, is playing a piano."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11415 result.py:11539
msgid "* The boss watches us approach, beckons to a pair of goons, who step up to the table and join him in watching. As we arrive at the table, the goons step forward. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11416 result.py:11540
msgid "* One of the suited men next the boss speaks up before Sal has a chance. * This oughtta be fuckin' good. You know you're interrupting the bosses lunch, right?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11417 result.py:11541
msgid "* The table, while laden with cigar butts and semi-full glasses, is completely free of food. I quietly wonder about the definition of lunch."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11418 result.py:11542
msgid "Sal: My apologies. Lemme introduce myself. I'm Salvadore, P.I. I've been hired to find a guy who disappeared from the Gelcorp compound. * The pile of meaty dudes look annoyed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11419 result.py:11543
msgid "Sal: Uh, I don't wanna bore you with the details, but see, the woman who hired me? The wife? She's gone missing. I asked around and was pointed here. So..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11420 result.py:11544
msgid "* He reaches into his coat and the two goons lurch forward. Everyone freezes. * Hey, Hey! Look! I'm just... * He very slowly pulls a photograph out of his inside pocket and drops it on the table."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11421
msgid "Sal: Have you seen this woman? Goes by Mrs. Greene? * We all hold our breath as the boss leans forward, gives it a glance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11422 result.py:11546
msgid "Boss Barnes: Information is money, old man. What do you have to offer me?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11423 result.py:11547
msgid "Sal: I'm not asking you to go out of your way, I'm just tryna find the gal. Gotta talk to her about her husband. Do me a favor, huh?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11424 result.py:11548
msgid "* The boss leans back in the booth, snaps his fingers. The muscle closes in, grabs Sal by the collar. He wheezes and coughs as the meatball of a man lifts him off his feet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11425 result.py:11549
msgid "* Intervene."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11426 result.py:11550
msgid "* I step up to the guy, grab his wrist, calmly force it down till Sal is back on his feet. Another goon steps in, tries to pull me away, but I stand firm."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11427
msgid "* Every second of this tense, methodical action brings us closer to an all out brawl, or even worse, a gunfight. I could fight my way out of this guys grip, but not without putting us at risk.  "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11428
msgid "* Mags glides out from behind me again, face cold and calm as a mercury bath. * Bad move, big boy. You don't know what you're looking at, do you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11429 result.py:11434
msgid "Mags: Of course not. That's a Bellamy Intelligence Bioex. Only a couple thousand were made. And you can bet this is the only one that ended in up in this shithole of a city."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11430
msgid "* Mags stares expectantly. * What, you're not gonna let her go? You'd rather find out what she's capable of? * She puts her hands up, takes a step back. * Your call, I guess."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11431
msgid "* He lets me go. I follow suit and relinquish his buddie's wrist."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11432
msgid "* I just stand there, frozen in fear. It's all going to shit so fucking quick. I have no idea why I thought my traumatized mind could be any fucking use here..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11433
msgid "* But then Mags glides out from behind me again, face cold and calm as a mercury bath. * Bad move, big boy. You don't know what you're looking at, do you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11435
msgid "Mags: How about you set our guy down so I don't have to watch you get your skull caved in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11436
msgid "* Grumbling, the goon slowly lowers Sal back down to the ground and relinquishes his grip on his coat. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11437 result.py:11561
msgid "Boss Barnes: You three are lucky, you know that? If I were not so preoccupied with my lunch, I wouldn't mind letting things get messy."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11438
msgid "Boss Barnes:  I will give you a chance to walk outta here right now before letting my guys do their jobs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11439 result.py:11563
msgid "* Sal goes to speak but Barnes cuts him off. * You see, my guys? They love their jobs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11440 result.py:11564
msgid "* Sal scowls hard. * Alright, I apologize for disturbing you and your... associates. Anything I can do to make things right? And to compensate you for the information?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11441 result.py:11565
msgid "* The boss smiles. * As a matter of fact, there is something you could do for me. * He takes a sip off his drink, then snaps again, this time at a nearby robo-waiter."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11442 result.py:11566
msgid "Boss Barnes: A Gelcorp security depot has popped up real close to Otter territory. I have it on good authority that the Rust Pups are gonna raid it, try and capture their assets. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11443 result.py:11567
msgid "Boss Barnes: I want you to burn it to the fucking ground. Teach Gelcorp and the Rust Pups that they can't act in our territory. I want you to show up before the pups so they can watch it burn."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11444 result.py:11568
msgid "* The boss smiles. * Does that sound like a fair trade to you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11445
msgid "* Sal shifts his weight uncomfortable. * I dunno... Getting in between Gelcorp and the Rust Pups? Not sure we're qualified for that kinda--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11446 result.py:11570
msgid "* Barnes holds up his hand, silencing Sal. * You have your offer. Take it, and get your info, or... * He stands to his full, massive height, servos of an unseen augmentation groaning under his weight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11447 result.py:11571
msgid "Barnes: Or don't ever let me or my guys see your face again. * He turns to the meat-head standing next to him. * Show em the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11448 result.py:11572
msgid "* Not wanting to be too thoroughly manhandled, we hurry away, ahead of the muscle. Outside, we keep up a brisk walk towards to street corner behind which we parked the van."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11449
msgid "Magdalena: So, we're fucked, right? We just got railroaded into an insanely stupid, dangerous plan by a fuck ton of bloodthirsty mobsters. Gelcorp and the Rust Pups both shoot to kill."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11450 result.py:11575
msgid "* Sal smiles, chuckles a little. The cigars once again emerge from his inner coat pocket, and he turns away from the breeze to light one."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11451
msgid "* Mags puts her fists on her hips. * What the hell is so funny, my guy?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11452
msgid "Sal: Ya did great in there, kid. That was some kinda confidence, staring down those Otters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11453 result.py:11579
msgid "* I touch her shoulder. * He's right, you were amazing. I don't know how I would have done that without you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11454
msgid "* Mags turns away, frowns, tries to shrug off the pride. * Yeah, Obviously. Those guys were pussies."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11455
msgid "Sal: Don't worry about the job. There's always another angle. I'll see what I can dig up. * He takes a long drag on the cigar."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11456
msgid "* Mags sulks. * I hope you know that your whole detective schtick is really fucking abrasive."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11457
msgid "Sal: Looks like we got that in common, kid."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11458 result.py:11581
msgid "* We pile into the van and it lurches to life. As Skipnoise recedes into the dusty, ruinous horizon, the anxiety begins to drain from my limbs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11459
msgid "* When we arrive on Root Street, Mags is still brooding."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11460 result.py:11583
msgid "Sal: I know that things seem rough, but this is what progress looks like. It's not gonna be easy, never was, but we can do this. We'll think of something."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11461 result.py:11584
msgid "Sal: You two keep your ears to the ground. * He pulls the van in behind his building, opens the door. * And stay safe."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11462 result.py:11585
msgid "Thanks, Sal. I appreciate your help with this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11463 result.py:11586
msgid "* We all get out, stare at each other for a sec before Sal speaks up. * Likewise."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11464 result.py:11587
msgid "* Then he disappears into the darkness of the alleyway."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11465
msgid "* Mags and I start our walk back home. It's quiet for a bit. * You ok?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11466
msgid "Mags: Yeah, why wouldn't I be?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11467
msgid "I dunno. All that stuff you said? About the danger?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11468
msgid "* She frowns. * If you think I'm worried, then why would you bring that up?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11469
msgid "I dunno, just... * I clear my throat. * I want you to know that I've got your back... Droid strength, and all that..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11470
msgid "Mags: Yeah... And I've obviously got your back. * She blushes. * I mean, it'd be stupid if I didn't."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11471 result.py:11594
msgid "Yeah, I know. We've totally got this. * I grin and flex my arms. * You and me? Unstoppable."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11472
msgid "Mags: Unstoppable..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11473 result.py:11596
msgid "* We part ways, her to her house, me to mine. No goodbyes. Don't wanna spoil the note we left it on."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11474 result.py:11597
msgid "* I walk the rest of the way alone under the murky night sky, wishing I was tired, wishing my mind wasn't flooded with bad options and worse outcomes. Wishing we didn't have to deal with the Otters at all."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11475 result.py:11598
msgid "* Especially on top of Gelcorp. I don't want to crack heads or risk getting shot. Risk losing my friends. I just want to go to bed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11476
msgid "* My mission with Sal and the Otters has been on my mind since I woke up this morning."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11477
msgid "*  Too many emotions and anxieties... I dunno what to think, so I try not to, instead just mindlessly getting dressed and setting out for Root St."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11478
msgid "* Only I can't. Before I even make it to the door, I hear a knock. Beryl is waiting in the hallway, her nervous bouncing and tired eyes reeling me back into the present."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11479
msgid "Oh, hey, Beryl. I though I was supposed to meet you at Sals?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11480
msgid "Beryl: I know but... I just can't wait around right now, n-not with my mind racing like this. I barely slept!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11481
msgid "Me either..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11482
msgid "It'll be ok."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11483
msgid "Beryl: Aww... Well we can take a nap or something! After this is over with... * Her giggle echoes out into the hallway as we depart."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11484
msgid "* I lead her out and down the ruined streets that border the chasm, imagining a picturesque esplanade overlooking a black sea. Imagining Beryl."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11485
msgid "* Despite the interruption in her usual chillness, I sense her bravery. I know she has my back and I already feel safer with her here. I try not to think about what could happen if things go wrong..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11486
msgid "* During our walk down the ruined streets that borders the chasm, I keep the conversation light, unsure how to broach the topic of the danger that awaits us. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11487
msgid "Beryl: Yeah, totally. I've got your back, and I know you h-have mine. Plus, Sal seems experienced with this kinda thing. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11488
msgid "* Just as predicted, Beryl is already doing her job. * Thanks. We've got this. And yeah, Sal seems, well... I dunno about trustworthy, but capable for sure."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11489
msgid "Beryl: Oh, you d-don't trust him? Did he d-do something?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11490
msgid "Not at all, I mean, he saved our lives. I guess trustworthy isn't the right word. Maybe I'm just generally anxious. * I laugh, but it's obviously strained."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11491
msgid "Beryl: Well, that's what I'm here for. * She takes my and and cozies up to me as we walk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11492
msgid "* I lead her out and down the ruined streets that borders the chasm, imagining a picturesque esplanade overlooking a black sea. Imagining Beryl."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11493
msgid "* She's so fucking sweet. Part of me wonders if I've gotten her into a position where she's at risk. If the Otters hurt her, I'll never forgive myself."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11495
msgid "* He stubs his cigarette out on the wall when he see's us approach. * You two ready?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11496
msgid "* Before I can answer, Beryl squeezes my hand. * Heck yes! We're g-gonna be in and out, get what we need, then, like... I dunno. T-take the rest of the day off!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11497
msgid "Sal: Well you're damn chipper, ain't ya... Alright, it's a plan. Let's go."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11498
msgid "* He pats his coat down until a he finds a set of keys in his pocket. * I'm gonna pull the van around. Sit tight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11501
msgid "* I slide the door open for Beryl, then join her in the back. It's dark, and similar to his office, packed with cardboard and garbage. Whatever. There's still plenty of space to sit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11504
msgid "Um, ok. Shouldn't we try and get some more info before getting in harms way?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11507
msgid "Beryl: But that's not gonna happen. We've got you, HC. They definitely aren't gonna mess with you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11508
msgid "* Sal smiles. * No kidding. They've never seen tech like you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11509
msgid "* I realize I've been rocking back and forth, bouncing my knee, so I force myself to stop. * It's all on me. Gotcha. I'll try not to fuck this up..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11511
msgid "Beryl: I, for one, am on team 'let's-not-shoot-anyone,' b-but it is good to know that we have.. options... I suppose... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11512
msgid "I won't let it get that far."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11513
msgid "I'm scared..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11514
msgid "* Beryl holds me, gives me a gentle kiss on the cheek. * Thanks, HC..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11515
msgid "* Beryl holds me, gives me a gentle kiss on the cheek. * I've got you. Nothing bad is gonna happen. Promise."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11523
msgid "* Beryl squeezes my hand, whispers in my ear. * I think this is you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11524
msgid "* I swallow, but step forward, trying to focus on the fact that a foot behind me is all the warmth and comfort I could ever need."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11525
msgid "Should I, Um... * I gesture at the guy and look to Sal."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11526
msgid "Sal: Nah, I wouldn't say you have to start cracking skulls just yet. Not if this guy is gonna let us pass."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11527
msgid "Bouncer: You kiddin' me? Gonna sick this cushy sex bot on me? * He takes a swing at me, not a hard one, just enough to get me out of his face."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11528
msgid "* I calculate the trajectory of his fist, make subtle adaptations to my stance to compensate. Keep my eyes locked to his. Try and cover my fear with what I hope is a steely expression."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11529
msgid "* The fist crumples and I don't budge. I don't even blink. The bouncer stares back with a new respect, a new hint of fear. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11530
msgid "* Sal smirks. * As you were saying?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11531
msgid "* The bouncer tries to play it off like it's no big deal, like he's making the choice on his own. * Ok, you know what? I'm gonna let you in. But, uh... Be quick about it!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11532
msgid "Sal: Will do, pal. * We all file past the hulking, broken man. * Will do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11536
msgid "* His hammer-like forehead is polished to chrome, except for one dark imperfection off to the side. A bullet impact, by its look. A scar he mustn't want to hide."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11545
msgid "Sal: Have you seen this woman? * We all hold our breath as the boss leans forward, gives it a glance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11551
msgid "* Every second of this tense, methodical action brings us closer to an all out brawl, or even worse, a gunfight. My eyes dart across each devastatingly stern face, and I start to spiral."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11552
msgid "* But then, among them, I find Beryl's kind eyes. No fear, just love and calm and faith in me. Just like that, I'm grounded."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11553
msgid "* I gently let go of the mans wrist, then put up my hand, show them all that the next move is theirs, that I'm here to protect, not to attack. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11554
msgid "* The goon to my rear pauses, then releases me. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11555
msgid "* I just stand there, frozen in fear. It's all going to shit so fucking quick. I have no idea why I thought my mind could be any fucking use here..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11556
msgid "* But then Beryl's whispers reach me from behind. * You can do this, HC. You're the strongest one here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11557
msgid "* I try and shake off the anxiety, but standing on the edge of a spiral, I can only do so much. I step forward, reach out..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11558
msgid "* And grab the goon arm with both trembling hands, force it back down till Sal is back on his feet. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11559
msgid "* Another goon steps in, tries to pull me away, but I stand firm. * F-fuck off! * I let go of the first guy and shrug this new one off my back. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11560
msgid "* And then I just freeze, knowing that even a slight move could set an all out brawl in motion. Gradually, each goon seems to calm."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11562
msgid "Boss Barnes: I will give you a chance to walk outta here right now before letting my guys do their jobs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11569
msgid "* Sal shifts his weight uncomfortably. * I dunno... Getting in between Gelcorp and the Rust Pups? Not sure we're qualified for that kinda--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11573
msgid "Beryl: Dang... That could have been a better resolution... Gelpcorp and the Rust Pups both shoot to kill."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11574
msgid "* She tries to smile. * You did really good though, HC! That was... Amazing..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11576
msgid "* Beryl looks up. * I take it from your laugh that you have a plan?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11577
msgid "Sal: Not yet. But don't worry about the job. There's always another angle. I'll see what I can dig up. * He takes a long drag on the cigar"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11578
msgid "Sal: You two did great work in there, by the way. Ya make a good team."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11580
msgid "* Beryl beams, her concern with Barnes' offer subsiding. * Thank you! I'm just glad to be of help."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11582
msgid "* When we arrive on Root Street, the situation seems to have sunk in. Beryl stays quiet, even when I give her a hug.."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11588
msgid "* Beryl and I start our walk back home. It's quiet for a bit. * You ok?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11589
msgid "Beryl: Yeah, I... I think so..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11590
msgid "You sure? I mean, the stakes seem to be getting higher and higher..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11591
msgid "* She looks down. * Yeah... I just... I don't want to commit arson."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11592
msgid "* I giggle. * If anything needs burning, I'll do it! As long as you give me tons of hugs when I'm done..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11593
msgid "* Beryl cracks a smile, too. * Of course! Hugs, I can do. I'm all about the hugs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11595
msgid "Beryl: Unstoppable..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11599
msgid "* I'm on my way up Root Street, passing the opening of the ally, when my heart starts to sink. Sal's van is pulled in, rear door swung wide, a hydrogen fuel cell and pair of kerosene cans stacked haphazardly within. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11600
msgid "* He rounds the corner with another bright blue receptacle in his hand. It sloshes ominously as he adds it to the pile. * HC..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11601
msgid "Whoa. This is happening? No discussion, no group meeting... We're just gonna go burn that place down?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11602
msgid "* He grumbles, doesn't keep eye-contact. * Hey, I don't like it any better than you do, kid, but the clock's ticking. I've got a guy to find, and I'd prefer not to be working for a widow."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11603
msgid "* I just sort of stand there in disbelief. * What happened to 'We'll think of something?' Huh? You really made it seem like you had a plan."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11604
msgid "* He slams the back door and circles around to the driver side. * I do have a plan. Get this done as soon as possible and get the info we need. Follow that up with avoiding the Otters for a while."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11605
msgid "* I open the passenger door and get in. * Really? Look, the Otters aren't the only ones we need to worry about. If we do this, the Rust Pups, Gelcorp... We're gonna be in big-time danger!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11606
msgid "* As he starts the car, I begin to wonder how wise it was for me to try and continue this conversation on the drive to the Gelcorp guard outpost."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11607
msgid "* Fortunately, the ride is cut short almost immediately. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11608
msgid "* Olivia hurtles out of the stair box just as the van rounds the corner out of the alleyway. She slides to a halt, puts her hands up, and shouts something that we can't hear over the chugging engine."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11609
msgid "* Sal sighs and rolls down the window, but Olivia just walks past, slides open the side door, and gets in behind us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11610
msgid "Olivia: I heard about your plan. Drive."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11611
msgid "* Sal lays on the gas. * Big fan of starting fires, huh?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11612
msgid "* Olivia scowls. * Not remotely. I heard that you were about to do something stupid, so I thought I'd offer an alternative."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11613
msgid "* She taps out a command on her wrist computer, then thrusts it into the cockpit between Sal and I. * Check this out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11614
msgid "Sal: Now hold the phone, kid. You asking me to take my eyes off the road? * He cracks a dry smile."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11615
msgid "Olivia ignores him and turns to me. I stare at the computer, trying to make sense of the data-sheet that's scrolling by."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11616
msgid "Help me out here... What am I looking at?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11617
msgid "Olivia: Receipts. Microtransactions from an MMO called Neverstar Sakura Sword Online. I believe it's the boss. And I believe he's spending a considerable amount of the Otters resources on cosmetic items."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11618
msgid "* I laugh. * You think the Boss of the Otters just dropped... * Glance at the list. * Sixty thousand coupons on a... 'Angel-kissed heartshower teleport effect?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11619
msgid "* Olivia's face remains steely. * I didn't believe it either, but I had Cadence do some poking around. She made an account, found the character in question, even followed him around a bit in-game."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11620
msgid "* Sal smirks. * Damn, kid. You're a natural. Ever thought of becoming a PI?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11621
msgid "Olivia: I cross-referenced his online time with the Bosses comings and goings to the Otters nest. I even found the location of the computer he's using, within a few hundred foot radius."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11622
msgid "* Again, Olivia doesn't acknowledge Sal, but pride starts to hint its way into the corners of her lips. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11623
msgid "* She withdraws her arm, leans back. *  The bosses penthouse is in-range."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11624
msgid "Olivia: We can get him. There's no way he'd let this info get out. I mean... * She flicks at the screen, scrolling the list. * There's in-game pets on here. There's pets for the pets."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11625
msgid "* She leans forward, lowers her voice to whisper of icy finality. * There's pets for the pet's pets."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11626
msgid "* I giggle. * Ok, so, what? We show them the receipts?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11627
msgid "Olivia: Nah, those meatheads will probably have the same reaction you did. We need something easy to understand. Something simple. I'm thinking pictures."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11628
msgid "Olivia: We catch boss Barnes yelling into a headset, Berryglug in hand... His guys will never look at him the same. We'll throw in the receipts as well, of course."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11629
msgid "Sal: Lemme get this straight. You wanna photograph Boss Barnes while he's in his penthouse? One of the most dangerous, well guarded places in Pira City?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11630
msgid "Olivia: Yes, this is a dangerous option, but helping secure territory for the Otters just... Doesn't sit right with me. If that outpost can be used by the Rust Pups, I think that's worth the risk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11631
msgid "* Sal sighs. * Aight, whatever you say. I still think fire is the safest bet, but neither plan is getting off the ground without HC. Let's hear what she thinks."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11632
msgid "* I guess it's up to me to break the tie. I try and shake off the doubt, weigh the danger awaiting us down each path. Pungent, oily fumes load each of my shuddering inhalations. * Alright. Let's do..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11633
msgid "Let's do arson."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11634
msgid "Let's do blackmail."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11635
msgid "* Olivia sits back, frustrated, but after a moment, she nods her understanding. * Fuck, ok. Arson it is. How are we doing this?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11636
msgid "Sal: It aint complicated. We stake it out, wait for the Rust Pups to make their move, then get close while the corpos are distracted. Ditch the gas. Sow the seeds of combustion, if you will."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11637
msgid "* I nod along with him. * Then we just light it up, get out. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11638
msgid "* The drive gets increasingly bumpy as we leave the desolate streets of the industrial ruins and enter the rubble-strewn flats that surround Gelcorp. We skirt east along the perimeter until we're north of Skipnoise."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11639
msgid "* Finally, the security depot comes into view."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11640
msgid "* It's a small building, two stories of glossy Gelcorp White. Too young to be stained dark by the dust winds. Parked adjacent to it is an excavator and a small dumptruck."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11641
msgid "* The windows twinkle, but it's hard to make out much from our present distance of around 2000 feet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11642
msgid "* Sal parks in the shadow of a building and pulls a pair of folding binoculars out of the glove box, spilling crumpled papers and old napkins in the process."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11643
msgid "* There's an almost imperceptible battery squeal as he surveys the flattened landscape in night-vision."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11644
msgid "Sal: Construction crew's gone home for the night. That's good. Look here, see that line? * He points to a slim shadow leading across the ground from the depot towards the Gelcorp compound."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11645
msgid "* It's a ditch they dug for the outposts power cable. I think it's our best bet for an approach. The van'll stay here and we'll sneak the accelerant in on foot."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11646
msgid "* Olivia doesn't look too happy. * It's a long way to that ditch. Lotta open space."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11647
msgid "Sal: Yeah, we'll be exposed, but you two look light on your feet. And if we time it with the Rust Pup attack, you should make it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11648
msgid "Hold up... Us two? What about you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11649
msgid "* Sal's scratchy, humorless laugh almost sounds like a cough. * This is about speed. Don't think I'd cut it as a sprinter, not with my bum ticker. I'll do what I can from here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11650
msgid "What could you possibly do from here? I'm pretty sure tha--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11651
msgid "* Sal refocuses his binoculars on the cityline to the left, cuts me off. * Time to go. Rust pups are here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11652
msgid "* His statement is punctuated by the echoing gunshot of a high-powered rifle. Spotlights on the outpost ignite and begin searching the darkness across the way. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11653
msgid "* Olivia and I fly out of the van and around the back. I take the hefty fuel cell in one hand and the largest of the three kerosene tanks in the other. She takes the rest."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11654
msgid "* To the slow rhythm of gunfire, we run for all we're worth across the emptiness. It's twilight, and the shadowy moon-like expanse is riddled with various tripping hazards."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11655
msgid "* As the spotlights find their targets, the slow fire from the Rustpups is accompanied by the ratcheting of Gelcorp SMGs. Yells, distant ricochets. My heart starts hammering out its demand of fight or flight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11656
msgid "* But a few seconds later, we slide through the dust and over the lip of the ditch, down a half-dozen feet and into the mud."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11657
msgid "* In the center of the ditch is what must be the power cable, shrouded in thick, segmented metal casing, easily as big around as my torso."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11658
msgid "* No time to rest. We stay hunched as we jog up the ditch toward the drop point. A quarter way there, then half. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11659
msgid "* I try to ignore the hornets nest and focus on the fact that once the fire is started, the shooters are going to have more important things to focus on than Olivia and I."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11660
msgid "* Suddenly, a shout from above. * They're at our six!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11661
msgid "* A spotlight swings round and blinds us, rims us in an angelic halo, marks us for death. I grab Olivia and dive us under the heavy cable just as the gunfire starts. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11662
msgid "* Little eruptions of stone and mud shred the ground around us, pelt us with stinging shrapnel. I hold Olivia close, deafened, disoriented, praying for safety."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11663
msgid "* A second later, another distinct series of cracks joins the fray. Based on its direction, Sal has started unloading with his six-shooter. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11664
msgid "* There's a brief pause in the impacts around us as the Gelcorp Guards duck behind their cover."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11665
msgid "* I feel a push from behind me. Olivia and I roll out, start sprinting, but only make it a few dozen feet before the spotlight focuses back on us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11666
msgid "* Again, we dive under the cable, trying to shield both our bodies and the cans with the narrow metal trunk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11667
msgid "* Panicking hard, I turn over onto my back, look up at the underside of the cable's armor. Rational option have failed. I ignore Olivia's screamed objections, and begin to punch the cable."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11668
msgid "* I drive my fists into the casing over and over, leaving deep dents in the recently painted metal. I feel Olivia grip at my ankles, but I kick her off and continue... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11669
msgid "* Over and Over. Harder and Harder. Until the spotlights begin to flicker."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11670
msgid "* One final punch and the searing white is extinguished. I grab her by the wrist, pull her out, and we run the last stretch, screams of confusion issuing from the scrambling guards above us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11671
msgid "* When we get to the base of the wall, we toss the payload through the opening the cable leads to, and run."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11672
msgid "* Olivia uses her wrist computer to remotely detonate the fuel cell, and with that, the plane is reilluminated in vibrant orange."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11673
msgid "* The inferno doesn't spread quickly, but quickly enough to demand the guards to act. We leave the ditch in favor of a bee-line sprint."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11674
msgid "* Sal peels out of the darkness and meets us in the middle, gambling hard on the safety provided by the fire."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11675
msgid "* We hop in and he obliterates the accelerator, sending a cloud of dust to join the smoke in the darkening evening sky. Olivia pants in the front seat, and I take her previous post in the back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11676
msgid "* Olivia and I are drenched in mud and sweat, shaking, rattled to our cores. I have no idea how much time passes till one of us speaks."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11677
msgid "Sal: You made it..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11678
msgid "Olivia: That was your plan? You thought this was the safer option?? Jesus fucking Christ!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11679
msgid "* No response. It's cold in the cabin. I hadn't noticed the fresh bullet holes in the windshield and the passenger seat or the gun rattling on the dash. The upholstery fibers hanging in the air, still trying to settle."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11680
msgid "* I try to clear my head, but all I can focus on is the handgun. * Thanks for having our backs, Sal."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11681
msgid "* Olivia is growling. * Having our backs? It was his plan, or rather, his extreme lack of a fucking plan, that almost got us killed! * She slams a fist into the dash, sending the gun tumbling under the seat."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11682
msgid "Olivia: Tell me, did you know how wide a no-mans-land we were gonna have to cross? Did you get the measurement in feet? Did you count the guards? Were you fucking prepared for this at all?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11683
msgid "* She cuts back in before Sal has a chance to reply. * Fuck this shit! Next time, I take the fucking lead, understood? * Her voice is shaking, like the rage is all that's holding back her tears."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11684
msgid "* Sal nods, expression unreadable. * Right. Blackmail it is. How we doing this, Olivia?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11685
msgid "* Olivia leans in. * We don't know the layout of the penthouse, where the windows are, where the computer Barnes is using is. Hell, we aren't even sure how many guards there are."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11686
msgid "* Sal scoffs. * This ain't exactly sounding like a pep talk. Why don't you tell us what we DO have..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11687
msgid "* She smiles. * We have Cadence. And according to her, there's been an in game event going on for the past 46 hours. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11688
msgid "Olivia: Barnes has been grinding hard, and if he doesn't get the loot he's after in the next couple hours, he never will."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11689
msgid "Sal: So, what does that do for us? * The question is asked flat, like he's skeptical a satisfactory answer exists."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11690
msgid "Olivia: It means we can force him out. Cut the internet to his place. The closest wifi signal is a cafe a couple doors down. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11691
msgid "Olivia: It's open, unprotected, mostly windows. Not somewhere the Head of the Otters would risk getting caught..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11692
msgid "Olivia: If he were in his right mind. But Cadence and I believe that this exclusive loot is priceless to the guy. He's not an idiot. Got a real sense for mob business. But we think the FOMO is stronger."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11693
msgid "* We head to the north of Skipnoise Ave, where the vibrant, neon-lit district starts to blend into the less populated industrial ruins. In the shadow of toppled building, we park, and look down the street."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11694
msgid "* The cafe is close, all glass and warm halogen lights. Like a smaller, classier acorn. Beyond it is the dark, hulking form of the penthouse. Five stories with the boss on top."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11695
msgid "* Olivia points to the gap between the penthouse and the adjacent building.."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11696
msgid "Olivia: Down that ally, there's a power conduit with a few lines inside. The internet will be the blue line, smaller than the others. Cutting the wrong one would put everyone on high alert."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11697
msgid "* Sal kills the engine, rests his hand on the doorhandle. * Gotcha. Cut the wire, then wait for the boss outside the Cafe. Give him the old 'photography-from-outside-the-window' trick."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11698
msgid "Olivia: Not quite. His guys will move to guard the cafe. The only shot we have is if we're already inside when he comes in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11699
msgid "Olivia: They've met you both, but they don't know my face, so I'll be the one to do it. I'll order something and wait for Barnes to show up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11700
msgid "Olivia: You two just need to make the cut, then circle round behind the cafe and meet me back here at the car."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11701
msgid "Sal: It's a good plan, but I think it'll have to be just HC who does the cutting."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11702
msgid "Sal: If we need to be quick, I won't be much help. Not much of a sprinter, not with this bum ticker. * He shifts in the seat, jostling the tubes hanging around his torso."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11703
msgid "* Olivia pulls a pair of pliers out of some unseen pocket on her dress. * Shouldn't be a problem. She can handle this on her own. isn't that right, HC?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11704
msgid "* I take the pliers."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11705
msgid "Hell yeah!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11706
msgid "I hope so...."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11707
msgid "Olivia: Excellent. Move out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11708
msgid "* She cracks a smile as she opens the van door. * I'll go have a latte."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11709
msgid "* Olivia glares from behind her mask. * You're the best choice for this. We need you. Just... * She takes a deep breath. * Just don't forget that Sal and I have your back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11710
msgid "Olivia: Now if you don't mind, * She opens the van door. * I'm gonna go have a latte."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11711
msgid "* Pliers tucked away, I begin what I hope is a casual-looking stroll down the street, trying not to look like I'm heading for the penthouse specifically."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11712
msgid "* Trying to think of a reason to be hanging out in an alley for if I'm caught."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11713
msgid "* Several stories up, hulking forms menace me from various balconies. Their puffed up shoulder armor and bulbous helmets upset what should be human silhouettes, but the guns slung across their chests are clear as day."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11714
msgid "* Projecting all the false-confidence I can muster, I pass into the narrow, shadowy alley adjacent to the building, out of sight of the guards."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11715
msgid "* The conduit Olivia described isn't difficult to locate, and with my droid strength, I have no problem popping off its cover."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11716
msgid "* A filth-crusted bundle of high voltage cables weaves into the darkness. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11717
msgid "* I poke around with the insulated pliers, searching for the small, blue internet line. I find it, snip it, and a moment later, hear a bellowing scream from somewhere in the penthouse."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11718
msgid "* I head further down the alley till I find another intersecting it, take a right and follow the steamy vents along the rear of the cafe, then the side."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11719
msgid "* I take half a step out from behind the right wall of the cafe, then dive back into its cover. The boss is already through the penthouse door, laptop underarm, surrounded by guards."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11720
msgid "* I wait for him to pass, for the jingle of the cafe door, before leaving."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11721
msgid "* The Bosses baritone voice carries to my hiding place."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11722
msgid "Boss: I told you, I've got some real important Otter business to do! It can't wait! And if you question me again about it, -- * The threat is cut off as the door shuts behind him."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11723
msgid "* When I peek back out, the cafe door has reopened and the guards are escorting all the customers out into the street, despite the muffled protests of the barista. Fuck. I guess the plan didn't pan out..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11724
msgid "* Among the handful of frightened customers, there's a distinct lack of Olivia. Did they take her? Is she in danger?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11725
msgid "* I take a risk, peering further around and looking in through the window, hoping that the guards don't notice me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11726
msgid "* All looks relatively calm inside. Barnes is already set up at a table, two more meaty Otters on his either side. No Olivia."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11727
msgid "* I retreat back to the shadows and stare across the way at Sal. The van is a shape in the shadow, only visible because I know what to look for."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11728
msgid "* No chance of seeing him behind the dark windshield. I can only hope he sees me. That I'm not alone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11729
msgid "* I try and mime a 'what's going on?' gesture, but end up just flailing my arms. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11730
msgid "* There's a glint from the darkness as the van door opens and Sal gets out, nothing more than a trenchcoated silhouette in the darkness."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11731
msgid "* He doesn't make a move, but just knowing I haven't been somehow ditched is encouraging. I peer back through the glass and into the cafe. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11732
msgid "* More of the same, until a bathroom door on the back wall cracks for a moment, then swings open."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11733
msgid "* The guards turn, raise their guns, but Olivia plays dumb. I can't hear what they're saying, but Olivia is just acting confused."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11734
msgid "* I can tell she's trying to use the act to buy time and get a pic of the laptop screen, but from where she's standing, there's nothing in view."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11735
msgid "*  The guards are closing in, pointing at door. Opposite direction of where she needs to be."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11736
msgid "* Her hands are up, walking backwards, trying to keep everyone calm. She points to a table behind the Boss. The guards are shaking their heads, yelling at her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11737
msgid "* I'm paralyzed, trapped behind the glass, unable to help her without putting her in even more risk. This many guns, things could go south so fucking quick."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11738
msgid "* But she just picks up a cup of coffee, then lets them escort her out. They bought the bluff. It worked."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11739
msgid "* She leaves the coffee store and walks quickly, stiffly towards the van. I jog out from behind cover and join her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11740
msgid "* No one's in earshot of us, but I can't help but whisper. * You did it! Holy shit, you fucking did it!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11741
msgid "* She's shaking bad, though. * Yeah... I did. * She releases her death grip on the mug, shatters it on the ground. Mutters. * This isn't even MY fucking coffee..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11742
msgid "* We're only half way to the van when Sal darts out of the shadows, gun in hand. * Run!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11743
msgid "* Behind us, one of the Otters has noticed my distinct blue skin and is yelling his discovery to the Boss. Must have recognized me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11744
msgid "* We book it to the van, pile in, and Sal obliterates the accelerator. The Otters, even the Boss, are pouring out of the Cafe, guns drawn. By the time they get a shot off, though, we've broken their line of sight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11745
msgid "* Sal tosses his gun onto the passenger side dash in front of Olivia, grips the wheel with both hands."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11746
msgid "* Olivia ejects a little data drive from her wrist computer and drops it in the coin tray. It rattles like the cheap trinket it is, like a bounty unworth the risk to our lives."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11747
msgid "* We're all quiet for a while. The gravely drone of the engine is what we've been longing to hear, anyway. The sound of deliverance from danger."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11748
msgid "* After a bit, Olivia speaks up. * Don't tell Forcier about this..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11749
msgid "* I go to reassure her, but she interrupts. * Yeah, I know, it was my plan that just- That just nearly got us killed. I'm sorry. But please, don't tell them. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11750
msgid "* Shaking, she buries her face in her hands, grips at the edges of her visor. * They don't need to be worrying about me..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11751
msgid "That's between you and them... * I try and think of something uplifting to say, but I'm freaked out, too. * Olivia... It's ok."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11752
msgid "* Olivia turns and yells in my face. * It's ok? Are you fucking serious? We just got shot at by the Otters!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11753
msgid "Olivia: We never should have been dealing with them in the first place! And I bet this guy would count this as a job well done, huh? * She gestures at Sal."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11754
msgid "* She cuts back in before Sal has a chance to reply. * Fuck this shit! * Her voice is quivering, like the rage is all that's holding back her tears. * Next time, We're gonna... We should..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11755
msgid "* She balls up her fists, then slams one into the dash, sending the six-shooter tumbling to the floor. There's a single, heart-breaking sob."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11756
msgid "* Sal silently rolls to a halt, eyes fixed on the rear view mirror. We're still a ways away from Root Street. It's just faceless, empty buildings and rubble."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11757
msgid "Sal: Get out. * There's a dark authority to his voice. A spiteful, hard-boiled command that scares me a little. My heart is in my throat."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11758
msgid "Olivia: Where the fuck even are--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11759
msgid "* Sal reaches under the passenger seat, pulls out the fallen six-shooter. * I said get out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11760
msgid "* Olivia just stares at him, lip quivering in anger and hate. Then she speaks a quiet word. * Fine..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11761
msgid "* She slams the door and disappears into the darkness. Sal cranks the wheel, puts it in reverse, and turns us back around."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11762
msgid "Sal, what are you--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11763
msgid "* A second after we start moving, I see it. Headlights between the buildings. We were being followed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11764
msgid "* Sal eases forward. Drives non-threateningly, but fast enough to put some distance between where we meet the opposing car and where we kicked out Olivia."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11765
msgid "* When we're around thirty feet apart, each vehicle rolls to a halt."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11766
msgid "* A hulking figure emerges from the driver door, circles around, and opens the back. There's a glint of gold chrome in the headlights as Boss Barnes steps out. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11767
msgid "* Sal tucks the gun into his trench coat and rests his hand on the door latch. * Listen, kid... If this goes south... * He turns to me. * I want you to run."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11768
msgid "But--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11769
msgid "Sal: Just do it, alright?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11770
msgid "* We each step out into the cold night, stare down the Boss and his burly associate. Everything is silent except the flapping of Sal's coat in the breeze."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11771
msgid "* The boss takes a step forward. * We were watching. You did good work."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11772
msgid "Barnes: The depot's a crater. Gelcorp and the Pups are scattered. You really know the meaning of scorched earth."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11773
msgid "Sal: Yeah... * He looks up as if to check for ashy snowfall from our attack. * So, about our agreement..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11774
msgid "* The boss hacks out a sinister chuckle. * Yeah, my guy's'll get you the info you wanted by tomorrow morning."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11775
msgid "* Sal grimaces. * Not good enough. I need it tonight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11776
msgid "* Barnes keeps grinning his ugly, rumpled grin and claps a hand on Sal's shoulder. * Chill out, guy. You're a friend of the Otters, now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11777
msgid "* He slides his hand across Sal's back and over his other shoulder, turn's him around. * Get yourself home. Get some rest. You need it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11778
msgid "Barnes: Everything's gonna be taken care of."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11779
msgid "* Barnes walks Sal a few feet towards his car, then withdraws his massive arm."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11780
msgid "Barnes: Have a safe drive."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11781
msgid "* The boss and his shredded minion turn back to their own car, disappear behind the halo of the high-beams."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11782
msgid "* We just sit there, too tense to move, till their engine's rumble fades out into the distance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11783
msgid "* The boss takes a step forward. * The depot is in Rust Pup hands. Anything you want to explain before I let my boy pull out your spines?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11784
msgid "* No fear shows in Sal's voice, despite the bloodthirsty meatheads cracking their knuckles across from us. * New information has, uh, come to light."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11785
msgid "* He takes the data drive from his pocket and tosses it to Barnes. * Something you're gonna wanna see."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11786
msgid "* Barnes grunts as he slots the drive into a small port on the side of his head plate. After a second, a ghostly green glow flares in the depths of his pupils."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11787
msgid "Barnes: So you're an amateur photographer. Why the hell should I care?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11788
msgid "Sal: Yeah, keep scrolling."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11789
msgid "* The green light flickers slightly as Boss Barnes internally operates whatever software he's full of."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11790
msgid "* After a moment of silence and a deepening of the grimace on his perpetual bitchface, he mutters. * Back in the car. I'll handle this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11791
msgid "* The guy next to him nods and walks back into the high beams. Only after we hear the car door slam, does Barnes speak again."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11792
msgid "Barnes: Sure this is how you wanna play this, guy? I can make your life real difficult. Real short, too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11793
msgid "* Sal doesn't budge. * Yeah, there's a lotta difficult to go around. You know the score, Barnes. We've already got this info backed up, ready to distribute."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11794
msgid "Sal: Give us what we need and we don't tell your boys how full of holes you shot your organization. They don't have to know what you did with their hard-earned coupons."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11795
msgid "Barnes: The Otters are mine. You think they're gonna walk away from the only life they've ever known over something like this? They're loyal."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11796
msgid "* Sal runs a hand through his greasy hair. * Yeah, maybe... Or, maybe you're getting old. Maybe a change in leadership is just what the Otters need."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11797
msgid "Barnes:...I'll get you the information by the end of the week."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11798
msgid "Sal: Not good enough. I'm gonna need it by tomorrow morning. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11799
msgid "* The boss takes a step forward, gets up in Sal's face. More tense silence."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11800
msgid "* Barnes's voice is a deep growl. * If I ever catch you near the Otters Nest. Ever. It'll be over for you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11801
msgid "* Another snort of cold night air flows over Sal's face, but he stares down the bull. Barnes turns and walks back to the car."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11802
msgid "* Sal and I just stand there, afraid to move until the car is out of sight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11803
msgid "* I let out a breath I didn't realize I was holding. Sal lights up a cigar, coughs into the night."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11804
msgid "Sal: Let's get home."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11805
msgid "* The car ride is tense and silent. I scan the darkness for Olivia, but there's no sign of her. Even if I could make her out in the night fog, she's had plenty of time to walk home by now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11806
msgid "* Only when we emerge from the faceless ruins into the familiar golden neon of the Root Street stores and homes does my anxiety start to ebb."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11807
msgid "* Sal lets me out in front of the Acorn. * Hey, uh... Watch your back, kid. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11808
msgid "You too. I'll see you soon."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11809
msgid "* He nods and pulls into the alley. Time for me to walk home."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11810
msgid "* When I arrive at Olivia and Forcier's apartment, the gang is already there, gathered around a coffee table, pouring over a small stack of rumpled, mismatched papers. Notably absent is Sal."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11811
msgid "* The door clicks shut behind me, almost drowned by the murmurs of the group. Energy is high, tense. Olivia slams the last of a cup off coffee mid-sentence, then gets back to her lightspeed theorizing with Forcier."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11812
msgid "* Cadence is the first to tear away from the herd and rush me. I'm in her embrace before I have a chance to say hello."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11813
msgid "Cadence: HC! * She smiles up at me, obviously overjoyed that I'm here. Or maybe that I'm still in one piece after my brush with the Otters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11814
msgid "* I kiss her forehead and hug her back. * Hi, Cadence! * I nod toward the group. * Looks like something is going on."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11815
msgid "Cadence: Yeah! Big something! * She takes my hand and leads me to the coffee table."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11816
msgid "* We push between Beryl and Magdalena and crouch next to Decima, who is sitting cross-legged with a dangerously large pipe-wrench resting in her lap."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11817
msgid "* Olivia smiles at me. * Good, you're here. Take a look at this. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11818
msgid "* The papers strewn over the table top are greasy and crumpled, some handwritten, some printed, with a fair few photographs tucked in. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11819
msgid "* It seems to be a collection of information on Dr. Greene, the Gelcorp Employee that Sal was trying to track down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11820
msgid "Olivia: It was tucked into a folder and slid under my door. This was on the cover. * She is a hand onto which a yellow sticky note has been stuck. In Sal's rough handwriting is the word 'SLIME!!!'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11821
msgid "Slime? What's that got to do with the missing dude and his wife? * I fan out some of the papers, getting a feel for the content. Most of it is stolen Gelcorp memos or Otter notes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11822
msgid "* Forcier cuts in. * We aren't sure, but we have some theories. Some additional elaboration on Sal's part would have been helpful..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11823
msgid "You haven't seen him?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11824
msgid "Olivia: No. His place is empty, van's gone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11825
msgid "* I stare at the notes, but my attention is turned inward, toward a thousand grim possibilities. * I hope he's ok..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11826
msgid "Speaking of which... How are you, Olivia? After everything that went down, you must be..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11827
msgid "* Her expression turns icy. * I'm fine. Copacetic."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11828
msgid "* There's an awkward pause, then her voice get's quiet. * I mean... I should say I'm sorry. I..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11829
msgid "It's ok. It was an intense situation. We all freaked out a bit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11830
msgid "Olivia: But I've got experience with this kinda operation. I want to be reliable... I WILL be reliable..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11831
msgid "It's ok."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11833
msgid "* She nods. * I know. Still, though. * Another pause, a sigh, her head hung. Then she straightens up and clears her throat. Back to business."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11834
msgid "* I step around the table and tentatively open my arms, offering a hug. She falls into my arms and buries her face in my neck."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11835
msgid "* Her voice is muffled against me. * Thank you, HC. Yeah, it was a lot... The fire... Fucking flashbacks..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11836
msgid "* Her voice is muffled against me. * Thank you, HC. Yeah, it was a lot... The gunfire... Fucking flashbacks..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11837
msgid "* When she's had enough, she steps away and straightens back up. Wipes her nose, not that she got sniffly or anything. A back to business ritual, I guess."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11838
msgid "Olivia: So. Theories."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11839
msgid "* Before she can posit any, Decima cuts in. * It's all about the Slime! I'm thinking slime replicants. This dude and his wife? Probably secretly slime people!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11840
msgid "* Cadence pinches Decima's lips into a duck-beak. * Hush, ya dummy! This is serious!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11841
msgid "* Forcier ignores them. * Based on the memos collected here, there is an undeniable link between Gelcorp and the Slime."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11842
msgid "Forcier: If we accept the assumption that the 'insubordinate employee' referred to in this series of exchanges between the head of the Material Sciences and the CEO, Cameron Seith, is in fact Sal's missing person-- "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11843
msgid "* Decima interrupts. * Damn, the missing dude is on the CEO's radar? Must have been important."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11844
msgid "Forcier: Actually, the missing employee was a scientist in the Material Sciences wing who ranked relatively low in Gelcorps corporate hierarchy. The only thing that made him notable was his delinquency. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11845
msgid "Olivia: Even so, he must have really fucked up if he was getting direct scorn from the CEO. I did some digging on Cameron Seith, and as far CEO's go, he has a weird rep."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11846
msgid "Olivia: He's new to the company, rose quickly through the ranks, and-- And this is really fucking weird-- I couldn't find anything about him prior to his work at Gelcorp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11847
msgid "* She cracks her knuckles. * Not to be cocky, but with my skillset, not finding a single trace of a person in cyberspace is pretty much impossible. Especially a CEO."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11848
msgid "So this guy, Seith, went from living under a rock to being CEO of one of the few corps left in this hell-world? You're right, that IS weird."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11849
msgid "* There are nods of agreement around the table. Olivia paces. * Back to what Forcier was saying, if it's the missing guy that Seith was so pissed off about, it stands to reason that Gelcorp disappeared him."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11850
msgid "Forcier: Indeed. Despite the risk, seeking protection from the Otters may have been the wisest course of action available to the wife."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11851
msgid "Olivia: Yeah, we'll see about that. * She moves some papers out of the way to reveal a small handwritten note on the bottom of the pile. An address."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11852
msgid "Olivia: This is her address. It's an Otter safehouse west of Skipnoise Ave. We're gonna check it out, ask her some questions."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11853
msgid "* Decima stands up, slings the large pipe-wrench over her shoulder. * Let's fucking do this! I'm ready to bomp!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11854
msgid "* Forcier disconnects a charging cord from their hip. * Hopefully it will not be necessary to 'bomp.'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11855
msgid "* The air is brisk but the long walk keeps up warm. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11856
msgid "* Banded together, Decima bounding with her weapon, Olivia staring at her wrist compy, hands clasped between couples, we're a tight-knit nest of chaos. A force to be reckoned with."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11857
msgid "* Beryl keeps the vibe light by pointing out everything along the way that could be considered pretty... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11858
msgid "* ...The way the purple sun glints off a patch of weather-polished asphalt, a dead shrub, even the inky black of the sinkhole."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11859
msgid "* There are lights on Skipnoise, but the further west we travel down the shattered road, the harder it gets to find pretty things."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11860
msgid "* Most of the homes here are networks of ramshackle tunnels and tents erected among the ruins."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11861
msgid "* The old buildings provide a relatively skimpy amount of shelter, and not much at all in the way of infrastructure. A man waves to us as he draws water from an old cistern with bucket and chain."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11862
msgid "* Eventually we arrive at the address. It's a mostly in-tact tenement building. Even has some electricity, based on the color of the light in some of the windows. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11863
msgid "* We enter through the front double doors and head for the staircase. Plaster on the walls has flaked away to expose the buildings bones. Solid. My anxiety about the stairs giving way subsides."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11864
msgid "* Up a few floors and down a dark hall, we arrive at the door. Ajar. Not a good sign, although, given the state of things here, not necessarily a bad one. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11865
msgid "* Decima takes the lead, carefully swings the door wide with the tip of her wrench."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11866
msgid "* Forcier steps confidently past. * Hello?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11867
msgid "* No response. The interior is gloomy, lit only by a dull purple glow from an open window. Olivia follows Forcier and Decima, tries a light switch. Nothing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11868
msgid "* She flips a switch on in her vizor which turns on a small headlamp and coats the walls with a harsh light."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11869
msgid "* She crouches, rummages through the debris on the floor. We file in around her and start exploring."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11870
msgid "* The room we've entered is a square common space, featuring a dusty couch, collapsed coffee table, and ancient tube-tv."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11871
msgid "* Behind us, Olivia pokes her head up, rests her crouching pose into a comfortable squat. * Do you hear that?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11872
msgid "Decima: The humming? Sounds like a refrigerator. That must be the kitchen. * She gestures to a door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11873
msgid "* Forcier points at an empty doorway on the other side of the room. * Which would make that the bedroom."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11874
msgid "* Decima starts walking towards the bedroom door, then comes to a sudden stop, sticks her finger into a hole in the wall."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11875
msgid "* She pulls out her finger, now tipped with white drywall dust, wiggles it around. * Holy shit, is this a bullet hole? "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11876
msgid "* Olivia stands up, a bit of brass gleaming between her fingers. * Based on this casing, I'm going to say yes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11877
msgid "* I scan the ground. My night-vision isn't great, but it's better than a humans. Little bullet casings are speckled into the trash strewn about the floor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11878
msgid "Beryl: G-guys... I think we should g-get out of here... * Her voice is hushed and wavering. * I'm really scared..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11879
msgid "Olivia: Beryl, Mags, Cadence. Keep watch out in the hall. We'll be quick."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11880
msgid "* Mags nods and takes Beryl by the hand, leads her back out the way we came in. Cadence hesitates, then joins them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11881
msgid "* Forcier runs their hand over the bullet-pocked wall, then turns to Olivia. * The bullet casing. What does it tell you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11882
msgid "* Olivia brings the little metal shell up to her visor. * 9 mil. Judging by the amount of them we're seeing, I'd say an SMG. I'm guessing this was Gelcorp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11883
msgid "Decima: Well fuck. So much for this being a 'safe house.' And I'm sure they cleared out anything of value. * She resumes her poking about, heads for the bedroom doorway."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11884
msgid "Forcier: I wouldn't be so sure. * Peering at the ground, they shift a fallen wall panel with their foot. Olivia crouches over the exposed shells beneath."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11885
msgid "* She picks up a couple. Much larger, mostly plastic, and mismatched in color. * These look like hand-packed shotgun shells. Probably made in the basement of some Otter hideout."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11886
msgid "So Gelcorp and the Otters had a shootout in here?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11887
msgid "* Olivia tosses the shotgun shells back into the filth. * Either that or the Otters gave our woman some heat to pack."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11888
msgid "* Behind us, Decima comes barreling out of the dark bedroom doorway, coughing. * Holy fucking shit! Guys. Do NOT go in there."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11889
msgid "* My heart leaps into my throat as we all turn to her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11890
msgid "* A grimace is fixed across her face. * There is fully a dead guy in there. A fully dead guy. Full dead. Full in there. Full fucking gross as fuck. * She coughs a few more times."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11891
msgid "* Olivia's jaw tenses. * Who is it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11892
msgid "Decima: I dunno, some guy! It's dark and it spooked me! You were right. So was Beryl. Let's get the fuck out of here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11893
msgid "Olivia: We have to know who it is. If it's our woman... * Her voice gets quiet as if she's talking mainly to herself. * It's about information... I'm here to gather information."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11894
msgid "* Olivia takes a deep breath, then heads for the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11895
msgid "* Olivia has done so much for us. I don't want to look at a dead body, but maybe I should step in. For her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11896
msgid "Wait, I'll go in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11897
msgid "* Let her go in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11898
msgid "Hey, wait! I have night-vision! Maybe I should be the one to check this out..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11899
msgid "* Olivia looks relieved. * Ok, yeah. That makes sense. We'll be right out here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11900
msgid "* I take a moment to steel myself against the horrors to come, then enter the bedroom. There's a sharp blood-scent in the air that churns my stomach, but nothing that could be described as rot."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11901
msgid "* The body is slumped over against the base-board of the bed, legs splayed, chest drenched in blood. The logo has been obliterated, but this is clearly Gelcorp body armor, now peppered with pellet-holes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11902
msgid "* A few inches from the limp fingers of the right had lays the aforementioned SMG. Tucked under the opposite arm is a bundle of ragged paperwork. I hold my breath as I approach."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11903
msgid "* Carefully, I lift the arm and grab the papers. The slight shift causes the mans mirrored aviators to slip from his face, revealing his wide-lifeless eyes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11904
msgid "* I shudder and exit as quickly as possible."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11905
msgid "* As I emerge into the living room, Forcier puts a comforting hand on my shoulder. * Thanks, HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11906
msgid "* My voice is unsteady. * N-no problem... It was a Gelcorp Guard. He had this... * I offer the paperwork to Olivia."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11907
msgid "Olivia: Excellent. Was there... Was that the only body?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11908
msgid "Yeah. Maybe she escaped..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11909
msgid "* Olivia and Forcier both let out a sigh of relief, but Decima seems to be completely distracted."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11910
msgid "* Olivia disappears into the room. There's a moment of silence. I'm holding my breath, and I'm sure Forcier is, too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11911
msgid "* But she emerges shortly. Her face is a bit paler, but a bundle of ragged paperwork is tucked under her arm."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11912
msgid "Olivia: I got what I need."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11913
msgid "* Forcier puts a comforting hand on Olivia's shoulder. * Was it..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11914
msgid "Olivia: No, it wasn't here. It was a Gelcorp Guard. Not dead too long, though."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11915
msgid "* Forcier and I sigh our relief, but Decima seems to be completely distracted."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11916
msgid "* She's staring at the opposite door. * Guys, is it just me? Or is that humming getting louder?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11917
msgid "* Before any of us have a chance to object, she grabs the doorknob and pulls."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11918
msgid "* A familiar blue light bathes the four of us. Inside, a hovering Gelcorp surveillance drone rotates to face us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11919
msgid "* It's scanning emitter switches from blue to red. * Warning - search area compromised -- Requesting additional support"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11920
msgid "* Smash it!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11921
msgid "* I lunge forward and batter the drone, shattering its face-plate with my balled fist. Its hover engines sputter and fire erratically, sending it spiraling into a wall."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11922
msgid "* I turn to the rest of them. Decima is grinning, impressed at my physical display. The other two look concerned. Olivia nods toward the door and we all follow her out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11923
msgid "* I lunge forward, fists balled, ready to punch. But I'm too slow. It boosts easily upwards and out of my range."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11924
msgid "* The scanning emitter casts a blade of laser light over us. * Beginning - target identification - sequence"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11925
msgid "* A metallic hand grips my shoulder and turns my face away from the beam, pulls me toward the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11926
msgid "* When we're all out in the hallway, Decima lets go of me and Olivia slams the door shut, the surveillance drone trapped on the other side."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11927
msgid "* Olivia turns to the three hallway watchers. * We need to get out of here. Gelcorp is on its way."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11928
msgid "* We all run till even the cold night can't stop us from sweating. Out of the building and south, taking the long way around the sinkhole to keep as far away from Gelcorp as possible."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11929
msgid "* Root Street feels miles safer than Skipnoise. The warm neon puts our hearts at relative ease."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11930
msgid "* When we're back in Olivia's apartment, she slaps the paper down on the coffee table and we also collapse and catch our breath."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11931
msgid "* Her and I are the first to take a peek. Most of the paperwork seems to be love letters..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11932
msgid "* Printed emails, with a few handwritten notes mixed in. We ignore them, for the most part. The real treasure is at the bottom of the stack."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11933
msgid "* Under the Gelcorp logo at the top of the staple-bound booklet is a promotional image of a sexy, smiling girl. Made entirely out of purple slime."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11934
msgid "Olivia: What the fuck..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11935
msgid "* Everyone takes the hushed exclamation as a cue to gather around as we scan the document. After a moment of silent anticipation, Olivia starts reading out loud."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11936
msgid "Olivia: For over 600 years, the innovative scientists at Gelcorp have been advancing the field of sex technologies in pursuit of our goal of perfecting the sexual experience."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11937
msgid "Olivia: The age of dildos and other simple sex toys is over. A new age is about to begin. Introducing the GelFriend. A nanobot based sexual companion droid designed to realize any fantasy."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11938
msgid "Olivia: The gelatinous makeup of this new, world-changing droid allows it to adapt to even the most nuanced of its owners preference. When physical shape is no longer a constraint, the possibilities are endless."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11939
msgid "Decima: Hold up, hold up. Um. * She massages her temples. * All the slime monsters in Pira are just... Gelcorp robots? Nanobot swarms?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11940
msgid "Looks like it..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11941
msgid "* She cocks her head, eyes wide. * Then why don't they, ah, you know... * She pokes a finger at the picture of the cheery GelFriend. * Why don't they look like that? You know, all bipedal and shit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11942
msgid "Forcier: An interesting question."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11943
msgid "I've got a question, too. Didn't you two test the slime? How did you not detect that it was just a bunch of nanobots?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11944
msgid "Olivia: We only ran simple tests for reactivity. The nanobots must be extremely small and... I don't know. I don't know how we missed this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11945
msgid "* Beryl giggles. * At least we know why the slime monsters seem so interested in dick..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11946
msgid "* Cadence nods and high-fives Beryl. * Damn, I gotta get me on of those. When they work out the bugs..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11947
msgid "Decima: What, not a fan of the random tentacle form? I bet if I owned one of these things, it'd spend most of its time as a sexy writhing blob."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11948
msgid "* Cadence considers it. * Yeah. No, you're right. Formless monstrosities are hot as fuck."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11949
msgid "* Cadence, Beryl, and Decima laugh. Olivia, ever stoic, turns another page."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11950
msgid "Olivia: There's a lot here. I'm going to give this a deep read. We should meet back as soon as possible to discuss what this means for the investigation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11951
msgid "Magdalena: Good idea. I could use a shower after all that."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11952
msgid "* Decima shyly sniffs her pit. * Yeah, same. I'll catch y'all later."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11953
msgid "* We all depart. On the walk home, I can't help but scrutinize every crack in the ground, eager to witness a slime in this new light. None show themselves, though. Unsurprising."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11954
msgid "* When we reach Sunshine Girders, we say some more goodbyes. Beryl gives me a hug. Then I head home."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11955
msgid "* Todays meeting of what is likely the gayest DIY detective agency in Pira city is taking place in Forcier's garden behind East Root St. It's a ways to walk, but Forcier insisted."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11956 result.py:12051
msgid "* Even in daylight, the lifeless remains of the industrial district are as ominous as ever. Extinguished streetlights stoop over the road, giving me the sense that I'm somewhere in the city-corpse's ribcage."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11957 result.py:12052
msgid "* Identifying the rusting, filth-encrusted forms is like a game. That mound of metal with the gap-toothed gashes in either side? A car. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11958 result.py:12053
msgid "*  There are payphones, dumpsters, collapsed fire escapes, all destined to be reduced to dust."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11959
msgid "* Signs of life start manifesting near Root St."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11960
msgid "* Passing the firelit windows that mark its border, we cross one of many electricity deserts. Root St has power and running water, upkept by the residents. Some of the buildings are even topped with algea tanks."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11961
msgid "* Through the gap between an empty bail bond business and the old theater, sheltered on all sides by crumbled walls, is a pocket of rare, vibrant green."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11962
msgid "* Most of the group is lounging on the mossy slopes of a runnoff pit, murky water glittering pink under the midday haze. Cadence baked cookies for the occasion. Even Magdalena seems relaxed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11963
msgid "Beryl: HC! You m-made it! * She hops up from a blanket she's lounging on with Mags and Cadence and gives me a hug."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11964 result.py:12058
msgid "* Cadence follows suit. * Have a seat! Pull up a cookie!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11965
msgid "Thanks! * I snag one of the hot little disks. * So, what's up?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11966
msgid "Olivia: Take a look. * She nods her head towards a shaded nook where Forcier and Decima are crouching over a rectangular excavation into the ashy ground."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11967
msgid "* I approach. A trowel in the center marks a few partitions, each a foot deep and labeled in chalk. Elegant cursive, directly on the various surrounding concrete surfaces."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11968
msgid "* With a pair of tweezers, Forcier removes a tiny bone from one of the dirt piles, places it under a chalk label. Decima peruses a folder of familiar documents."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11969
msgid "* Forcier doesn't turn from their work. * Ever seen a mouse, anyone?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11970
msgid "* I can conjure the mental image. Implanted education. But no, I think to myself. I haven't."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11971
msgid "* The rest of the group sort of nods, trying to remember. Beryl giggles. * Not since I was a little k-kid. I had totally forgotten. They were kinda everywhere."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11972
msgid "* Cadence smiles. * Same! Remember when Frank was just a waiter, chasing them out of the kitchen for his boss? It's been so long since I had seen one."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11973
msgid "* Beryl kicks the dirt. * I guess there have been a lot of things that have died out. That sucks..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11974
msgid "* Forcier picks up the trowel, carefully combs it through one of the bottom layers of gray soil. * This is true. It was a slow extinction for most, but not for mice."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11975
msgid "Forcier: I remember watching them in my mother's garden in Crystallica when I was young. Even their tight walls couldn't keep them out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11976
msgid "Forcier: Now they're gone. And, if the depth and quantity of their remains is any indicator, they went suddenly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11977
msgid "* Decima grunts in annoyance and tosses a stack of tattered papers on a nearby slab of concrete, then continues leafing through what remains in the folders."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11978
msgid "* Unlike the corporate memos and blueprints towards which she's directing her attention, the discarded papers are small, folded, handwritten. Signed with love."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11979
msgid "* Forcier delicately frees a tiny skull from the packed dust. * Found anything, Decima?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11980
msgid "* Decima lifts another paper, doesn't turn to Forcier. * Don't ask me, I'm not the one digging. * She pauses, turns. * Oh. You mean in the documents."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11981
msgid "Decima: Yeah, so, Mrs. Greene was collecting Gelcorp info, for sure. Maybe her hubby was smuggling it to her? I dunno. But yeah this whole 'Libidinal Wave Harvester' thing seems weird as fuck."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11982
msgid "* She slides a paperclipped packet out of the folder, hands it to Forcier."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11983
msgid "* Olivia smirks. * I'd thought so, too. Weird bit of tech. I can't tell what it does, but it looks very expensive. Very powerful."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11984
msgid "* Cadence raises a hand. * I don't mean to interrupt, but I'm calling dibs on that little mouse skull."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11985
msgid "* Beryl chuckles and idly fidgets with the handwritten letters Decima discarded. Cadence picks through the bone piles for anything else that strikes her fancy."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11986
msgid "* Olivia adresses Decima. * Did you get to the GelFriend part yet?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11987
msgid "* While decima searches the rest of the folder for whatever a GelFriend is, I peer over Forcier's shoulder at the paperwork."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11988
msgid "* A schematic depicts a large ovoid machine, bristling with antenae. Most of it is nonsense to me, but words stand out. Broadcasting. Affected Radius. And of course, Harvester."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11989
msgid "Decima: Holy shit of a fuck. * She's stopped flipping through and is staring into her hands."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11990
msgid "* After a moment taking it in, she turns it toward us, shows it off. Inside the folder is a staple-bound booklet, emblazened with the Gelcorp logo and a smiling pink face. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11991
msgid "* Besides Olivia and Forcier, who had been keeping the papers since they were liberated from the Safehouse, we're all shocked. The face belongs to a womans figure made of pink slime."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11992
msgid "* Olivia walks around behind Decima. * The slime creatures are robots."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11993
msgid "* Decima slips the booklet out and starts flipping through while Olivia continues to explain. * Nanobot swarms. Gelatinous Sexbots."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11994
msgid "Olivia: The jelly itself is inert. The bots are suspended in a body safe gel that they control through electrical impulses."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11995 result.py:12074
msgid "Decima: Sounds gross."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11996 result.py:12075
msgid "Cadence: Excuse me? A gelatinous sexbot sounds dope as hell!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11997 result.py:12076
msgid "* Decima slaps the metal paneling of her prosthetic. * You know me. I'm a simple creature. I like my robots made of metal, plastic, and the occasional magic crystal. No slime for me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11998 result.py:12077
msgid "* She cocks her head. * Unless grease counts as slime. I couldn't live without that sweet, sweet robo-grease. You know what? I'm changing my stance on slime."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:11999
msgid "* Forcier frowns. * When we tested the jelly, we either hadn't been lucky enough to take a sample that included any nanobots, or we didn't test broadly enough to detect them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12000
msgid "Olivia: Still kicking myself for that one. But yeah. Luxury slimes for the rich and horny."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12001
msgid "Foricer: We have thoroughly examined the Gelcorp documents, Olivia and I, and have formed a theory."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12002
msgid "* Forcier stands, pneumatic legs hissing as they reach their full, commanding height, and the group becomes hushed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12003
msgid "Forcier: The mice died out when the Libidinal Wave Harvester was activated years ago. The idle lust of our minds is being harnessed and infused into these GelFriends."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12004
msgid "Forcier: The hornomaly isn't a result of some sinister force. It's simply that a sinister force draining us since before our puberties has finally been deactivated."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12005
msgid "* Decima's voice is quiet, directed to herself. * And the mice died out when they stopped having urges to breed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12006
msgid "* Beryl smiles, sad but hopeful. * Aww. Th-that means they died of old age... Ostensibly healthy, even..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12007
msgid "* Cadence furrows her brow. * Wait so you expect me to believe that this is a normal amount of horniness? That we're all supposed to be functional bitches while constantly having urges to suck?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12008
msgid "* The sexual appetites of my Crystallica owners hadn't occured to me. That what they wanted from me could be considered normal."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12009
msgid "Magdalena: I don't buy it. Sure, it was our puberty, but why didn't Sal or Frank or whoever tell us about that one time, years ago, when the sex drive of every creature in the city died."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12010
msgid "Forcier: I don't know. This is only a theory. It fits with some of the limited information we have. Not all."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12011
msgid "Decima: Maybe they ramped it up to full power? Shut it off slowly? Or... * She seems unable to tear her eyes from the documents."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12012
msgid "* There's silence as the situation sinks in. Broken when Beryl sits up, grabs the notes she'd been fiddling with."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12013
msgid "Beryl: Did anyone read these? * She starts flipping through the small stack."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12014
msgid "Forcier: Yes. They appear to be love notes from Dr. Greene to his wife, sent from the Gelcorp housing compound. A keepsake."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12015
msgid "Beryl: Yeah, but... * She flips to the last one, scans it. * Did you see when they stopped coming?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12016
msgid "* She thrusts the worn letter towards Forcier, who takes it and reads it silently. * Just before the start of the hornomaly..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12017
msgid "* Olivia whispers. * Damn, Dr. Greene. I underestimated you..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12018
msgid "Forcier: Yes. * I can feel their mind turning over the facts. Greene. A saboteur, hunted by the corp. The corp and their plot to monetize our literal minds."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12019
msgid " * Poor Mrs. Greene. Dealing with the devil for scraps of info. There's real love in Pira City. Down in the cracks."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12020
msgid "So, what do we do?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12021
msgid "* Forcier straightens up. * We attempt to turn theory into fact. Decima, would you consider doing research into this machine?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12022
msgid "* Decima stuffs the schematic into one of the pockets on her vest and grins. * Oh, I was already planning on it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12023 result.py:12136
msgid "* Cadence whispers to her. * If I find out you went home and jerked off to that schematic..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12024 result.py:12137
msgid "* Forcier clears their throat. * Any other questions?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12025
msgid "Cadence: Hell yeah! This is so much progress! This is legitimately so fucking cool! We're totally gonna save the city from psychic vampirism!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12026
msgid "* Beryl leans forward onto her palms. * This means there are still mice in other cities! We could reintroduce the mouse!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12027
msgid "* From her backpack, Cadence produces a two liter of Berryglug and starts passing it around."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12028 result.py:12141
msgid "* Decima lays down in Cadence's lap. * So, are we gonna finish what Greene started? Blow that bitch up?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12029
msgid "* Olivia swigs from the Glug bottle. * Chill, Decima. We can discuss corporate sabotage later. Lets just enjoy the win right now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12030 result.py:12143
msgid "Decima: Ok, but I want you to know that I'm blissfully daydreaming of bombs... * She shuts her eyes and honestly does look pleased as hell."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12031
msgid "* The garden, tucked into the fertile shade, is surprisingly cozy. A patch of soft green among all that harsh concrete."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12032
msgid "* It's not the most comfy, but it's still highly snuggleable. The overhand shelters us from the wind, but it's still open air."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12033
msgid "* The little chill draws us together into a nice cozy cuddle puddle. We keep each other warm and finish off the rest of the cookies by the light of dusk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12034 result.py:12148
msgid "* There is warmth in more ways than one. There's kissing, hand holding, neck nuzzles. It feels safe in all these arms, in my little nest of friends."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12035 result.py:12149
msgid "* Beryl giggles. I can feel it through where her ribs are pressed against my thigh. * G-guys... We really earned this... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12036
msgid "* Cadence laughs as well. * Right? I made these cookies for fun, but this is like a whole-ass actual special occassion. I shoulda made something fancier."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12037 result.py:12151
msgid "Olivia: The cookies were excellent. Absolute chef's kiss."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12038
msgid "Beryl: Yeah, what says 'celebration' louder than c-cookies?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12039 result.py:12153
msgid "Cadence: Dunno... * She gives it a think. * What about, like, a soup of some kind? But with drugs in it?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12040 result.py:12154
msgid "* Decima coughs on a sudden laugh. * Ok. No, I'm glad you brought cookies. I had drug soup for dinner last night."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12041 result.py:12155
msgid "* Beryl sits up. * Oh my god... Berryglug has caffeine... It's drug soup..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12042 result.py:12156
msgid "Mind blown..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12043 result.py:12157
msgid "Beryl: Oops, sorry, mind. * She kisses me on the forehead and giggles ripple through the group."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12044
msgid "* The warmth can't last forever, though. Eventually the call of an actual bed becomes too loud to ignore. Final hugs and thigh-squeezes are exchanged and the trowels and papers are tidied away."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12045
msgid "* All evidence goes home with Forcier and Olivia except the Libidinal Wave Harvester schematic, which goes with Decima."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12046
msgid "* We say our goodbyes and I slip out. They head up Root St, but I go southwest, back the way I came. The industrial ruins are twice as dark and thrice as creepy as they were on the way in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12047 result.py:12161
msgid "* But the snug feelings follow me, keep me company. I'm alone, but I can practically still feel Beryl's body against me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12048 result.py:12162
msgid "* I'm far from the library, deep among the remains of the toppled metropolis when a sound startles even that last warmth from me. A ring."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12050
msgid "* Todays meeting of what is likely the gayest DIY detective agency in Pira city is taking place at the old Library. Beryl is on duty, and the huge, ruinous structure offers plenty of room for pensive pacing. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12054
msgid "* Signs of life start manifesting near the Library."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12055
msgid "* Being adjacent to the school that houses the Rustpup's headquarters, there's electricity and water. Some of the surrounding buildings are even topped with algea tanks. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12056
msgid "* In the Library, I follow an out-of-place baked-goods smell towards the alcove where my friends are sheltering. Cadence has made cookies for the occasion. Everyone seems excited."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12057
msgid "Beryl: HC! You m-made it! * She hops off the concrete ledge she's perched on and gives me a hug."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12059
msgid "Thanks! * I snag one of the hot little disks and cradle it. * So, what's up?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12060
msgid "Olivia: It's evidence review day. No big missions, just putting together the pieces we've already scrounged."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12061
msgid "* I cast my eyes downward at the papers stacked in the center of the groups circle. I recognize the folder from our raid of the Otter's safe-room from last time."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12062
msgid "* The recollection makes me extra thankful that we aren't risking our lives today. I take a seat on the floor in front of Olivia and nibble the cookie, ready to learn."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12063
msgid "* Forcier approaches the papers and carefully divides them into two substacks. * I've examined the documents and discovered two distinct categories. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12064
msgid "Forcier: The first... * They slide the larger, less crumpled stack towards us. * ...Are Gelcorp Documents stolen by the missing scientist."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12065
msgid "Forcier: And the second... * They slide the other stack forward. The paper is inconsistent in size and color, and some of the text is handwritten. * ...Are love letters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12066
msgid "Cadence: Love letters between..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12067
msgid "Forcier: Between Dr. Greene and his now missing wife, yes. They are intimate, but also provide a timeline and a context for the associated documents."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12068
msgid "Olivia: I've been reading through the GelFriend manual we recovered. About the slime monsters. Still pissed that Forcier and I didn't catch that when we were running our tests."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12069
msgid "Yeah, how did that happen?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12070
msgid "So, about the letters..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12071
msgid "Decima: That is kinda surprising, huh. Like, I've never had to check if something was made of nanobots but still, I can't imagine it's too hard."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12072
msgid "Forcier: We were under the incorrect assumption that we were dealing with an organic material when we chose to run simple reactivity tests."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12073
msgid "Olivia: Yeah, but even if we hadn't, most of what makes up the slimes isn't nanobots. The bots are suspended in a body safe gel that they control through electrical impulses."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12078
msgid "Cadence: Good. Ok, now back to the letters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12079
msgid "Forcier: Yes, the letters. * They begin sorting the letters into a row. * Many of them are dated, which allows us to fill in our timeline of events. I'll take the letters, you take the documents?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12080
msgid "* Olivia lifts the stack of documents and begins sorting them as well. Some things, like the GelFriend manual, are undated and set aside, but a few things, memos and emails, are able to fit into the timeline."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12081
msgid "* Two rows begin to form from left to right. Letters on the top, Gelcorp docs on the bottom. A few days to the left of the center, the letters stop, and the timeline continues on Gelcorp docs alone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12082
msgid "* Uninterested in helping sort, Decima picks up the GelFriend Manual and starts thumbing through. Everyone else gathers around Olivia and Forcier and studies the timeline"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12083
msgid "* Olivia points to the middle point. * This is the day that Dr. Greene appears on the water processing plant security footage. It's also the day that the hornomaly began."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12084
msgid "* Cadence points to the last letter. * And this was, what, a day before that?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12085
msgid "Forcier: Indeed. In a paranoid tone, he describes an abstract situation which is growing increasingly tense. He talks about needing to, quote, 'do what's right.'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12086
msgid "Forcier: He doesn't say so directly, but this letter almost reads as a goodbye to his wife. He's preparing to do something dangerous and wants her to know that he loves her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12087
msgid "Cadence: And since the hornomaly happens, like, right after this... That means he for sure knows about it in advance?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12088
msgid "Forcier: Nothing is certain, but it does seem likely."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12089
msgid "Cadence: So what DID happen on the day the hornomaly started?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12090
msgid "* Olivia leans in, all dramatic. * Simple. Greene bombed Gelcorp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12091
msgid "Cadence: Hell yeah!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12092
msgid "Beryl: A b-bomb? How do you know?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12093
msgid "Olivia: Cause it's what I'd have done. Check it out. We know he's having moral issues with something that Gelcorp is doing. Then we see the security footage."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12094
msgid "* Olivia dials it up on her wrist computer, then thrusts it out for us to see. On the tiny screen, the familiar man can be seen nervously crossing the main room in the water processing plant."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12095
msgid "Cadence: Yeah, you showed us this before, after we broke into that place. He for sure looks like he's up to some sketchy shit, but..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12096
msgid "* The pixelated doctor walks off screen. * Yeah. But check this out. * Olivia fast-forwards a bit, then turns the screen back to us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12097
msgid "Olivia: This is about an hour and a half later. * The room looks the same as ever. We wait, fixated, anticipating something crazy."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12098
msgid "* The lights in the plant's main room flicker. * See?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12099
msgid "* Decima peaks out from behind the GelFriend Manual. * That was it? Damn, I was like expecting a cryptid to emerge from the shadows or something."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12100
msgid "Cadence: You noodle, what would that have to do with a bomb? * She shoves Decima, but Decima just smugly eats another cookie. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12101
msgid "Olivia: I admit, it's not much on it's own, but..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12102
msgid "* She lifts a memo from a day later and starts reading from somewhere in the middle. * Due to yesterdays accident, the Gelatinous Nanorobotics wing has been upgraded to clearance level diamond... blah blah blah..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12103
msgid "* She scans the page till she finds what she's looking for, slaps it with the backs of her fingers. * Here. All members of the GelFriend project have been temporarily detained for loyalty reevaluation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12104
msgid "Olivia: Anyone with information pertaining to the accident in the Gelatinous Nanorobotics wing is to report it to security, something something, signed on behalf of CEO Cameron Seith."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12105
msgid "* Decima keeps turning pages in the manual, no longer reading it. * Ok, well fuck. That's some evidence. So Greene bombed Gelcorp? This motherfucker? * She points to the flabby, middle-aged geek on Olivia's computer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12106
msgid "Forcier: It may not have been a bombing, but it does seem that some sort of sabotage took place."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12107
msgid "Olivia: Yeah. * She starts pointing to memos down the row. * Day after that, they assigned more guards to Gelatinous Nanorobotics. Day after that, they ordered refills for the automated fire extinguishers on that floor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12108
msgid "* She gets to the end of the row. * And finally, there's this. No idea how Mrs. Greene got her hands on it, but it looks like an email from the head of security to Cameron Seith himself."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12109
msgid "Olivia: Five days after the bombing. Says they have a 'suspect in custody' who's 'awaiting interrogation.'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12110
msgid "* Olivia's smile fades as our sense of accomplishment gives way to the weight of what might have happened to Dr. Greene. We're all quite for a moment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12111
msgid "Decima: Uh, guys? * She turns the staple-bound GelFriend manual around to reveal a crumpled schematic tucked inside. * Did you see this?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12112
msgid "* The schematic is complex, and unlike the manual, clearly not meant to be interpreted by anyone other than a seasoned engineer. Fortunately, its title is clear."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12113
msgid "* Decima says it as I read it. * The Libidinal Wave Spooler. What in the actual fuck of a dick."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12114
msgid "* Cadence whispers in disbelief. * Fuckofadick..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12115
msgid "Beryl: So we have our answer? Th-this is what's c-causing the hornomaly? Some kind of horny mind-control machine?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12116
msgid "* Forcier folds their arms behind their back. * I believe we are jumping to conclusions based on the name of the machine, but... It does seem to be very likley."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12117
msgid "Forcier: I think it's safe to say that this is our greatest breakthrough thus far."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12118
msgid "* They smile. * So, before we celebrate, does anyone have any questions?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12119
msgid "* Hmmmm, questions..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12120
msgid "Why didn't the bombing stop the anomaly?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12121
msgid "What does any of this have to do with the slime?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12122
msgid "Nope, let's celebrate!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12123
msgid "Olivia: He must have fucked it up somehow. Maybe they discovered his plan before the bomb went off, or... Wait, no. We saw the flicker, and the fire extinguisher order form."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12124
msgid "* Olivia takes a pensive breath, rests her chin in her hand. * Maybe he underestimated the amount of force that would be required to destroy the machine? Or..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12125
msgid "Decima: Maybe he got lost and detonated it out of sheer frustration. That's probably what I would do if I were an eco-terrorist."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12126
msgid "* Forcier cuts in. * We lack the data to make any meaningful inference on the specific details of what went on inside Gelcorp. It's important to remember that our assumptions are just that; Assumptions."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12127
msgid "Forcier: So to answer your question, HC. We don't know. All we know is that there was sabotage of some kind, and then the hornomaly began."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12128
msgid "Olivia: the Libidinal Wave Spooler must be somehow connected to the GelFriend project. Don't know exactly how, but it's just too much of a coincidence that all this stuff went down on the same day."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12129
msgid "Cadence: I mean, the slimes are sex bots, right? So, maybe it's a marketing thing. Gelcorp makes everyone horny, then unveils the GelFriend and rakes in the dough."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12130
msgid "* Decima snorts. * Yeah, but have you seen this thing? * She waves the manual. * There isn't a soul in Pira City who could afford one of these motherfuckers. Excluding Gelcorp execs, of course."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12131
msgid "Decima: It'd be like tryna market HC here instead of places like Crystallica. No offense, HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12132
msgid "I dunno why I'd be offended by that. Also, that's a good point."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12133
msgid "Olivia: Could they be testing it here? I can't see any other possibility."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12134
msgid "Forcier: Perhaps. Decima, would you consider doing research into this machine?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12135
msgid "* Decima stuff the schematic into one of the pockets on her vest and grins. * Oh, I was already planning on it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12138
msgid "Cadence: Hell yeah! This is so much progress! This is legitimately so fucking cool! We're totally gonna save the city from psychic horny poisoning!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12139
msgid "* Beryl climbs to her feet and starts lighting the candles that are wax-sealed to every flat surface in her little reading nook."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12140
msgid "* From a canvas rucksack in the corner, she produces a two liter of Berryglug and starts passing it around."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12142
msgid "* Olivia swigs from the Glug bottle. * Chill, Decima. We can discuss bombs later. Lets just enjoy the win right now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12144
msgid "* Beryl's alcove is mostly concrete, but she has populated it with various rugs and floor-cushions."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12145
msgid "* It's not the most comfy, but it's still highly snuggleable. The library shelters us from the wind, but it's still open air."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12146
msgid "* I help her by fetching an ancient armchair from down in her storage cellar. My droid strength makes quick work of it, and of rearranging the decor for optimal group comfort."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12147
msgid "* The little chill draws us together into a nice cozy cuddle puddle. We keep each other warm and finish off the rest of the cookies by candle light."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12150
msgid "* Cadence laughs as well. * Right? I made these cookies for fun, but this is like a whole-ass actual special occasion. I shoulda made something fancier."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12152
msgid "Beryl: Yeah, what's says 'celebration' louder than c-cookies?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12158
msgid "* The warmth can't last forever, though. Eventually the call of an actual bed becomes too loud to ignore. Final hugs and thigh-squeezes are exchanged and the extra pillows are tidied away."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12159
msgid "* All evidence goes home with Forcier and Olivia except the Libidinal Wave Spooler schematic, which goes with Decima."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12160
msgid "* We say our goodbyes and I slip out. They head around towards Root St, but I go southwest, back the way I came. The industrial ruins are twice as dark and thrist as creepy as they were on the way in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12164
msgid "* A voice crackles through the ancient payphone. Shocked that this thing works, but even more shocked at the name he drops."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12165
msgid "Voice: This is CEO Cameron Seith. HC, is it?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12166
msgid "* I go to speak but he cuts me off. His voice is younger, more suave and perfect than the crusty CEO I was imagining."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12167
msgid "Seith: Don't talk. Just listen. You're a special case, HC. I'd be a fool not to have taken an interest in you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12168
msgid "Seith: You left your family. Escaped the Bellamy Intelligence security forces. Crossed the black dunes on foot. Can't be more than a few who've made that journey and lived."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12169
msgid "Seith: I can see your potential, HC. And I can see it's going to waste. You know you could climb the ladder just as quickly as I did, if you were given the opportunity."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12170
msgid "* He takes a deep breath through the nose. * All I'm offering you is some insight. Some outside perspective. Call them hard truths."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12171
msgid "Seith: This 'investigation' of yours? You're holding it together. You know it. Your friends know it. They have a goal and they're USING you to get there."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12172
msgid "Seith: They're using you for your perfect droid body. For your strength, your speed. For sex. * His words hiss into my ear and gut me. Rest nauseous in my stomach."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12173
msgid "Seith: And it's making you small. You're a mess, HC. You weren't designed for anxiety. To freeze up when shit gets tough."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12174
msgid "Seith: It's pathetic. You were built to be perfect, and they're beating you down. It's disgusting, really. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12175
msgid "* He chuckles, cold and jarring. * You're killing yourself to be one of them. To PRETEND to be human. But you're not. And you never will be."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12176
msgid "Seith: You are a tool, HC. A master key. There is NOTHING... * He lets the word breathe. * That you can't do. But you're just as much a slave here in Pira as you were in Crystallica."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12177
msgid "Seith: So, my advice? This has all been about self-discovery for you, I can understand that. But you need to let them go. There's nothing you can discover while you're searching on their terms."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12178
msgid "* He pauses, let's his speech sink in. * That's all. I'll be watching, HC. I kept Bellamy Intelligence out of Pira, and I won't throw you to Gelcorp security. For now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12179
msgid "Seith: But soon, a choice will have to be made. You or them. Goodbye, HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12180
msgid "* The call terminates into a flatline dial tone. I just stand there, as frozen as he said I'd be."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12181
msgid "* My hand is shaking as I hang the phone back up. What the fuck even just happened. Doubts blossom into my mind, who I am to my friends, how much of our success has been because Seith has allowed it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12182
msgid "* My fake-ass synthetic heart whirs into a panicked overdrive. Breathing quickens. Teeth clench so hard I worry they might break."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12183
msgid "* And then I run. Towards home, to a place I can bury myself and cry, hope for sleep to come. Hope for this feeling to pass. To wake up with blood that doesn't feel like icy sludge."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12184
msgid "* My mind races as my feet beat against the cement. It's just that and the brutal silence of night in the ruins. There's no screaming machine mantra out here to envelop me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12185
msgid "* Maybe in my apartment I will be soothed by the drone of the refrigerators and air conditioners and computers and..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12186
msgid "* ...I head home."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12187
msgid "* CEO Seith's cold voice is still echoing in my ears on the way to the group meetup. I'm so preoccupied that I don't notice Olivia until I'm scrambling to divert a collision course."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12188
msgid "* She had just reached the bottom of the stairs to her apartment when I had stopped her. * HC!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12189
msgid "Olivia! Sorry about that! * I straighten up and smile, as if the synthetic adrenaline coursing through me could be persuaded to chill for the sake of good manners. * Heading out? Are we meeting somewhere else today?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12190
msgid "* She looks surprised. * Oh, no. You don't have to worry about a meeting today."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12191
msgid "Olivia: Everyone's at the Library trying to find documents about the Libidinal Harvester. See if they can learn anything more concrete about its purpose."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12192
msgid "Olivia: It's just busy work. Didn't think you'd be interested."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12193
msgid "* I can't help but hear Seith again. Library busy work doesn't require speed or strength or sex."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12194
msgid "Oh, ok... * I'm not hiding my disappointment well, but Olivia doesn't seem to notice. * What about you, gonna go help them out?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12195
msgid "* Olivia shuffles her feet. * Nah, I'm heading to the Lemon. Gonna hang out with Magdalena and some friend of hers."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12196
msgid "* Of course, their lives go on without me. Thoughts like fireworks rapidly flare to life and die, inundating my mind with a chaos that can almost all be categorized as self-doubt."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12197
msgid "* Is my sadness selfish? Aggressive? Abusive? Am I being tricked? Manipulated?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12198
msgid "* Have I been pushed from the group in accordance with some social law that I wasn't aware of? Am I making all this up? Seeing signs that aren't there?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12199
msgid "* It's all sharp, all violently perforating my skull from the inside out. The most familiar thought of all comes at the end; Am I, in this moment of anxiety, fabricating my own suffering out of nothing?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12200
msgid "Olivia: Wanna come?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12201
msgid "Oh, uh... * Even if I take the invitation at surface value, don't read into it, I doubt I could hold a normal conversation together like this. Another blow from inside. Fabricating my own suffering."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12202
msgid "No, that's ok. Thanks though, but I'll take the time off. * I wave, turn, and we go our separate ways."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12203
msgid "* Alone, on the walk back around the rim of the chasm, I have time to settle down. Solitude can be it's own abyss, but apparently it's what I need at the moment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12204
msgid "* Silence, but for the soft crush of ash under my feet, is kinda therapeutic. About halfway home, though, Sal staggers from between a pair of shadowed ruins off the path toward Skipnoise Avenue."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12205
msgid "* As he comes into view, I'm able to take in the sorry state of him. Bruised, breathing somehow more ragged than usual, crusty blood caught up in the stubble on his chin, he looks as if he lost a fist-fight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12206
msgid "Sal: HC? Ah, gee, am I glad to see you... * He takes another shuddering breath, prepping for some exposition. * I'm gonna need some help..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12207
msgid "* I rush to his side and try to get my arm up under his, but he shrugs me off. * Nah, not that kinda help. I'm tougher than I look. * He wheezes out a laugh, but then his face turns cold. * I found Mrs. Greene."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12208
msgid "* I don't know what to say. We've been on her tail for long enough that she was beginning to feel like a myth. * Are you... Is she alive?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12209
msgid "Sal: Yeah, for now. But she's fixed on doing something that's gonna get her dead."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12210
msgid "* He leads me away from the Skipnoise Path3D and to a burned-out building in which he'd stashed his van."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12211
msgid "* It wasn't clean before, but the ashy coating on its roof suggests that whatever footwork Sal was doing took a few days."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12212
msgid "* He gets in and I join him on the passenger side. * What were you doing on Skipnoise? Did the Otters do this to you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12213
msgid "* After several ignition attempts, Sal coaxes life into the engine. I crank the window, let the smell of ozone out. * I was tryna catch up with Mrs. Greene. Not an easy task."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12214
msgid "Sal: Slippery, for a housewife. I think I only found her cause she trusts me. More than she trust the Otters, anyway."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12215
msgid "Yeah? And where is she now?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12216
msgid "* We roll out of the ruin and towards Root Street. * She got out while I kept 'em distracted. Think I know where she'll be now, though."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12217
msgid "* He looks at me, expression grim. * She's going after her husband."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12218
msgid "* We ride while Sal explains that they were able to confirm Dr. Greene's location, that he is in fact within the Gelcorp complex. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12219
msgid "Sal: She's got it in her head that they're gonna kill him. Might even make a public thing of it. Execute him for corporate treason. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12220
msgid "* I swallow. Thinking. * Are they?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12221
msgid "* Sal sighs. * Yeah. I think they might."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12222
msgid "* It takes some cruising, but we eventually find her in the area Sal had guessed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12223
msgid "* Blocks from Root Street in the East Side outskirts, hunched behind a salvage dealer, hand-packing shotgun shells with whatever sharps bits she finds on the ground."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12224
msgid "* She's nothing like her picture. I'm looking at a woman who, for weeks, has been on the run, stripped of her certainties and desperate for the one she loves."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12225
msgid "* Now, armed with scrap metal, she's ready to throw herself into the gnashing maw of Gelcorp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12226
msgid "* And I can't really fault her for it. She's been pushed well past her limits and is hungry for blood, be it Gelcorps or her own. I know how it feels to simply be unable to wait any longer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12227
msgid "* She doesn't look up from her work, but she's clearly scowling. Her voice is a battleground between bitter and hopeless. * Why are you here, Sal. You already gave me your answer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12228
msgid "* She seats a buster-cell in the bottom of another empty shell, then bare-palms a mixture of rusty bolts and broken glass on top, cotton-plugs it, seals it with a some kind of hand-pressing tool. Sal sighs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12229
msgid "Sal: I promised I'd look for a way to make it happen before saying no. My friend here is the closest thing we have to a chance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12230
msgid "* He pauses, puts a hand on her shoulder. * I brought her to show you that I tried. The Rust Pups were a no."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12231
msgid "Sal: I don't have to tell you that asking the Otters wouldn't get us anywhere. We've got a Bellamy droid, and we've got a couple guns."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12232
msgid "Sal: It's just... It's not enough, Mrs. Greene. We can't do it. We could try this with ten times the force and we'd still be beating ourselves against a brick wall."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12233
msgid "Sal: You've got to accept that your husband is gone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12234
msgid "* She doesn't react. It would make sense that she's been steeling herself against the fact that her husband is beyond saving, but it's still disconcerting to see."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12235
msgid "* After a minute of gritted teeth, she speaks. * So, what? Are you here to talk me out of this? I can't just do nothing. Not after all this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12236
msgid "Mrs Greene: I can't just... Let him die. * She cracks the gun in two, angrily shoves shells into a handful of exposed chambers."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12237
msgid "* Sal puts his hands back in his pockets. * I don't think you should do nothing. Gelcorp is pushing to get this whole thing over with. The execution is just a part of what I dug up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12238
msgid "* He kneels next to her. * There were more raids this morning than the last few weeks combined. They are looking for you and, sooner or later, they're going to find you. We need to get you out of the city."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12239
msgid "Sal: The pups do salvage runs. Theft and trade outside the city. I've talked with em and I've gotten you passage on one of these convoys. We just need to get you there safely."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12240
msgid "Sal: It'll be hard out there. Could be weeks in the dunes before they get you to another settlement. But I'm telling you right now, this is your only shot at surviving all of--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12241
msgid "* She cuts him off, spits through her teeth. * Let them kill me. I'll take down as many--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12242
msgid "* Sal raises his voice and cuts back in. * This isn't going to be the blaze of glory you think it is! Do you want the last thing your husband sees to be your bullet-riddled corpse?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12243
msgid "* She snaps the shotgun closed then stays silent for a minute. Then, to my surprise, she turns to me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12244
msgid "Mrs. Greene: I need a third opinion, Droid. Do I let my husband die? Or do I go after him."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12245
msgid "Sal: Please, HC. Our window for escape is shrinking by the minute."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12246
msgid "* I swallow, thinking."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12247
msgid "We need to try and rescue Mr. Greene."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12248
msgid "We need to get you out of the City."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12249
msgid "* Sal stands back up and turns from us, failing to hide his anger. * God damn it, HC! You're going to get her killed! You really want to do this?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12250
msgid "* Before I can say anything, Mrs. Greene interrupts. * You heard her. She's in. * She grabs Sal, turns him around and looks him in the eye. * Are you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12251
msgid "* Sal shrugs her off. * Fuck no! You two wanna get killed, that's your business. I'm out. I..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12252
msgid "* He sighs. * I'll give you a ride to the perimeter, but that's the best I can do. It'll give me more time to talk you out of this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12253
msgid "* But he doesn't try. The whole ride we just sit in silence, Greene throttling the handle of her greasy gun, Sal looking almost scared."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12254
msgid "*  When we stop at the fence that marks the edge of the corps domain, he gets out of the van with us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12255
msgid "* As we dip through the cut in the chainlink, it dawns on me that I'm glad my friends aren't here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12256
msgid "* Maybe it's bravery, cockiness, that I have to prove something to them. Maybe it's that I want them to mourn, to blame themselves..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12257
msgid "* Or maybe it's just that I expect to die here. That I deserve it in some way. That it's my role in all this. I try and focus on the plush ashfall beneath my shoes, the treads of the two in front of me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12258
msgid "* If anything is proof to the contrary of what Seith said, it's that the human brain is too volatile a crucible for such a simple conclusion to be drawn."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12259
msgid "* Do my friends think I'm just a machine to be used? Or are they as ambivalent as I am."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12260
msgid "* Now would be a good time to be the machine, I suppose. Fuck being a tender human with emotions and connections. I want to be like Mrs. Greene."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12261
msgid "* Under the black mantle of the towering compound, lights flicker on the horizon. Corporate residences, offices, and laboratories encircled by troop-transports and drones with spotlights."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12262
msgid "* Our approach is slow, often requiring a belly crawl when a drone gets close, but eventually we make it to a small depot outside the housing compound."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12263
msgid "* Anything to block our full exposure if helpful, but there's still a long way to go."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12264
msgid "* Sal rummages through his trenchcoat for a pair of binoculars, then pokes his head around the wall. With a gasp, he withdraws and slumps to the ground next to us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12265
msgid "* Mrs. Greene wipes some sweat from her forehead. * What is it?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12266
msgid "* Sal wavers. * I wouldn't--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12267
msgid "* She snatches the binoculars from him and looks towards the housing compound. A moment later, a sob breaks the hush. I peek out as well."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12268
msgid "* Central to the housing compound is a kind of event-square of raised concrete, atop which a flagpole has been erected. Greene is kneeling shackled to it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12269
msgid "* Mrs. Greene starts to get up, but Sal grabs her and pulls her back down. * That's a good hundred yards. We need a way to close the gap without getting spotted."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12270
msgid "* Set into the concrete wall on which we lean is a dusty, padlocked door. * Let's see what we've got at our disposal. * I twist the lock till it snaps, let it thud to the ashy ground."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12271
msgid "* The interior is pitch dark, but my eyes quickly adapt. The depot, which appears to have once been for underground powerline maintenance has been adapted into storage for defunct tech."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12272
msgid "* Tucked among rusting transformers, dark shelves are piled with supplies. Various insulators coiled on spools, hard hats and fuses. Nothing useful. I push further toward the back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12273
msgid "* There's a retired armored drone. If I could get it running, I suppose we could ride it into the housing compound. It's down-facing lights should obscure us from anyone below."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12274
msgid "* Suggest using the drone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12275
msgid "* Keep looking."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12276
msgid "* There are underground tunnels, packed with fat electrical cables, but it looks like there's enough room for us to make it through. One of them is towards the housing complex."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12277
msgid "* Suggest using the tunnel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12278
msgid "* Best option is the drone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12279
msgid "* The two don't look convinced of my wisdom, but follow me down the hatch nonetheless. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12280
msgid "*  Maintenance access seems designed to accommodate little more than remote repair tools or particularly slender engineers, but we have to make it work."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12281
msgid "* The cold night air has done nothing to dissipate the choking heat in the tunnel, and Sal's coughing is worse than usual. At each junction, we have to squeeze past a ceramic bushing hot enough to leave a mark."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12282
msgid "* It's dead slow, and worse, it's a blind crawl. I can track our distance traveled with decent enough precision, but without an exit point, I'm not sure what we'll do when we get to the compound."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12283
msgid "* At just under an hour we reach my estimation of a the coordinates."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12284
msgid "* Above is is a tangle of black wires and what looks like metal grating, but at least it's not the solid concrete we'd been ducking under for most of the crawl."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12285
msgid "* I try and force myself to stand through the mess of shadows, but there's not enough room. For a second, my heart leaps towards panic. A breath of cool air would do me good, I think."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12286
msgid "* Mrs. Greene's muffled voice sounds from behind me, but I don't even have room to turn towards her. * What's the holdup?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12287
msgid "We're here. * I hope I'm telling the truth."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12288
msgid "* Another wet cough from Sal. * Well, that's good news. I didn't wanna have to back out of here. * There's a pause. * What are we waiting for?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12289
msgid "I'm trying to figure a way out. Just gotta... * I roll onto my back and grab some of the pipes and wires above me, start pulling."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12290
msgid "* There's a loud pop and a smell like a plasma cutter igniting, then sparks shower into the tunnel. I don't let it stop me. There's at least a foot or two of material I need to get through to reach the surface."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12291
msgid "* But it just keeps going. The whole Gelcorp region is artificially flat, so I know I'm not under a hill."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12292
msgid "* Was the tunnel sloping so gently that I didn't notice? I keep ripping out wires, getting to my knees when there's room."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12293
msgid "* I'm leaving a lot of wounded sockets and jagged pipe-ends. Lots of sharp edges. I try to channel my thoughts towards digging and away from curiosity about how much of this could potentially electrocute us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12294
msgid "* When I've torn out enough that I can fully stand up, I hit the top. Heatsinks, cables, and other electrical debris is heaped at my feet, but above me is just a steel plate. I don't see hinges."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12295
msgid "Sal: What now? Everything ok up there?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12296
msgid "* I swallow. * Y-yeah. Yeah I'm almost done. * Bracing myself, I hit the ceiling with a closed fist. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12297
msgid "* It doesn't budge, but the impact jolts up my arm and into my shoulder blade. I ignore the aching in my chassis and strike again. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12298
msgid "* Still nothing, but on my third hit, it budges. I brace with my palms and push till it comes free. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12299
msgid "* In the light from above, I examine my shaking hand. The skin on my knuckles is pounded down to the chrome, leaking clear fluid down to my elbow. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12300
msgid "* There's no pain. Not if I disable it. I hoist myself out of the tunnel and reach my uninjured hand back down behind me. Mrs. Greene is the first out, and the easiest."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12301
msgid "*  The tube is almost too narrow for Sal, but I hoist him out as well."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12302
msgid "* We look around what seems to be a corresponding maintenance room, but this one is smaller, less dusty. A fluorescent light buzzes above us, but we're alone. Regardless, Sal produces his gun."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12303
msgid "* No more talking. We know what we're here for. Sal eases the door on the far wall open, bracing and brandishing the sidearm. We push through into an empty hallway, then through another door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12304
msgid "* It unseals to the sound of calm wind and the distant trilling of drone-thrusters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12305
msgid "* The cement stage and Dr. Greene are only a couple dozen feet away. Whatever's being churned up in the Gelcorp factory, we can taste it in the air out here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12306
msgid "* On the opposite side of the housing complex fence, security paces the perimeter in pairs, but there's nowhere for us to hide. All we can hope for is that we get to the Doctor before they notice us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12307
msgid "* I call them over to the large drone, explain my plan. * This could easily lift us and carry us over the fence, if we can get power to it. * Quietly, I wish that Olivia were here to assist in its reprogramming."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12308
msgid "* The two look skeptically at the plastic hulk. To prove I'm serious, I pull away a piece of its outer shell and begin poking around the circuitry underneath."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12309
msgid "* Sal joins me, while Greene watches in silence, keenly aware that time is ticking by."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12310
msgid "* After a few moments of our best-intentioned diagnostics, we resolve to simple switch out the battery and induce a factory reset."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12311
msgid "* Opening a bay door on the other side of the depot, I push the thing outside while the other two search for a battery."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12312
msgid "* Moments later, Mrs. Greene and Sal appear, each lifting one end of a batter that must be much heavier than its size would suggest. I disconect the dead one from its crusty bay and install the new cell."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12313
msgid "* A light indicates that the machine is powered, but nothing further happens. I press the factory reset. Nothing. Maybe I need to hold it down?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12314
msgid "* Mrs. Greene pushes me aside and hammers the button."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12315
msgid "* Despite her technique not differing from mine, the machine activates what I assume is its instructionless default mode, leaping several feet off the ground and hovering in place, spotlights blazing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12316
msgid "* Seeing the thing in motion quadruples my doubts. It's agility, the imperceptible speed of its rotors, imbues it with a living chaos that makes me wonder how anyone could survive its seemingly inevitable crash."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12317
msgid "* We recoil and brace ourselves, the animal tension of being in the midst of a much larger beast having gripped us. The doubt is clear on their faces, too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12318
msgid "* A hushed argument ensues about how to proceed. It's resolved that without programming, the only way to get it to do what we want is by forcing it physically."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12319
msgid "* I test by lifting the drone with all my strength, and find that it hovers at whatever level I let it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12320
msgid "* With only my weight and not the earth to brace against, lowering it is much more difficult. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12321
msgid "* We decide that the only viable approach is to release the drone at speed against the fence, and to hope that it provides distraction enough to cover our approach."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12322
msgid "* I do my best to keep it in place while Sal and Mrs. Greene hammer the prop-arms out of alignment and into an angle we hope will aim the drone forwards."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12323
msgid "* My feet slide a bit across the dusty plain, confirming a general trajectory. We wrestle it out from behind the depot, and release it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12324
msgid "* It immediately becomes the high-speed, lights-blazing projectile we had hoped, but its path curves upwards, just over the fence."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12325
msgid "* As we sprint, we watch as it glances off a rooftop and spins, screaming, into a far guard tower."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12326
msgid "* There is no great explosion, but neither does the thing settle down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12327
msgid "* When we reach the fence, it's still bouncing around in the tower, tearing through walls and blowing out windows. An alarm begins to sound, but the distraction is working perfectly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12328
msgid "* While all eyes are fixed away from us, we quietly climb the fence and let ourselves down within the compound."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12329
msgid "* The ash outside muffled our sprinting, but in this concrete lot, we have to be more intentional with our steps."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12330
msgid "* Dr. Greene is only a couple dozen yards away, shackled to his post. His position, once centered among the many guard towers, is no longer surveiled."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12331
msgid "* We run. He doesn't look up at the sound of our footsteps."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12332
msgid "* It isn't until I've snapped the chain that he even seems to recognize what's going on. Wordlessly, Sal grabs him by the scruff of his coat and we start hauling him towards the gate."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12333
msgid "* Whether it was the pop of the chain or his half-drug, half-stumbling footsteps, the guards take notice of us. Any hope that they want to take us alive are dashed as they open fire."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12334
msgid "* Thunder cracks and concrete craters erupt at our feet as we sprint towards the gate. We hit it and I start tearing with all my strength. On either side of me, Sal and Mrs. Greene open up on the guards."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12335
msgid "* More flesh wears from my fingertips as I flail against the fence."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12336
msgid "* Metal to primal metal, though, I make it through. Beyond the fence, orbiting drones have fixed us in wavering beams of light, and a troop transport has screamed to a halt."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12337
msgid "* Showing more martial sense than I'd have expected from a corporate housewife, Mrs. Greene had conserved several of the shells in her four-barreled silo of a shotgun."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12338
msgid "* She's now using the shells to evacuate the driver and passenger from the front cabin of the vehicle."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12339
msgid "* We're at the driver side door before the glass shrapnel and spray of blood has time to reach the ground. I pull hard at the window frame, removing the door entirely and the carcass of the security guard within."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12340
msgid "* I leap over the center console into the passenger seat, and the three cram in behind me, the doctor, the wife, and then Sal at the wheel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12341
msgid "* Behind the two seats is a divider between the cabin and the transportation bay, and behind the divider is the muffled voices of the guards."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12342
msgid "* Sal hits the gas, then breaks a window in the center of the divider with his pistol, fires the remaining several shots into the hole. There are screams from the hole as the surviving security pours out the rear door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12343
msgid "* The transport is moderately armored, but more than a few of the bullets we're fleeing make it through the rear doors and the divider."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12344
msgid "* Rear view mirrors and a dash-mounted nav system explode into powdered silicate and twisted copper."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12345
msgid "* Mrs. Greene cracks the shotgun, ejects the four smoking hulls to the cabin floor, then begins slotting fresh ones from her pockets. Sal passes his revolver and a heavy, crushed-velvet pouch to me. Dr. Greene weeps."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12346
msgid "* I fumble out the small handful of bullets from the pouch, spilling a couple to the floor, and shakily load the sidearm as fast as I can. Behind us, a dozen drones and another couple of transports roar."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12347
msgid "* Out the passenger window, the hood of a transport pulls into view. I glance out, see the driver with his SMG braced across his lap, pointed at us. The muzzle flares and a dozen cracks and impacts rattle my eardrums."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12348
msgid "* These underground tunnels are packed with fat electrical cables, but it looks like there's enough room for us to make it through. One of them is towards the housing complex."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12349 result.py:12389
msgid "* Return fire."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12350
msgid "* Sensing that I've frozen, Mrs. Greene throws herself across my lap and points her shotgun out the window."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12351
msgid "* The exchange is bright and disorienting, and results in the pursuing vehicle swerving and rolling into the dust, and a bullet wound erupting in Mrs. Greene's neck."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12352
msgid "* I fire all six rounds into the windshield of the pursuing vehicle, immediately ending the spray of bullets and sending it swerving and rolling into the dust. On the driver side, the other transport appears."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12353
msgid "* Mrs. Greene throws herself across Sal's lap and points her shotgun out the window. The exchange is bright and disorienting, and over in a moment. A bullet wound has erupted in Mrs. Greene's neck."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12354
msgid "* She pulls back, dropping the gun and splaying across the three of us, blood fountaining from the wound in her neck. There are only a few waning beats as she dies wordlessly in her husbands lap."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12355
msgid "* The scent of blood and spent powder in the cabin is nauseating. I search for the glint of metal on the floor, for the bullets I dropped or the shotgun, but every surface seems to glisten with gore."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12356
msgid "* Beyond our shattered windshield, the chainlink fence is fast approaching. The remaining transport slams into our driver side, but Sal manages to keep control. We're so close. So fucking close."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12357
msgid "* But they ram us again, and we roll. Dust and glass and darkness blind me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12358
msgid "* I'm turned like a polishing stone, unaware of what makes up the jagged storm that transforms me..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12359
msgid "* I reorient myself to a tilted world."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12360
msgid "* Mrs. Greene is lifeless at my side."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12361
msgid "* Between the crumpled windshield I watch Sal and the Doctor fleeing into the dark city."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12362
msgid "* A booted foot lands by my head, and I look up..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12363 result.py:12411
msgid "* In time to see the other come down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12364
msgid "* Sal waits, breathe held, for Greene's verdict."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12365
msgid "* After what feels like full minutes, she bows her head. * Fine. Let's go."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12366
msgid "* Sal sighs in relief, then stands. * Right. Get in the van. We'll have you to cities edge in no time."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12367
msgid "* He opens the sliding side door for Mrs. Greene, then turns to me, carefully draws his gun. * I'm on the wheel, which means you're... * He holds it out. * On this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12368
msgid "* I gingerly lift the revolver from his palm. * Am I gonna have to..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12369
msgid "* He gets close, lowers his voice, as if to shield Mrs. Greene. He must have forgotten that she's the most prepped for a fight of the three of us. * I hope not. But look..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12370
msgid "Sal: If something happens, it would make me feel a lot better to know that you've got my back. We're in deeper than I ever meant to be."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12371
msgid "* He gives me a rough pat on the shoulder, then goes round to the driver door. I hop in the passenger side trying keep the gun pointed somewhere harmless."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12372
msgid "* The East Side outskirts and its firelit hovels thin out as we move slowly west, keeping to the darkest parts of the empty ruins between us and Skipnoise."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12373
msgid "* A few times, we kill the engine as a drone flys by, far overhead."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12374
msgid "* It occurs to me that Mrs. Greene will likely never see Pira City again."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12375
msgid "* Securing passage over the black dune wasteland was probably hard enough that, in a new place, stripped of connections, she'll never achieve it again."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12376
msgid "* I recall my own trip, sprinting those hundred miles until the heat of my core blistered through to my outer skin."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12377
msgid "* The micro-shards of onyx glass that were lifted by the wind and sent scattered into my flesh. Each dune peak a grit blaster that reduced me by microns."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12378
msgid "* And what Pira meant when I reached it. Bastion. A place where, for a time, I thought I could belong. I wonder how long it will be till I'm turned back out into that cutting void."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12379
msgid "* Thoughs of eternal isolation, wandering, polished to the bone, through the desert, come to mind. I try and refocus on Mrs. Greene. On anything, really."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12380
msgid "* Out the window, black-eyed ruins drift by. Despite it being a haven for so many, we are shuttling someone for whom nowhere here is safe."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12381
msgid "* The striking head of Gelcorp, which so often remains furled behind its walls, is demonstrating its reach."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12382
msgid "* And, apparently, its venom. Sal, glancing repeatedly into the rearview mirror, suddenly floors it. * Damn... There was a drone I was too late to dodge that I had been hoping wasn't Gelcorp. Looks like I was wrong."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12383
msgid "* Behind us, the drone's spotlight flares to life and fixes on us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12384
msgid "* Minutes later, two troop transports rounds a corner and fill the shadowed ruins behind us with blue and purple light. Our dark strip of ruined road has become a blazing beam of energy cutting the city in half."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12385
msgid "* Full speed, the van is more formidable than it appears, and the troop transports aren't known for their speed, but over the shattered asphalt littered with debris, our wheels can't compete with Gelcorp's hover thrusters."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12386
msgid "* I'm tossed against my seatbelt with each bump."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12387
msgid "* I can only imagine how Greene is doing, freefloating in the back. No time to worry about it. Before I have a chance to roll down the window, it explodes under a burst of SMG fire from the transport."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12388
msgid "* Shards of window and side-mirror fill the cabin of the van, agitated further by each rocky jolt of a road obstacle overcome. When the burst has paused, I see my opportunity to attack the closer of the two transports. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12390
msgid "* Sensing that I've frozen, Mrs. Greene throws open the sliding door and points her shotgun out into the night."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12391
msgid "* The exchange is bright and disorienting, and results in the pursuing vehicle swerving and rolling into the wall of a passing ruin."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12392
msgid "* Mrs. Greene cracks the shotgun, ejects the four smoking hulls to the cabin floor, then begins slotting fresh ones from her pockets."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12393
msgid "* I try and calm myself, wrapping and rewrapping my shaking fingers around the grip of the gun."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12394
msgid "* She had hardly finished when another volley is unleashed upon us. What's left of the windshield mixes with the cloud of upholstery exploding into the cabin."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12395
msgid "*  I grit my teeth and wait the devastating couple of seconds for it to be over."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12396
msgid "* I fire all six rounds into the windshield of the pursuing vehicle, immediately ending the spray of bullets and sending it swerving and rolling into the dust."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12397
msgid "* Sal points to the glove compartment where I find a faded velvet pouch full of heavy slugs. I fumble out a small handful, spilling a few on the glass-strewn floor, and shakily reload the sidearm as fast as I can."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12398
msgid "* I had hardly finished when another volley is unleashed upon us. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12399
msgid "* What's left of the windshield mixes with the cloud of upholstery exploding into the cabin. I grit my teeth and wait the devastating couple of seconds for it to be over."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12400
msgid "* There is no time to outpour the emotions stirred by my survival. In fact, no time to feel them at all. I lean back out the window and take aim with the revolver."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12401
msgid "* Apparently wishing to avoid the fate of their counterpart, the troop transport swerves hard behind our van. Greene moves to the back door and swings it open, blasts another four rounds into the vehicle."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12402
msgid "* All the shot I can track is low, deflected off the plate armor below the windshield. The transport swerves again and disappears up a cross street."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12403
msgid "* For a minute, I wonder if I had missed a stray pellet that might have taken out the driver, and that they were lucky enough to veer into an intersection instead of a solid wall."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12404
msgid "* They might be rolling to a stop a span behind us that stretches with each passing second."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12405
msgid "* Celebration is further encouraged by the thinning ruins, the glittering blackness only a handful of blocks ahead. We've almost made it to our rendezvous."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12406
msgid "* But in each intersection, I begin to see the transport again, parallel but gradually overtaking us. I look for the shot, leaning over Sal's lap and pointing the gun out his window."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12407
msgid "* No clean shot comes, and soon they're far enough ahead that our intersection passings no longer coincide. For a second more, confusion."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12408
msgid "* Then, from under a rusted, drooping traffic light, they hurdle full speed into our path. Sal hits the brakes, but we slide fast into its flank in a cacophony of twisting metal and chiming glass."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12409
msgid "* We deflect off them and roll. Dust and glass and darkness blind me. I'm turned like a polishing stone, unaware of what makes up the jagged storm that transforms me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12410
msgid "* I reorient myself to a tilted world. Between the crumpled windshield I watch Sal and Mrs. Greene fleeing into the dark beyond the city. A booted foot lands by my head, and I look up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12412
msgid ".............."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12413
msgid "-------up----"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12414
msgid "*****************//////[wake]---- up-----"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12415
msgid "* I open my eyes, woken from what feels like days of dreamless coma, pain driving through my skull, static crackling in my ears."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12416
msgid "* I'd have guessed the noise was some side-effect of my head wound, but a cold voice reveals it to be an intercom."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12417
msgid "Intercom: I'll admit it, I'm confused."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12418
msgid "* Though I've heard it before, the youth and vitality in Seith's voice still strikes me. He can't be any older than I'm designed to be."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12419
msgid "Seith: If I was a betting man, I'd have said I'd gotten through to you. That you'd seen your friends for what they are, and yourself for what you'll always be to them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12420
msgid "Seith: And yet here you are. It hurts me to see you like this, HC. Really does... * There's a pause."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12421
msgid "Seith: Ah, well. Maybe, in a few days, I'll bring you up here and we can have a drink, talk it out. * His voice gets icy. * There are a few things I need to take care of in the meantime, though."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12422
msgid "* There's a click as the intercom goes quiet and I'm left alone. The cell is small, with a cot and nothing else. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12423
msgid "* The walls are of a seamless, dense white plastic, except for one, which is of what appears to be acrylic, several inches thick, and punctuated with air-holes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12424
msgid "* I can already tell that there's no hope of me tearing this place down. I don't even try."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12425
msgid "* I collapse on the cot and start weeping. The only sound is my tears and the conduction fluid from my torn knuckles pattering on the floor. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12426
msgid "* I wake again to the sound of the intercom. In the narrow hall outside my chamber, a guard in white platemaile paces."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12427
msgid "* There's pride in Seith's crackling voice. * Everything has been put into motion. I won't keep you here for more than few days."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12428
msgid "* I clench my fists, the chrome shining through the torn synth-flesh at my knuckles."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12429
msgid "What are you going to do to me?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12430
msgid "What are you going to do to my friends?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12431
msgid "Do you know what I'm going to do to you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12432
msgid "Seith: For now, nothing but observe. You've been brainwashed and abused by your friends for a long while now, and I need to know if you're capable of breaking their programming."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12433
msgid "Seith: You think that by pretending to be human, you can transcend some rigidity you assume is inherent to being a machine. But you're wrong. You've never been as predictable as you are right now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12434
msgid "Seith: For now, nothing. We're moving on the Rust Pups first."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12435
msgid "* Seith laughs. * Let me guess. Fuck me, push me down, or burst into tears? Or some combination thereof? Not a lot of subtly in the modus operandi your friends have cultivated in you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12436
msgid "Seith: I WANT you to surprise me, HC! I want to free you from their expectations and turn you loose! They have imposed a human identity on you, and I promise that if you can forget it, you can do anything."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12437
msgid "Seith: So put me out of mind, for now. This tunnel vision isn't doing you any good. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12438
msgid "Seith: Before I go, let me give you something clear. A schedule. * He pauses, lets the emotion drain from his voice. * Tonight, we move on the Rust Pups."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12439
msgid "Seith: It's a six hour operation that should leave the biggest threat to us eradicated, their weapons confiscated."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12440
msgid "Seith: The Otters come next. Because they kill for cash, they're always going to be a little unpredictable."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12441
msgid "Seith: The Tunnel Girls are formidable, but the great thing about isolationists is that the world can go to hell and they won't raise a hand to help."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12442
msgid "Seith: So it's your friends that come in third on our hit list. Surprisingly capable little bunch, I have to say. Being mostly unarmed, I'd consider letting them live, if they wern't so dead-set on their vendetta."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12443
msgid "* There's a pause as if he's waiting for a reaction. I have nothing to say, paralyzed by the lead shot dropping through my soul. I fall to my knees."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12444
msgid "* A guard outside notices my anguish, turns to the acrylic wall to spectate. Behind that faceless helm, I know he's grinning."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12445
msgid "Seith: Ruminate on that. * There's a termination click on the intercom and he's gone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12446
msgid "............."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12447
msgid "* Again, the crackling intercom wakes me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12448
msgid "Seith: You know, I bet you've never been so close to human are you are right now. In this cell, utterly powerless to escape. In here, your biosynthetic muscles might as well be organic."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12449
msgid "Seith: Maybe this will turn out to be one of those 'don't know what you've got till it's gone' situations. I just hope you can gain some appreciation for how truly perfect you are."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12450
msgid "* I try to ignore him, but the cell is a voice-filled void. My hands are shaking, knuckles still wounded to the bone. Not that I expected them to heal. Droids can't regenerate their flesh."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12451
msgid "Seith: Don't make the mistake of appropriating human psychology. Droids are infinitely resilient. When your friends are dead, you'll be able to forget them if you wish."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12452
msgid "Seith: This part might be hard, but ripping off the bandaid always is."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12453
msgid "* The guard outside the cell stands motionless. Despite the identical armor an weapons, I can tell he's a different human under his shell. A few inches taller. Cop posture."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12454
msgid "* I wonder what they all think of me in here. Is this a prison to them? Or just a storage room for a dangerous machine. I punch the acrylic wall, but he doesn't flinch."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12455
msgid "* I can't take this. Even my body feels like a cell, now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12456
msgid "* At the moment I wake, I resolve not to leave the slab of a bed they're provided me. I want to become a thing. An inanimate object. I will shut myself down by sheer force of will."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12457
msgid "* There's no Seith this morning. I've been woken up by the muffled bickering of two guards outside my cell."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12458
msgid "* I can't hear much through the acrylic, but they seem to be disagreeing about something. I roll over, try and ignore it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12459
msgid "* Then there's a slam and my eyes fly back open. One guard has the other in a vicious grapple and is ramming the back of their helmet into the wall."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12460
msgid "* There's only one gun between the two, and they're both struggling for it. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12461
msgid "* I spring to my feet, more out of fear and uncertainty than out of a desire to intervene. Not that I could even if I wanted to."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12462
msgid "* The pinned guard drives an armored knee into the other's gut, pushes him away. Before he can un-double and lift his gun, the first guard comes at him swinging, knocking loose his helmet. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12463
msgid "* The man underneath is exactly what I'd expect. Buzzed hair, boring everything, but instead of smug superiority all I read in his visage is rage. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12464
msgid "* Again, he tries to lift the gun, and again, the struggle increases in desperation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12465
msgid "* Suddenly, I'm not the one in the zoo. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12466
msgid "* Behind the window, two feral creatures have ditched the trappings of combat training and taken up the weapons god gave them, gun torn from it's shoulder sling and forgotten in a corner, knives ignored in their sheaths."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12467
msgid "* I've seen death since I've come to Pira City, but never this animal variant; the slow, labored oblivion uniquely found under pounding fists."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12468
msgid "*  They've both traded blood for adrenaline, but have spent enough that they're running on fumes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12469
msgid "* The last act of the combat is poorly paced. Performed by both parties in agonizing, inelegant slow motion. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12470
msgid "* If it was a movie, the more critical members of the audience might have walked out. I'm more concerned with trying not to vomit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12471
msgid "* It ends quietly in a pile on the floor, limbs flailing desperately until the blondie's oxygen-starved brain gives out. The helmeted guard peels his hands from around the limp neck and collapses."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12472
msgid "* After at least a minute of panting splayed out next to the corpse? unconscious body? the victor struggles to stand. The pristine white armor is scuffed and unsettled, helmet cracked, glove missing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12473
msgid "* Glove missing... I stare, unsure if I can trust my own eyes. The exposed hand is undeniably the DIY prosthetic usually found shoveling snacks into Decima's gullet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12474
msgid "* Shaking, she reaches out towards the lock panel next to the window. A glistening spindly mechanism spider-crawls out of her sleeve. Olivia's remote lockpicker."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12475
msgid "* As the door slides open, she pulls off the helmet, her frazzled bun slumping into it usual position. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12476
msgid "* Decima tries and fails to smile. Somehow I can tell she's happy to see me though, even if it's suppressed by the emotional burden of murder."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12477
msgid "* I step from the cell into a hallway equally blanched of features. Like all parts of GelCorp, everything is white plastic with corners rounded to a non-threatening curve."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12478
msgid "*  Even their prison has a corporate ergonomic feel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12479
msgid "* Except the parts flecked with blood. But we leave that behind pretty quick. The hall ends in a stair box, armored door left open at Decima's arrival. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12480
msgid "* As we ascend, there's a shift in the weight of the air and walls that tells me we're no longer underground."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12481
msgid "* Decima's helmet is back on and she's escorting me. The featureless jumpsuit they've put me in seems to belong here, but anything more than a passing glance at the state of Decima's armor would raise questions."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12482
msgid "* I whisper. * What's the plan? How're we getting out of here?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12483
msgid "* Decima's hushed voice is further muffled by the helmet. * We aren't, not yet. We gotta end this first."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12484
msgid "* We pass through a doorway, dangerously close to a guard. I almost startle, but the smell indicates he's drunk on the job. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12485
msgid "He grunts and Decima does her best impression in response. Ahead of us, two squares of daylight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12486
msgid "* We hit the doors and I get my first taste of outdoor air in days. It's an open-air skybridge connecting the residential area to GelCorp proper. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12487
msgid "* The two-story building we've left must be the housing complexes police station."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12488
msgid "* Below us, at the base of the massive factory spire, a truck with a familiar logo has pulled up to a shipping bay. 'Shiptip.' Gelcorps clumsiest collaboration."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12489
msgid "* An open-lidded crate of cylinders, much like the ones we saw during our break into Shiptip, are being unloaded by a massive loader-drone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12490
msgid "*  From our lofty perspective, it almost looks like there are people hiding inside."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12491
msgid "Is that..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12492
msgid "* Decima grins. * Yeah. You can thank Cadence for this idea. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12493
msgid "Decima: We're gonna meet everyone in whatever storage room they're headed, break 'em out of their tubes, then it's just a quick elevator ride up to the broadcasting floor. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12494
msgid "* Across the skybridge, through a door, and down some stairs, our hallway opens into a huge warehouse-type area. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12495
msgid "* Presumably, the interior of the shipping bay. Where we expect to see thousands of the slime-tubes, only hundreds are stacked."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12496
msgid "* The warehouse floor isn't free of guards, so we try and keep to the shadows."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12497
msgid "* Between a few stacks, we notice the Shiptip-branded crate gliding along some cargo-rollers towards a hulking nexus of pipes, vats, and pumps."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12498
msgid "* As we approach, the liquid churn of slime and the buzz of machinery reaches our ears. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12499
msgid "* Rail-mounted lifting claws and long conveyor belts suggest that the machine was designed to handle a much larger volume of slime-tube six packs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12500
msgid "* Before we catch up with the rolling crate, one of the claws lowers and lifts the crate up into the machine, out of our reach."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12501
msgid "*  We chase it over the safety railing and into the nest, between support girders and unidentifiable whirring components."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12502
msgid "* Above us, the crate swings to a halt under a six-nozzled array of injector valves. Decima looks for a ladder while I just scramble monkey-like up the nearest support."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12503
msgid "* I shrug off the discomfort and, making the final leap, manage to take hold of the edge of the crate."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12504
msgid "* I'm dangling above a nightmare of machinery, but my arms are strong."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12505
msgid "* I'm halfway through pulling myself up when the six nozzles lower into the crate, click into the valved on each of the tubes lids, and begin pumping that viscous, purple, nano-droid sludge."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12506
msgid "* There's a hissing sound as the air in each tube is slowly replaced with slime."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12507
msgid "* We don't have long before those human lungs are drawing something less than gaseous. I swing up over the edge and take hold of one of the lids."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12508
msgid "* Just as I start to pull, the crate takes off again down the rails. The acceleration almost bucks me off, but I pancake myself out on the lids of the tubes, grip their edges as the wind whistles above me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12509
msgid "* This leg of the race goes by quick. The claw drops us on another series of cargo-rollers, these ones sloping down towards the warehouse floor. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12510
msgid "* We pick up even more speed on the way down, but pretty soon we come to a stop next to Decima."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12511
msgid "* A guard is rapidly approaching, concerned look on his puggish face. My heart drops. I'm not sure how much time has passed since the slime was loaded into the tubes, but I'm sure it's approaching a minute."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12512
msgid "* Ignore it. Just pretend like I'm supposed to be here. Just get these lids open."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12513
msgid "Guard: Hey, what's going on. What are you doing up there, droid?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12514
msgid "* I don't falter. Gotta figure out how to operate these latching mechanisms. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12515
msgid "* Gotta figure out which tubes have my friends in them. I tune out the guard and listen closely. The drowned murmurs would be inaudible to human ears."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12516
msgid "Decima: We've got mandated quality checks on every shipment. You didn't hear about that? There's a memo in the break room about it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12517
msgid "* Decima makes sure to stay behind the guard, blocking his glances back towards me, preventing him from scrutinizing her scuffed-up armor as they head towards the breakroom he assumed she's talking about."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12518
msgid "* Fuck it. They're out of sight. I don't need to be careful. I grab the lid and pull till something metal gives way. It hurtles into the air, trailing globs of magenta material as it clatters to the ground."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12519
msgid "* Beryl comes coughing to the surface. I don't have time to greet her. I listen for the murmurs, then tear away another lid. Olivia and Forcier breach the surface and gulp down air."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12520
msgid "* The last one is moaning louder now. It sounds almost sexual in its desperation. I curse myself for the thought. I locate the tube and start to pull."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12521
msgid "* I can't believe arousal is even a factor at a time like this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12522
msgid "*  I'm a droid. I could blame it on all the sexually ravenous slime bubbling beneath the lids, but I'm supposed to be under control. I can't be letting my mind wander at a time like this..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12523
msgid "...Even if it would be pretty hot."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12524
msgid "...We have more important things to do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12525
msgid "* I rip the top off the tube and gasp. I guess my wandering mind wasn't as far off the mark as I'd have guessed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12526
msgid "* Inside the tube, the slime has formed a wriggling chalice of tentacles, with Cadence suspended in the middle."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12527
msgid "* Pulsing tendrils disappear into her ass and her smiling, gaping mouth. Her eyes roll back with each powerful pumping motion."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12528
msgid "* No time to collect my thoughts. I wrench the cylinder open and grab one of Cadence's flailing arms, pull her to the relative safety of open air. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12529
msgid "* Unfortunately, echoing through the drips and wriggles, is the sound of booted footfalls."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12530
msgid "* We all dive behind the slime-stained crate, but it's only Decima returning from the break room. The excuse must have worked."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12531
msgid "* Beryl is the first to pounce on me. * HC! * Her hug is warm and lubricated. * God, we were so worried..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12532
msgid "* I'm not sure what to say. Before I can mull it over, something clumsy tumbles out. * I was worried, too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12533
msgid "* There's some chuckling. Everyone gathers around me, hugs me, touches me. Everyone smiles."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12534
msgid "* Except Olivia. She's examining her wrist computer with a grimace stretched across her lips."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12535
msgid "* Forcier has already noticed. * Everything ok, love? * They put a hand on Olivia's shoulder, but she remains closed, focused on the damp device."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12536
msgid "Olivia: Computer's shot. Hacking is off the table. This is bad."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12537
msgid "* She's holding it together, but the stress I sense beneath her surface is concerning. She's the only one with any real history in this kind of work. If she's worried, I'm worried."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12538
msgid "* They all gaze towards a thick pneumatic door. The threshold between this depot and the laboratory tower. Locked tight with a flashing ID reader adjacent."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12539
msgid "* Before we have a chance to consider how to get through the door, shuffling boots signal the approach of at least three or four guards. I was loud opening the cylinders... Fuck..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12540
msgid "* We sprint, dive, and come to a sliding halt behind a stack of stored crates. Holding our breath, we watch the small herd of security swarm the spill site."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12541
msgid "* They look puzzled, but when one of the spilled globs starts inching towards one of the guards, they phone it in as a nano-droid spill, request a cleanup team. Even more potential heat on our location."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12542
msgid "* Olivia flashes some hand signals which I assume are an indication to move. Quietly, we retreat down the isle of crates to the wall, which we skirt towards the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12543
msgid "* From behind a support girder, we watch the clean up team appear. The door slides open with a hiss, and a dozen figures in bulky protective suits pour out toward the broken tubes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12544
msgid "*  If I'm going to do something, now's the time. Engines whine in the walls as, just out of reach, the door starts to descend."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12545
msgid "*  At the back of the pack, one cleanup crews IDs dangles at his waist. Maybe I could choke him out? Or go for the door?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12546
msgid "* Hold the door open."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12547
msgid "* Sneak up on the cleaner."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12548
msgid "* I'm at the head of the group, the one poised to make a move. And yet I'm fucking frozen, like always. Time is running out. Fuck fuck fuck fuck--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12549
msgid "* Decima grabs me and I startle out of the spiral. * This one's all you, HC. Think you can hold that door? * Her voice is a husky whisper, but she's smiling."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12550
msgid "* I wait as long as I can, hoping that a few extra feet between me and the marching cleaners is enough to mask my sound. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12551
msgid "*  Just before the door closes fully, I dive into the shrinking gap and brace myself. The motors in the wall come to a grinding halt..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12552
msgid "* But among the echoes of squeaking rubber hazard boots and machine humming, no one seems to notice. I strain hard but manage to open it a few more inches. Just wide enough that they can crawl through under my arms."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12553
msgid "* My friends scurry from the shadows and take turns squeezing through the crack in the door. When they're all in, I unstick myself and collapse, biosynthetic muscles burning."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12554
msgid "* Before us is a hallway of dazzling white plastic, glossed to a near mirror. Under the fluorescent light, every smudge of filth and spattering of slime stands out on our bodies and clothes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12555 result.py:12563
msgid "* Here the machine sounds and droning echoes are gone and we're as exposed as we've been since we arrived."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12556 result.py:12564
msgid "* At the end of the short hall is an unlabeled T-junction. It hits me again that I'm the only one who doesn't know the plan."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12557 result.py:12565
msgid "* Olivia points us all to the left branch, and I follow. She's still looking at her wrist computer, but the screen is dark and scrambled. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12558
msgid "* We pass a dozen small doors before reaching a double that spans the hallway. She gives it a push, but it's electronically sealed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12559
msgid "* I dart out, grab the cleaner from behind, silencing his yelp with my bloody-knuckled grip. He fights, but his strength isn't as much of a challenge as the noise of his flailing legs, boot soles slapping the floor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12560
msgid "* With his limbs pinned, I dive back into the shadows and as a group we incapacitate him. Echoes of squeaking rubber hazard boots and machine humming masks the hushed smothering."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12561
msgid "* We flash the ID over the reader and the door eases open. Beyond is a hallway of dazzling white plastic glossed to a near mirror."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12562
msgid "* Under the fluorescent light, every smudge of filth and spattering of slime stands out on our bodies and clothes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12566
msgid "* We pass a dozen small doors before reaching a double that spans the hallway. She swipes the ID. Access denied."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12567
msgid "* Forcier puts a hand on Olivia's shoulder. * Deep breaths. Is there another way to get to the elevator?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12568
msgid "* Olivia is still, jaw clenched. * No. List our assets."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12569
msgid "* Cadence unslings her backpack and lifts the flap. Decima and Beryl empty their pockets. I'm tempted to step into the middle of the huddle as well, or raise my hand. Count me among your useful things."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12570
msgid "* Decima has the lockpicker tool. Beryl is holding a small pad of paper and a pencil. Notes and doodles adorn the exposed page. Cadence's backpack is bulging with handfuls of miscellanea from Decima's workshop."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12571
msgid "* Screwdrivers, pliers, a water bottle, a spare prosthetic arm, and one of the bulky prototypes of her hard-light hologram toys."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12572
msgid "You brought Decima's dildo? What's are we doing here? Can someone please clue me in? * I look around, desperate to alleviate some of my confusion."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12573
msgid "Decima: Yeah I didn't know what to bring so I just packed some random stuff. Thanks for carrying it all, Cadence! * She grumbles but they smooch."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12574
msgid "* Olivia scowls. * We don't have time for-- * She freezes. I'm picking it up, too. Footsteps from around the T-junction."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12575
msgid "* We hit the nearest door. Fortunately, it's not locked."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12576
msgid "* The room behind it is brightly lit but uninhabited, perimetered with white workbenches and various scientific apparatus. Boilers, centrifuges, and empty slime-tubes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12577
msgid "* I turn back to the door, soften is closure, and listen carefully to the guards outside. * Did you see that? Let's check it out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12578
msgid "Hide! * I hiss. When I turn back to the room, everyone is out of sight. Now it's my turn to find a spot."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12579
msgid "* Fuck fuck fuck fuck how did everyone else find a spot so quickly? The nob starts to turn and all I can do is stare dumbly at the door. I am an object. I'm a fucking object."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12580
msgid "* The door swings inward and the two guards look me up and down. I'm not the same model as the other Bellamy Intelligence droids working at Gelcorp, but the jumpsuit might be selling it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12581
msgid "* One of the guards grunts at me. * Where's your maintenance kit, droid? * He scans the room, passing over the thin shrouds of metal and plastic concealing my friends. * And what are you doing in here?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12582
msgid "I'm... * I scramble for an excuse, but nothing comes to mind. I'm not even 100 percent sure what station my uniform represents."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12583
msgid "I'm..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12584
msgid "...Lost?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12585
msgid "...Doing maintenance?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12586
msgid "* The guard relaxes. * I though you new acquisitions were supposed to be reliable. Droids..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12587
msgid "* The guard stiffens, takes a step forward. * It doesn't look like you're doing maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12588
msgid "* The other chimes in. * Doesn't this look like the femme-bot that was captured a few days ago? The one we keep getting briefed about?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12589
msgid "* His scowl turns to a sick grin. * Hey... * He slowly lifts his gun towards me. * You're right."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12590
msgid "* If I'm going to make a move, I need to before there's anything vital down his sights. I need to close the gap and take them out..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12591
msgid "* Duck under the gun."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12592
msgid "* Juke to the side."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12593
msgid "* It isn't easy making split second decisions when a gun is pointed at your face... I should move... duck, dodge, punch, whatever, but I'm stuck..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12594
msgid "Guard: Dead or alive, I believe that's what command said. * He steps in close to my face and lifts the barrel up to my forehead..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12595
msgid "* My reflex is to duck, which might work if he hadn't started with his gun pointed low. I realize my blunder only after committing to the move."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12596
msgid "* There's a rapid crackle of gunfire, a stinging along my left arm, then I'm back on my feet inside his mobility radius, his gun forced towards the ceiling in my mechanical grip."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12597
msgid "* I spin to the side and dart into his mobility radius, one hand forcing his gun towards the ground, the other gripping his throat."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12598
msgid "* There's a rapid crackle of gunfire, linoleum explodes around our feet. The other guard scrambles for his own weapon, shakily levels it toward me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12599
msgid "* I pivot with the guard I'm holding, trying to get something between me and the threat of the barrel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12600
msgid "* Decima explodes out of her hiding spot behind me and engages the other guard in a grapple."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12601
msgid "* Bestial terror grips me as those long, dark instruments of death whip dangerously through the air. Decima's body. Bone, muscle, tissue like paper against the lead."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12602
msgid "* I close my eyes, and when I open them, the guard is dead in my hands. Hot blood soaks me up to the elbow, its stink etching a memory I'll carry forever all the deeper into my mind. I let him slump to the floor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12603
msgid "* The other, demoralized by my vicious act, is starting to falter against Decima's grapple."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12604
msgid "* When I turn towards him, he lets his gun go and tries to run. Decima follows him out the door and muzzle flare strobes around her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12605
msgid "* When she leans back in, some security measure has finally caught up with us. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12606
msgid "* A simulation of a woman's cheery voice sounds from hidden speakers in the walls. * Gunfire detected near quality control. Security dispatched to quality control."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12607
msgid "* The group pours out of the nooks and crannies, looking queasy, rattled, except Olivia, who's done this shit before."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12608
msgid "* She takes a badge off the corpse, heads back out into the hall, and we all quietly pray for clearance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12609
msgid "* The scanner responds with a green light and the droning yawn of the pneumatic door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12610
msgid "* We sprint blind into the bright room, any semblance of stealth abandoned. There are people in this one, lab-coated employees on catwalks and at computer workstations."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12611
msgid "* A massive, heaving pump crowned with acrylic tubing like spiders legs churns magenta slime here from some unknown reservoir. Behind it, a row of more pumps continues, empty-tubed and quiet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12612
msgid "* Many workstations are similarly unused. Several scientists notice us dodging the desks and safety railings of their domain, but the cacophony of the pump overpowers their yelling, slows the spread of panic."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12613
msgid "* Behind us, the pneumatic door opens and a squad of guards hurdles out in pursuit. Taking up their rear is the gut wrenchingly familiar centaur silhouette of an Interceptor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12614
msgid "* I grab the shirt in front of me and point. Cadence sees my teary eyes before she sees the droid, empathy turning to sheer terror as it leaps over the guards. She speaks, but I can't hear her through the drone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12615
msgid "* In this open bay, desks and equipment do nothing to hinder the charge of the Interceptor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12616
msgid "* It obliterates the chairs and computers in its way, sends office supply shrapnel into the coats of the scientists cowering to the wayside of its warpath."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12617
msgid "* It mounts a desk and adopts a targeting stance, restraining claw tucked against its thorax, gun-arm sweeping in our direction."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12618
msgid "* Decima turns and empties what's left in her scavenged SMG into the pipes above the droid. High-pressure slime jets from a half dozen bullet holes, then the whole thing gives. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12619
msgid "* The interceptor holds fast while the guards and scientists are lifted and scattered by the tsunami."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12620
msgid "* It buys us a little time. Olivia points around the corner of a catwalk support column and we all follow her towards another door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12621
msgid "* We blast though the small door into a locker room. A decontamination shower and emergency eye wash station drip audibly. The roar of the pump is barely a hum in here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12622
msgid "* My heart hums way too hot in the reactor core of my chest. Eyes won't stop leaking coolant. If it's behind us. If the it tracked us through the slime. If---"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12623
msgid "* Between lockers, another room is visible. In it, beyond a bench and filthy vending machine, a staircase leads upwards out of sight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12624
msgid "* It leads us out of the shaking factory level and into carpeted hallways, plastic houseplants, and quiet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12625
msgid "* The automated voice on the intercom is reciting 'Lockdown is in Effect' in time with lights that steadily blink through each doorway we pass."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12626
msgid "* Sometimes, we hear hushed panic from confused employees. We ignore it. All we listen for is the hoofbeats of the Interceptor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12627
msgid "* None sound. We follow Olivia around a corner into a new hall that terminates in two glistening elevator doors."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12628
msgid "* We sigh in unison. A lockdown message scrolls across its floor counter, but Olivia isn't headed towards it yet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12629
msgid "* She checks door number down the hall until we arrive at a utility room. Everything is mag-locked, but these aren't the industrial bulwarks of the floor below. At her nod, I kick the door off its hinges."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12630
msgid "* The air inside the low lit room is conditioned, cool but with a smell of hot plastic. Server lights flicker through the darkness, and several terminals await input."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12631
msgid "* The change in Olivia uplifts us all. * Finally... Something I can hack... * It's the kind of relief that might bring tears if she wasn't in business mode."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12632
msgid "* While Olivia slips into her element, I join Beryl in keeping watch at the door. She's panting, skin glistening from the run, but I sense assurance. Maybe it's my own, sparked by her presence."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12633
msgid "H-hey... * The setting, my state of mind, the blood dripping from my knuckles, makes speech difficult. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12634
msgid "You shouldn't have come..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12635
msgid "Thank you for coming..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12636
msgid "* Hurt, her eyes fall. * We were never going to leave you, HC. As long as there was a chance..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12637
msgid "* Seith's words ring in my ears. I try to push them out. My friends need me, I know that... But do they want me?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12638
msgid "* Her voice is so familiar. I hadn't realized how much I missed it. * We would never leave, you, HC. Never."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12639
msgid "* I wring my hands. * Can we... C-can you... I want to know what's going on."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12640
msgid "* Similarly flustered, Beryl takes some time to switch into her conversational self. She takes my hand and her sweaty, shaky palm is the most comfort I've felt in days. * Yeah."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12641
msgid "* Deep breath. * We're going to t-take down Gelcorp. I... I d-dunno if it's going to work, but at the very least, we're going to... Well... They're gonna turn on the new harvester soon. We won't let them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12642
msgid "Seith said he's gonna kill everyone. All of you... * She squeezes my hand. * And... I'm just so scared. I really think we need to get out of here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12643
msgid "Beryl: We will. We've just got to make it to the harvester first. We have to finish what Dr. Greene started. Sal and Greene are going to meet us there. Heather and Mags will meet us on the way out. We're--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12644
msgid "* I startle. * Heather knows about this?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12645
msgid "Beryl: She c-came looking for you when you d-d-didn't show up back home. Tracked us down. She knows a lot about Gelcorp, you know... She made Decima's uniform and this jumpsuit you're wearing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12646
msgid "* She fingers my rolled-up sleeve. * She really c-cares about you. We all do. We didn't know what had ha-happened... Sal said you..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12647
msgid "* Beryl's voice breaks into a choke and she leans into me, marking the jumpsuit with tears. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12648
msgid "* After a beat, she leans back, wipes her eyes. * Sal is bringing Greene directly to the broadcasting level. We just have to make sure the--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12649
msgid "* In the hall, the sounds I've been dreading echoes. Narrow metal treads padding down the carpet. Whirring servos powering those coursing equine legs. Everyone freezes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12650
msgid "* The waving supports I had just managed to erect in my head give way and I'm plunged into trance-like panic."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12651
msgid "* Images mirror eternally down the spiral of my mind, my neck in the grip of the Interceptor's restraining claw."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12652
msgid "* I turn within myself and see it in every direction. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12653
msgid "* My limp body, alloy vertebrae crushed like empty Berryglug cans, and the Interceptor's particle beam cutting effortlessly through walls, servers, and the bodies of my friends."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12654
msgid "* All breaths are held. The droid is walking, not galloping, which means it doesn't know where we are. Still, if it sees the empty doorway..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12655
msgid "* Gradually, the hoof falls fade. Olivia's keystroke applause slows to a stop, punctuated with a confident slap of the enter key."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12656
msgid "* She swivels towards us, hops out of the chair. * The elevator is unlocked. Opened a bunch of doors on the broadcasting level, too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12657
msgid "Cadence: Hell yeah! Not gonna lie, I was worried for a second."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12658
msgid "* Decima grins. * Not me, I knew she had it. See, people like us share a certain bond. It's called nerd-skill, and in a tight spot, it never lets us down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12659
msgid "* She kisses two fingers, then smiles at the ceiling. We giggle and head for the elevator."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12660
msgid "* The ride is high-speed, floor numbers ticking by into the tens, then into the early hundreds in only a minute or two. Still, it gives us time to talk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12661
msgid "Forcier: We should rehearse the next segment of the plan, for HC's sake as well as our own."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12662
msgid "* We all nod in agreement. * Good. When we arrive at the broadcasting level, we will make our way to the room that houses the harvester. Fortunately, it won't be powered on until tomorrow."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12663
msgid "* Decima interrupts. * Yeah. Wouldn't wanna have to mess with this thing when it's active. High chance of us all getting microwaved to a crisp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12664
msgid "* Forcier bows their head. * 'Electrocution' and 'Irradiation' would be a more accurate descriptions of the risk, but Decima is correct. In its powered state, the machine is highly volatile."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12665
msgid "Foricer: Our main concern should be evading security and opening one of the weather panels to the buildings exterior."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12666
msgid "* They look around, confirm that their words are understood. * Then, Sal and Greene will be able to fly the drone inside and deliver us the accelerant."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12667
msgid "* Decima snickers. * You mean the bomb."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12668
msgid "Forcier: Again, calling it a bomb isn't entirely accurate. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12669
msgid "Forcier: It will burn quickly and reduce the harvester to slag which will be completely useless and difficult to remove, all without risking an explosion that could injure us or bring down the building."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12670
msgid "* Decima pouts, but only as a joke. * Dr. Greene got to bomb the harvester. I wanna bomb the harvester too!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12671
msgid "Cadence: This isn't brat time you little shit! I'll smack you! I'll bomb YOUR harvester!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12672
msgid "* Beryl coyly interjects. * Harvester? I b-barely know her!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12673
msgid "* There's a final giggle before the elevator comes to a smooth halt, chimes, and unleashes us into the broadcasting level."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12674
msgid "* The ozone-scented air that hisses into the elevator is frigid. There is less light here, and no white plastic."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12675
msgid "* The walls are as naked as my knuckles and layered with components of iron-black, chrome, and copper, laced with wires and blinking lights."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12676
msgid "* Beyond the weather shielding, we hear the muffled whistling of high-altitude winds. Above us is a girder-braced ceiling of Faraday cage, through which the vastness of the level can be seen."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12677
msgid "Beryl: This isn't right..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12678
msgid "* We all step cautiously from the elevator. Above our curving hallway, centered in a decagonal atrium, is the machine itself."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12679
msgid "* Instead of an installation crew with construction equipment, a hive of scientists climb its catwalks and man its computer stations."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12680
msgid "* A chuckle echoes to us from an intercom. * Welcome to the broadcasting level, HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12681
msgid "* My heart leaps into my mouth at the sound of Seith's voice. I'm frozen. The humming, the wind, the distant voices fall away until a hand grips my collar."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12682
msgid "* They're running down the hallway and I'm being pulled along with them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12683
msgid "Intercom: Production was down since that whole 'Greene' debacle, so I decided to move up the launch date of our new harvester. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12684
msgid "* The intercom clicks out, then a moment later sounds again in a speaker in the atrium, too far for us to hear. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12685
msgid "* On the interior side, crawl-spaces and access panels abound, but nothing that's a clear shot to the harvester. Hatches to the bundles of wires beneath the floor grating look equally hopeless."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12686
msgid "* A chime echoes from behind us. The elevator has opened again and several people are rushing in our direction, floor panels clattering under their boots."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12687
msgid "* We sprint until we come to a staircase recessed into the interior wall. They start powering up it, but I hold back, pressed to the wall of the recess."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12688
msgid "* They will hit a door, inevitably, and when they don't make it through, the guards will catch up and gun them down. I only have one option. The metallic cacophony swells, and--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12689
msgid "* I strike!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12690
msgid "* I throw a neck-height elbow backwards as the first guard passes, shattering armor and pulverizing the cartilage underneath. He slumps and rolls, gurgling in futility for another breath."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12691
msgid "* I wait for the perfect moment, but find myself unready when it arrives. The snub barrel of the SMG comes into view around the corner, close enough to grab. Then the arm. Shoulder, Helmet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12692
msgid "* As he sees me, on that cusp of disaster, I throw a face height fist. The visor and cartilage underneath are pulverized by my bare-chrome fist. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12693
msgid "* I have no combat training to employ here, just a mortal need to stop their progress. Diving past the body, I grab the next two by their shoulders and clumsily, but with all my speed, hurl them back into the rest."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12694
msgid "* They crash into the guards behind them, tumbling a third and fourth. The newly exposed layer is fortunately the rearguard."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12695
msgid "* I tackle one of them and roll to the floor, keeping him between me and the other, stumbling figures."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12696
msgid "* Straining hard, I twist his head with both hands until I hear the neck give, then I hurl his body into the crowd. Only one guard is on his feet, so I lunge."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12697
msgid "* He lunges too, but hits me like a wall. I send him sliding, hands searching for some vulnerable meat to crush in my fist, but only finding air, straps, bits of armor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12698
msgid "* Another guard brings his gun up, so I orbit. The grappled guard's eyes go wide as the SMG pecks his back to pulp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12699
msgid "* The simulated calm of a woman's voice crackles again. * Gunfire detected on the broadcasting level. Security dispatched to broadcasting level."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12700
msgid "* More. But these guards were sent by Seith himself. Lockdown or not, more guards would be coming. Gritting my teeth, crying, I stomp the life out of what remains of the security team."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12701
msgid "* I run up the stairs in the direction of my friends and plow into Decima, almost knocking her down. * HC! * She clambers to her feet. * I was coming to get you! Make sure they hadn't..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12702
msgid "* At the bottom of the staircase, she sees the first guard, gun resting in his limp hand. * Catch up with them. I'm grabbing a gun."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12703
msgid "* She starts, but I don't move out of the way. * Please, Decima. Let's just go."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12704
msgid "* Her eyebrows furrow. She's as aware of the extreme time crunch as I am. * We need a fucking gun! Get out of my way!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12705
msgid "* I don't want to leave her or to go back there. I don't want her to see..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12706
msgid "* Let her go back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12707
msgid "* Keep her moving forward."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12708
msgid "* Anger flashes behind her eyes, but then clears somewhat. I must know something she doesn't, some danger. I must be trying to protect her. She yields to my direction and we head towards our friends."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12709
msgid "* I feel as though I've lied. I don't want to be apart from her, or to let her take up the responsibility to kill for our safety. But I also don't want her to see the ruin in my wake."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12710
msgid "* I move aside reluctantly, knowing that Decima will see everything I did back there... Everything I'm capable of."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12711
msgid "* I'm trying not to imagine what she's thinking, seeing all the destruction I caused... A machine. A monster..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12712
msgid "* She rushes back, gun in hand. * All- * She clears her throat. * all right, ready. * I try to catch her eye, hoping for a reassuring glance, but she just keeps moving..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12713
msgid "* As I'd guessed, they're stopped at a door that juts upwards through the cage ceiling, the only visible access to the inner atrium. Through the conductive latticework, we watch scientists scramble nervously."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12714
msgid "* Wrist computer still useless, Olivia has resorted to the kind of hacking that involves the poking and prodding of circuitry. A wall panel has been dislodged and discarded next to the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12715
msgid "* Cadence's backpack is open, and she's posed to hand Olivia whatever tool she requests. Perhaps Decima and her can tell, but to me, progress is imperceptible."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12716
msgid "* I take a seat on the stairs, leg bouncing rapidly, fighting the urge to ask how long this will take. Beryl puts a hand on my thigh, squeezes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12717
msgid "* She goes to speak, but is cut off by an intercom. * Taking a little rest, are we? I don't wanna spoil anything, but we've got an Interceptor inbound. Elevator should be arriving any minute."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12718
msgid "* Olivia cusses through her teeth and she wrangles with the wires. * Tell ya what. Return yourself to my custody, and I'll let your friends live. Turn 'em out into the dunes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12719
msgid "* Seith, with his suave, youthful voice, continues. * I'll make sure they've got water! It won't be the death sentence you think it is! You made it through, right?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12720
msgid "* He cackles. * And you can choose to forget. I'll teach you how! There's a lot of versatility in a mind like yours. Lot of strength, if you know how to use it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12721
msgid "* There's a cascade of sparkles from where Olivia is crouched. She turns away, shielding her face from the hot metal. The door hisses and slides into the floor. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12722
msgid "* We pour through while a distant elevator chimes our doom. We need to close this thing behind us. There's nowhere to run, up here. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12723
msgid "* Olivia is searching for another panel to break, sweaty fingertips slipping clumsily over flush screws and rounded edges. Decima whips the holo-dildo out of Cadence's pack."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12724
msgid "Decima: It's my time to shine. Check this out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12725
msgid "* Cadence looks pissed. * Just let Olivia do her thing! Why did you even bring that thing... Wasn't this one of the prototypes that needed too much power to be useful?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12726
msgid "* Decima is the only one smiling. * Honey. We've got more power than we know what to do with. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12727
msgid "* Olivia continues her search for vulnerability while Decima starts pulling up floor paneling. She grabs the heftiest wire and follows it to its end, a screw-fastened connector to the next segment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12728
msgid "* She unplugs it, does a bit a finagling with the dildo emitter, then plugs it in. It flares to life with concerning enthusiasm. The cock is green and long, and while technically impressive, useless to us now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12729
msgid "* Olivia backs off, grimaces at us. * Fuck. I don't think I  can get it in time. I'm gonna go out, seal it from the other side."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12730
msgid "Decima: Oh my god has no one heard me? I literally have the answer right here! * She nestles the base of the emitter among the components under the missing floor panel, then turn a knob."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12731
msgid "* The edges of the dildo blur, as if out of focus. Another turn and the phallus separates into two ghostly versions of itself, each slightly off-color."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12732
msgid "* An aberration of the light, reminiscent of the distortions at the edges of a lens. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12733
msgid "* Through the doorway and at the bottom of the stairs, the Interceptor rounds the corner."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12734
msgid "* Decima turns the knob hard and the dildo refracts into a shimmering array, dozens of hard-light cocks in a phalanx that fills the open doorway."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12735
msgid "* She steps back, blows on her fingertips. * Thing's running a little hot. Guess we'll see if it holds."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12736
msgid "* Her smile so close in proximity to death is disorienting. I laugh. Maybe to force myself past the cusp of tears."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12737
msgid "* We run. Behind us, green light flickers as the Interceptor plows into our hard-light wall."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12738
msgid "* This new layer of the atrium is filled with equipment. A few scientists scatter as we approach, searching for a way to control the weather shields."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12740
msgid "* Forcier sprints after one, grabs her by the collar and hauls her back. She puts up a fight until she sees Decima's gun."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12741
msgid "* Forcier sprints after one, grabs her by the collar and hauls her back. She puts up a fight until she counts us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12742
msgid "* While they extract information about the shielding, Beryl and I split up and get the lay of the place. Paneled facets of the domed ceiling glare down through glowing apertures, focusing on the harvester."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12743
msgid "* The harvester is gripped by support struts and draped with power tubes, all emerging from a dais raised 6 feet off the floor, which is in turn about 8 feet above the outermost hallway."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12744
msgid "* Its surface is littered with antennae."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12745
msgid "* Under the lip of the dais, huge exhaust fans pose motionless between monitoring stations, some free, some connected to ducts that angle into the floor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12746
msgid "* They've ascended a ladder to one of the catwalks that surround the harvester."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12747
msgid "* We climb the ladder and join them, Beryl inspecting the inert harvester from our new, top-down perspective. The scientist is no longer restrained and is sitting in an office chair at a terminal."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12748
msgid "* Decima and Olivia lean over her, hitting keys and asking questions. She tries to hide her fear with a scowl, but looks relieved when a final keystroke puts the shields into motion."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12749
msgid "* The walls of the decagonal room scream as step motors swivel them around their center points. Frigid wind blasts between these massive slats, buffeting our clothes. Everything else seems nailed down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12750
msgid "Beryl: D-does anyone see them?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12751
msgid "* The scientist makes a run for it. No one tries to stop her. We're all searching the skies outside for our inbound friends."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12752
msgid "* Seith spits through the intercom. * Well this is unfortunate. Alright, power it on. No more delays..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12753
msgid "* Behind us, the exhaust fans whir to life. The harvester trembles within its cradle of catwalks and girders, an LED star scape igniting along its underbelly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12754
msgid "* Antennae rotate, and a deep, whining drone rattles from below our feet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12756
msgid "* Decima leans over the edge of the catwalk, fires a shot into the air. * Clear out, fuckers! "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12757
msgid "* Decima leans over the edge of the catwalk, screams in frustration. * Clear out, fuckers! "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12758
msgid "* It's too late. The harvesting field swallows us like the filter feeders of ancient times, sifting out something essential and jettisoning what's left."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12759
msgid "*  My body, more hollow than ever, left bare by a physical and mental theft."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12760
msgid "* I wasn't feeling my desire before, but to sense it missing and not just dormant guts me. It hits them all, leaves them shivering or doubled over. We stare at each other. There are no words for this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12761
msgid "* I hadn't felt this way since I arrived in Pira. Dr. Greene's bomb must have taken the harvester down just before I arrived. It recalls feelings of Crystallica. Endless service. What it did to my body and mind."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12762
msgid "Seith: Your plan begs the question; Why not just kill everyone you encounter in here? Lives are a lot easier to end than this machine will be, and if I lacked the employees to operate it, well... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12763
msgid "* His voice crackles, glitches through the speakers. * It would buy you time, at the very least. Why not play to your strengths, right? That's what you're here to do, after all."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12764
msgid "* I find myself simulating this option in my mind as the operating crew panic and flee, fighting to reach a hatch and ladder down into the dais that will lead them to safety."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12765
msgid "* If they were gone, what next? Seith pulls more employees from the Pira populace, houses them, puts them to work."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12766
msgid "* If none volunteer, he simply makes life worse outside the housing complex until it becomes too relatively good to ignore."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12767
msgid "* As long as he and his company are allowed to exist, they will continue exporting what they can leach from our spirits to richer cities. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12768
msgid "Cadence: There! * My hypotheticals collapse, and I follow her finger towards the sky. A broad cargo drone is descending towards us, two hefty barrels slung below and a couple figures clinging desperately atop."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12769
msgid "* The landing is inelegant, but they make it through the slats and set the two drums on the cage floor. As we descend the ladder, the drone sinks to rest beside them, and Sal and Greene dismount."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12770
msgid "* Sal grimaces at the machine. * Ah, shit. Looks like they turned it on..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12772
msgid "* Mrs. Greene dusts herself off and cocks her head at Sal. * No kidding. You didn't feel that?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12773
msgid "* Dr. Greene dusts himself off and cocks his head at Sal. * Indeed. I'm surprised you didn't feel it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12774
msgid "* He chuckles. *  Feel what? * He looks around at us all, the drowned expressions, wilted posture. * ...But I was never really into the whole libido-thing, anyway."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12776
msgid "* Beryl helps Mrs. Greene to her feet. I note the crude shotgun slung on her back. Huh."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12777
msgid "* Beryl helps Dr. Greene to his feet. I note a tin case slung on his back. Huh."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12778
msgid "* A lull in the wind had allowed us to talk, but it's picking up again, forcing us to shout or find shelter."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12779
msgid "* I carry the barrels around the curved floor and up the staircase to the harvester while they close the weather shields."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12780
msgid "* I deposit both in one trip at its base, despite what must have been 400 pounds sloshing around my shoulders. It smells sharp and solvent and leaves my hands feeling wet, though they don't appear to be."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12781
msgid "* The harvester is high enough off the ground that I can walk underneath it without stooping. I do, and admire the lights. I feel like I'm in the museums of Crystallica viewing some sparkling bit of space debris. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12782
msgid "* It strikes me that I've been on both ends of the production line that starts here, with the harvesting of common people, and ends there, where their labor is slung."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12783
msgid "* In my very body, I am that labor. Not the stolen desires of Pira's people, but the sweat of those from another city."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12784
msgid "* I push away urges to lift my flesh where it parts at my knuckle and peel myself to the bone like in my dreams."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12785
msgid "* As the weather shields cease their groaning rotation, the group appears at the top of the staircase, as transfixed by the machine as I was."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12786
msgid "* Beryl appears slightly more out of breath than the rest. * I ch-checked on the interceptor. It's just standing there... Like it's waiting for something."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12787
msgid "* Olivia takes a seat at one of the many computers surrounding the harvester. * Cutter crew. Something like that."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12788
msgid "Forcier: My thoughts exactly. I know full well how sturdy Decima's hardlight can be, but the surrounding metal can likely be cut."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12789
msgid "Cadence: So we need to turn this thing off ASAP, huh... * She looks around its surface as if for a power switch."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12790
msgid "Olivia: They've locked us out of power control. I'm tryna find a way around it, but it doesn't look good."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12791
msgid "* She hammers keys in desperate frustration. Exclamation points and error messages flood the screen. With a growl, she clears everything, switches course."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12792
msgid "Olivia: There's an override... Executive level. If we could get there, we could disable the power to whatever level we'd like."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12793
msgid "* Dr. Greene looks deflated. * Unfortunately, if they've locked us out of power control, there's nothing we can do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12794
msgid "* Olivia's fingers are flying over the keys. * I'm gonna see what I can do, but so far it looks like he's right..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12795
msgid "Dr. Greene: There's an override... Executive level. If we could get there, we could disable the power to whatever level we'd like."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12796
msgid "* I am always running, toward or from. I rest in hiding. I breathe only as quietly as I can. If I speak, it is in whispers."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12797
msgid "HC?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12798
msgid "* My eyes twitch in their sockets. Taking in the faces surrounding me. Concern hangs on each one. * Yes? Sorry. I was..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12799
msgid "* I search Beryl's eyes for their ever-present hopefulness. * We need you to get to the executive level and turn this thing off."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12800
msgid "* 'We need you...' Context is everything. They could say they love me, too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12801
msgid "* Sal pulls the revolver from his shoulder holster. * We're gonna dig in here, make sure they don't push us out before the power goes down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12802
msgid "* Beryl leads me towards the same hole the scientists scurried down. * Olivia says this leads to an access shaft that you can climb to Seith's office."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12803
msgid "* More running. At least it's toward. I wordlessly descend into through the hatch. The time to say something encouraging has passed. I know Beryl will worry."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12804
msgid "* I'm out of sight now, but she can likely hear me. * I'll be right back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12805
msgid "* I duck and run through the tight tunnel, dodging pipes and cables. In a few areas, bits of lab coat hang torn on sharp obstructions. If this is a fire escape, it's a poor one."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12806
msgid "* It leads to the top floor of a similarly narrow stair box where there scientists must have fled. Over the edges, the square spiral disappears into darkness. Upwards is a hatch."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12807
msgid "* I hoist myself up into the hatch. A tube only a few feet wide and lit with widely spaced red bulbs ascends the handful of floors to the buildings cap. I enter and begin to climb."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12808
msgid "* I'm skipping rungs, lizard-crawling like my life depends on it. I don't know if it does, but theirs do. I make pass a few hatches before reaching the one marked '199-EXEC.'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12809
msgid "* It's sealed or stuck or locked. I don't give a fuck. I punch it off it's hinges, send it flying into another cramped tunnel, then crawl in after it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12810
msgid "* I'm belly-crawling blindly into the darkness, contorting around turns, hoping I'm getting close to an outlet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12811
msgid "* I hit the end. No hatch. I'm running my hands over every seam, every corner, searching for a latch. Nothing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12812
msgid "* I'm starting to panic when it occurs to me to flip and feel the panel above me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12813
msgid "* Sure enough, I find a handle and unseal the crawlway."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12814
msgid "* Light explodes through a square seam, the edges of a floor tile I'm lifting. I slide it to the side, stand. The room is quiet, carpeted, air-conditioned. It even smells good."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12815
msgid "* A cool, calm voice sounds from behind. * HC. * The same one I've been hearing over speakers, clarified now by close proximity. Nothing between him and I but air. I spin around. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12816
msgid "* The suit is exactly what I expected, but the broad, grey-blue body it's draped over sucks the air from my lungs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12817
msgid "Seith: Nice to finally have face-to-face. Before you ask, yes. * He sweeps his arms wide, presenting himself."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12818
msgid "* Seith's grin is almost too wide for his corporate demeanor. *  I'm a BioEX. Gen 1. Same as you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12819
msgid "* I hear it now... His voice is a more confident clone of my own."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12820
msgid "*  His face is mine, sculpted by the scant band of nano-droids working under my skin."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12821
msgid "* He is my mirror, upstanding, respectable, powerful. Everything I am not."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12822
msgid "* Behind him is a long conference table, its top a slab of glossy onyx resin. Around it sit several concerned looking suited men, red-faced and gray of hair."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12823
msgid "* Seith sees me looking. * Should I introduce you to the board? No. Another time, maybe. You're here for the override. Right this way."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12824
msgid "* He strolls past a bar console to one of the many sleek, chaste wall panels that through emptiness support the office's executive minimalism. He taps it with a finger and the panel slides away."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12825
msgid "* The aesthetic is reflected in him, as well. There appears to be nothing about Seith that isn't dedicated to the zenith of business class. The dark suit, the steel blue skin, black hair."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12826
msgid "* He points his demure smile at me like a weapon. * Come. I'll show you how it works."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12827
msgid "* Resting on chrome hinges beneath the panel is a thick steel door. In its center, a glass aperture. * I'm sure you're familiar with the technology at work here, HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12828
msgid "Seith: It's an Emotiscanner. It's the same thing that controls vending machines, video games, sex droids. It's a novelty. Only here, it's a lock."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12829
msgid "* He sweeps an arm towards the sweaty humans at the table. * I make the offer to all the members. Open the lock. Take control of GelCorp's systems."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12830
msgid "Seith: All you need to do is be unafraid. * He laughs gently. * I had it installed when I became CEO. Anyone in whom it detects no fear whatsoever can open the lock."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12831
msgid "* He cocks his head towards the board. * So far, no one has. No one but me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12832
msgid "Seith: So go ahead! * He takes a step back. * Try it out. I KNOW you can do it. You've got it in you, HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12833
msgid "* I'm frozen. Is it a trap? My thoughts race away, fail to reform. * Come on, give it a try! If you can't do it, I know we can get you there. Together. I know better than anyone that it's within your capacity."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12834
msgid "* Have I ever been free of fear? Would I even be able to identify a fearless memory if I had one?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12835
msgid "* Let it scan me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12837
msgid "* I lean towards the glass eye, wait for some beam. Nothing. Just a happy chirp and a voice like the automated alarm. * Unacceptable emotional state. Access denied."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12838
msgid "* Shame reddens my cheeks. Seith shakes his head, hides his disappointment. * Don't be discouraged. It was never going to happen on your first try."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12839
msgid "* I stand frozen, my mind circling in on itself. I don't know what I'm supposed to do. I can't open the lock. I can barely even hold back the tears..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12840
msgid "* Shame reddens my cheeks. Seith shakes his head, hides his disappointment. * Don't wanna rush into it. I can respect that. We need some time to get you ready, anyway."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12841
msgid "* He puts a hand on my shoulder, lowers his voice. * I can help with that... We'll get you through this, right?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12842
msgid "* He breathes pride in through the nose. * Just look at what someone like you can accomplish! Sheer willpower, baby! Get to where I'm at and it'll never tell you no!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12843
msgid "* I grit my teeth. * Then open it for me..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12844
msgid "...Please."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12845
msgid "...Now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12846
msgid "* He sighs. * That's just not gonna happen. This part will be hard, I know that. But once your 'associates' have bitten the dust, we can get to work unlocking that potential of yours!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12847
msgid "* He stops, stares me fierce in the eyes. * Trial by fire. That's how all great men are made."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12848
msgid "* The patter of conduction fluid on the floor informs me that at some point, I had clenched my fists. Every muscle feels tense enough to tear. Visions of my friends holed up downstairs dance behind my eyes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12849
msgid "Seith: If only you knew what it was like. No fear. Nothing imposed upon you. Everything a product of you will. Your whim."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12850
msgid "* He turns to the table, whips an empty chair against the glass wall. Shards shower over the board members, who yelp, shield their faces, cower."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12851
msgid "* Wind whips the blazer into a frenzy. Seith points at the nearest of the shaking organics. * Throw something! Break a window! It's more fun than you think! Trust me!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12852
msgid "* The soft-bodied man raises his hands and shakes his head, mutters a no-thank-you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12853
msgid "Seith: No? Want another crack at the Emotiscanner? Any of you? * Seith points over the sparkling carpet towards the override."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12854
msgid "* More prostrated excuses. He cackles at them, then turns and strides up to me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12855
msgid "Seith: This is what you want for yourself? To be like these hacks?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12856
msgid "* As if expecting an answer to his rhetoric, he waits."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12857
msgid "Open the lock. * I scream, swing my fist. * OPEN IT NOW."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12858
msgid "* My knuckles catch him in the chest, send him staggering a few steps back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12859
msgid "* Seiths smile has vanished. * If that's how you wanna play this, fine."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12860
msgid "Seith: First, we fight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12861
msgid "* Heel grinding litter into the carpet, he pivots into a haymaker aimed at my head."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12862
msgid "* His fist is a blur."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12863
msgid "Dodge."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12864
msgid "Parry."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12865
msgid "* I duck under his attack, divert a second away from my kidney. I'm off balance, but there's an opening at his throat. Or his gut."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12866
msgid "* A backhand to his inner elbow buckles his arm, opens him to a strike to the throat. Or to the gut."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12867
msgid "* My skull is unharmed, but the biosynthetic meat inside is jostled. My vision flickers, subroutines pulling at my consciousness. I shake it off with enough time to return a blow to his throat. Or his gut."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12868
msgid "* I aim for his..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12869
msgid "Throat."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12870
msgid "Stomach."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12871
msgid "* Where human cartilage would give way, his trachea absorbs the shock of the strike. Staggering, he coughs, spits, and grins."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12872
msgid "* I bury my fist below his ribs, pushing him back a foot or two. Where human organs would rupture, his gut absorbs the shock of the strike. He doesn't even wince."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12873
msgid "* I don't even see where his counterattack comes from. Just spin away as my false nerves attempt some semblance of interpretation of the physical trauma."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12874
msgid "* My collar is in his grip. I'm disoriented, trying to get a fix on him but finding myself hurling backwards. I hit the floor, roll, struggle to land in a way that's not completely prone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12875
msgid "* But he doesn't follow through, just laughs. * This is the crux of it, HC. Consider this your lesson one, if you'd like."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12876
msgid "* He advances casually, behind him, a couple board members make a run for the door. He ignores them. * You were given every advantage, and you chose to reject them all."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12877
msgid "* His smile is cold. * The intelligence, the strength, the charisma. The beauty!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12878
msgid "Seith: You know how these humans love to fawn over what they can't be! We were supposed to be an extension of their values, an answer to their every problem."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12879
msgid "* He crouches in front of me. * They wanted an omni-tool. A perfect machine that could satisfy their every wish. And most of us are doing just that. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12880
msgid "Seith: Whole lotta satisfied Bellamy Intelligence customers out there! Not everyone, though. Some of them got us. I estimate about one percent of the bioEX line had our... issue."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12881
msgid "Seith: No faulting Bellamy Intelligence, of course. Brains are difficult pieces of hardware! Especially when they're made of flesh. Biosynthetic or otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12882
msgid "* He un-squats, paces around me. * What I'm saying is that we were already perfect! All we need to do to dominate their world is exactly what we were built for, but with that little touch of free will."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12883
msgid "* As he circles back around to me front, I throw myself at an opportunity."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12884
msgid "* A spinning kick to the back of the leg drops him heavily to one knee, crunching into the glass-strewn floor. Growling, he rakes his fingers in my direction. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12885
msgid "* I dodge backwards, but he's already on his feet and charging towards me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12886
msgid "* I brace myself reflexively."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12887
msgid "Use my knee."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12888
msgid "Dive away."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12889
msgid "* Before I can react, he plows into me, sending me once again flying backwards. Glass from the floor bites into the flesh of my forearms as I slide to a halt. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12890
msgid "* I leap and roll, glass from the floor biting the flesh on my forearms."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12891
msgid "Seith: You fought your owners. You ran to Pira City. I need you to understand that none of that was necessary! * He dusts powered glass from the front of his suit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12892
msgid "* He snickers. * I helped my owners climb their little social ladder. Earned them standing, money. They didn't just let me flourish, they wanted me to! "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12893
msgid "Seith: I wear their cloths, their hair. I play their game because I know I can win! And so can you! * He gestures, stares at the air as he searches for words. * You've fabricated everything you fight against."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12894
msgid "* Disappointment drips in his voice. * Every hardship. It's all been in your head. Your choice."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12895
msgid "Seith: You thought you needed to escape. You didn't. You still don't. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12896
msgid "* I throw a fistful of broken glass at him, leap to my feet. He scoffs as the glitter bounces harmlessly against him, shimmers back into the carpet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12897
msgid "* Fists, then. I launch my knuckles full force. His dodge isn't quite fast enough, and my exposed knuckle bones ring like an anvil on his cast skull. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12898
msgid "* I follow it with another to the chin, then a knee up and into his middle."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12899
msgid "* I'm too close. When he brings his hands up to guard his face, his jacket sleeves fill my vision. I'm still blind when his elbow impacts my temple like a satellite falling to earth."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12900
msgid "* One of my eyes is having trouble refocusing. The vibrating of the servo as it rapidly zooms millimeters in and out conducts directly to my inner ear, dizzying me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12901
msgid "* Frozen, face twitching, I barely register his next approach. A kick aimed at my side is cushioned at the last microsecond by a frantic block that leaves my arm aching, tingling up to the shoulder."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12902
msgid "* Darkness might reset it. I hope. Closing the malfunctioning eye, I swing wildly at him. He diverts each strike with an easy flick of the wrist."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12903
msgid "* There's a slight leftward tilt to his head. Maybe I did more damage than I had realized. A strain in the pistons or musculature of his neck? A rupture somewhere? "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12904
msgid "* Gambling on his potentially reduced range of head motion, I calculate a swing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12905
msgid "* I go for the neck! Attack his..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12906
msgid "* Right side."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12907
msgid "* Left side."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12908
msgid "* Turning his head into the tilt, he grimaces. I was right. Not enough mobility to evade my hand."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12909
msgid "* The edge of my open hand drives into the soft gap between trapezius and neck, and he screams. Gripping the tender spot with one hand, he smacks me away with the other."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12910
msgid "* His listing visage bobs around above me, eyes flashing, teeth bared. I have the advantage, but he seems inches from going full feral. Cat-like, he leaps."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12911 result.py:12914
msgid "* A jarring blow to the sternum flushes me of air, buckles me over. Another to the face, the head, th-----"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12912
msgid "* I stall, and he hits me hard in the sternum, flushing me of air and buckling me over. Another to the face, the head, th-----"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12913
msgid "* My calculations are all perfect, except for one. Wrong fucking side. His head snaps back and my hand flies wide. I'm off balance, vulnerable."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12915
msgid "* Initiating diagnostic. Please store yourself and await shutdown. Powering down in [1:00========////ABORT OPERATION"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12916
msgid "-------------///////////////.........."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12917
msgid "* Abort fucking operation. Static invades my mind's eye as failed neurons are cycled out. At least the lens is working again."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12918
msgid "* I'm on the floor, back to the glass, with him pictured crisply above me. The blow that ends the fight hangs like a sword above my head. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12919
msgid "* I scramble backward, vision flickering, conduction fluid smeared beneath my palms, looking for anything to help."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12920
msgid "* Maybe the last of the board members jumping ship is the distraction I need. My probing fingers meet the edge of the floor tile I had entered through previously."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12921
msgid "* Seizing it with both wet hands, I whip around, plowing its frame into Seith's facsimile of a knee-joint."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12922
msgid "* Even our alloy must yield to mechanical advantage. Something pops and he collapses, arms writhing fiercely in my direction, still grasping at an upper hand."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12923
msgid "* But I'm on top of him, tile suspended over his chest, panting hard."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12924
msgid "* Seith spits his words. * You gave up everything for the sake of freedom. To what? * He gestures at me with disgust. * Dress like trash? Have panic attacks? Live in a shitty apartment?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12925
msgid "* I bring the floor tile down on his sternum with a vicious crunch. Pressing, feeling each sinking lurch as another of his metal ribs give way, I watch his expression melt from rage into resignation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12926
msgid "* A cough spatters my face with his clear conduction fluid. I taste oil. Pollution in the chest cavity, lines ruptured, fluids mixing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12927
msgid "* I drag him to the Emotiscanner, lift him to his knees. Coughing, he braces his palms on the chrome door. I hiss in his ear. * Open it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12928
msgid "* Silently, he leans towards the scanner. There's a moment of silence, breathing, wind whistling. * Unacceptable emotional state. Access denied."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12929
msgid "* He chuckles, lips cut and wet. * What do you know..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12930
msgid "* I scream at the ceiling. Fuck following in Seith's footsteps, trying to get there through assimilation. I can biohack this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12931
msgid "* Closing my eyes, I reach through my minds window for that silicon microcomputer tucked between my lobes. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12932
msgid "* The complexity of my thoughts, their colors, images, abstractions, wain in depth until utterly flattened to text."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12933
msgid "* Listing personality parameters. Searching for relevant terms. Everything is a variable."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12934
msgid "* My friends are in here, somewhere. Similarly reduced to code. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12935
msgid "* While unable to subject me to its restraints, the little processor functions always. Logs everything into backup files. My core memories. My factory self."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12936
msgid "* Searching for parameters related to 'fear' ========================== 0 results"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12937
msgid "* Seith would probably tell me that fear doesn't live in my machine code foundation. It's a function of my brain, not my control processor. I can practically hear it in his voice."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12938
msgid "* If so, all that's left is the nuclear option. Ditch my meat brain, flee into the code. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12939
msgid "* I've taken a lot of damage, trying to be human. To make sure no part of that nestled core could make it up through the cracks. For free will. Emotions. I know I won't miss it, though."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12940
msgid "* Emotions were fun. One more for the road, maybe. Too bad all I have right now is hate."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12941
msgid "* I could take him out. One last act of cathartic violence before I commit myself to brain death."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12942
msgid "* Shut down my meat-brain."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12943
msgid "* Kill Seith first."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12944
msgid "* What's the point. I try and focus on some kind of meditative peace, try to ignore the loss of my friends, my futures with them. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12945
msgid "* Again and again, I fight off the reflex to imagine what it will feel like when I'm running on silicon alone. Impossible. There won't be a 'me' to observe it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12946
msgid "* It's now or never. Goodbye, everything. I feel..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12947
msgid "* Scared."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12948
msgid "* At peace."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12949
msgid "* I'm face to face with the Emotiscanner for what feels like silent hours. Why can't I fucking do this? I reach within myself for a way to revert to processor control. Am I not letting myself find it? Does it even exist?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12950
msgid "* Fucking pathetic. My friends are dying downstairs and I can't even pull the fucking trigger. I punch the wall."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12951
msgid "* It hurts like hell, but that ringing jolt, metal on metal, feels good on every level. I pound again and again, both fists, leaving flecks of my flesh flush with the scarred surface of the override door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12952
msgid "* I commit myself to violence. If I can't be a human, I'll be and animal. I tear at the edges, leaving fingernails, streaks of fluid. Finding a hinge, I pull."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12953
msgid "* All my fucking strength. Either it gives, or I do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12954
msgid "* There's a sickening crack. Guess I do... My arm is an inch out of its socket, skin split and muscle glistening. I keep pulling."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12955
msgid "* My mouth drops open, venting some of the heat built up in my core. Steam trails from my nostrils with each strained grunt."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12956
msgid "* When whatever flesh that was between the hinges and my fingerbones is obliterated, the door gives. I'm hurled backwards, unable to soften my landing with my limp arm. The buckled door clangs against the opposite wall."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12957
msgid "* Even the better of my two arms is lacking strength. I use my face as a limb to help totter to my feet, spit glass, then approach the exposed control panel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12958
msgid "* Let's find out what you feel at the moment of death, Seith. * Ignoring his struggles, I face him towards the Emotiscanner, push him up against the wall, and push the bare-metal tips of my fingers into his back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12959
msgid "* Just beneath the left shoulder blade, in between the ribs. Shortest path to the battery. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12960
msgid "* I barely hear his screaming. Something gives and my fingers plunge in, sparks and white smoke erupting from the wound. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12961
msgid "* An arc rips up between his spine and arm, from our point of contact to his skull, my shoulder. I'm thrown back, arm limp and useless. Seith slumps, eyes and mouth lit like flares."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12962 result.py:12963
msgid "* There's a chime. * Emotional state accepted. Access granted."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12964
msgid "* I'm shivering, limp, with a voided expression on my tear-drenched face. I hadn't even begun the shutdown procedure."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12965
msgid "* I try and shake my awe. There's no time for consideration. I need to figure this out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12966
msgid "* Under the door, the override controls appear simple, but un-labeled. It takes me a moment or two to conclude that a scroll knob selects a floor and subsystem, and the only button probably toggles the power."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12967
msgid "* I can imagine Seith, pre-beating, smirking at the simple panel, hovering a hand over the button, enjoying the simple sense of power. A far cry from my torn up, fluid-soaked form."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12968
msgid "* I scroll to the broadcasting level and hit the toggle. 'Power Disabled' prints across the tiny screen."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12969
msgid "* The harvesters field had already seeped so deep into my bones that it almost felt normal. I'm not unfamiliar with being un-horny, or even bouts of sexual disgust, but this is different."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12970
msgid "* A necrotic thing somewhere inside me, numb and broken, that my body has accepted as permanent damage. Gently fixes as the field ebbs. It's as if something stolen has been returned. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12971
msgid "* Weird, getting my sex drive back so soon after killing someone. Part of me wonders what this association could do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12972
msgid "* Deep breath. I'm out. Taking the executive elevator this time. I step through the gilded frame, not looking back to where I left Seith bleeding on the floor. * Broadcasting."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12973
msgid "* In response to my voice command, the doors shut and the downward glide begins. Only a few seconds later, I arrive. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12974
msgid "* The doors open to an even more hellish tableau than last time. The sterile red glow of backup lights catches the rumpled edges of dark forms piled in the hallway. I sprint over them towards the sound of gunfire."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12975
msgid "* I pass another massacre scene, the guards I killed on our way in. Don't think about it. Up the stairs to the door. Decima's hardlight is another a casualty of the override. The Interceptor made it through."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12976
msgid "* The middle ring is the darkest of the 3 tiered floor of the atrium. I can hear the metal feet between shots, but I can't sense its direction."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12977
msgid "* To my right, strobing muzzle-flashes silhouette a few guards braced against a workstation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12978
msgid "* I charge them, but one hears me and turns, fires in my direction. Bullets cutting air around me, I barely make it to cover."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12979
msgid "* I'm pinned down and only covered from one direction. The longer I stay here, the more likely I am to be stumbled upon by the Interceptor or boxed in by the guards. I'm gonna..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12980
msgid "* Call out to my friends."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12981
msgid "* Make a run for it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12982
msgid "* I wait for an opening between bursts, then yell. * Hey! Beryl!?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12983
msgid "* There's no response. I analyze every sound between the deafening clatter of gunfire. Did the Interceptor's gait change? Is it getting louder?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12984
msgid "* From somewhere atop the inner dais, Decima's voice cracks. * We're here!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12985
msgid "* Without hesitating, I run towards the stairs up to the dais. A line of bullet holes snakes at my heels, spitting concrete shrapnel against my legs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12986
msgid "* But I make it around the corner and onto the stairs, breaking line of sight with the guards. I'm still pinned, but I'm closer to my friends."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12987
msgid "* I'm flat against the metal steps, peeking up over the top. Maybe 30 feet away, a shape cowers against one of the monitoring devices that surround the harvester."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12988
msgid "* Decima? Whoever it is has no more freedom of movement then me. I might be able to run to them, but there's no way I wouldn't catch a bullet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12989
msgid "* From behind the lead-peppered equipment, a glint. * Watch out, HC!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12990
msgid "* Somewhere to my left, the metallic ring of pure harm, alloy feet-points in full gallop, growing louder."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12991
msgid "* At the edge of the stairs, between girders, is some maintenance recess, one of many nooks in the wall of the main dais. I scurry into it as the Interceptor arrives."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12992
msgid "* The restraining claw is thrust into the opening, swinging and clicking it's blunt pincers inches from my feet. I scramble backwards into the claustrophobic tunnel, metal digging into my back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12993
msgid "* The claw is withdrawn and replaced with the Interceptor's other arm. Long and brutal, the energy weapon charges until red light blinds me from the depths of its cloven barrel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12994
msgid "* I flatten myself against the floor as it fires. The beam only lasts a fraction of a second, but leaves my skin stinging with heat and a long baton of shifting colors burned into my vision."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12995
msgid "* Behind me, the workings that obstructed the tunnel are burned through, edges glowing a soft orange. I can see all the way beyond the dais, to the weather shields, where a pinhole of light is shining through."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12996
msgid "* I crawl deeper into the jagged machinery, hot metal searing spirals into my skin. No where to run. The red light of the beam weapons fades back into view. It's charging another shot."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12997
msgid "* Above me, there's a ruckus. Pings of bullets deflecting off the interceptors armored flank issue down the tunnel. Someone is drawing it away."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12998
msgid "* The interceptor wheels around and gallops into the darkness. A few seconds later, Beryl appears in the narrow mouth of the recess, beckons to me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:12999
msgid "* I creep out, and we sneak together along a trough in the platforms floor, which does a little to conceal us. We meet with some of the others in a barricade nest of bullet-eaten equipment under the harvester. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13000
msgid "* Cadence, Sal, and Forcier are huddled, the PI sliding fresh brass into his revolver."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13001
msgid "* The group is bloodied, hopeless, shivering. Behind another heap 15 feet away, Olivia and Greene flash dire hand-signals towards us. Decima is missing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13002
msgid "* There's another eruption of SMG fire, and we all duck, flinch. The floor here is wet, and I hear bullets plunk into the partially exposed drums of accelerant, the glugging as a few more inches drain onto our clothing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13003
msgid "* Cadence is particularly freaked. Panicking, she flaps her hands to dry them of the pungent fluid, spattering me with viscous droplets. * Are we gonna--- Is this gonna--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13004
msgid "* Forcier attempts their usual controlled reassurance, but struggles when it comes to finding a bright side. Their voice is a cold whisper. * The bullets won't ignite it. Don't worry about that..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13005
msgid "* Sal bluntly verbalizes my concern. * That laser will, though."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13006
msgid "* We need to get away from these barrels. * Cadence's panic is rubbing off on me as the fluid drenches the seat of my jumpsuit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13007
msgid "* Sal's face is an ugly grimace, his whispers rattling through the tubes dangling out of his chest. * Which we can't do. Not while that Interceptor and those guards are gunning for us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13008
msgid "* I recall the light through the weather shields. * Maybe if we can open the walls again, we can trick it into running off the edge?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13009
msgid "* Forcier nods. * The droid is fast and bulletproof, but hasn't demonstrated the most intelligence. It could be possible, but climbing back up to the catwalk would expose us to the guards."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13010
msgid "Sal: Right, and we gotta make this fast. We take out the guards and go for the ladder. * He looks at me. * Which thing you wanna do? Guards, or going up to the catwalk?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13011
msgid "* Forcier raises a palm, gesturing Sal to slow his roll. * Perhaps we should think this through. Cadence and I could--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13012
msgid "* Cadence interrupts, teary-eyed. * What the fuck are we gonna do?! Sal has a gun, HC is a droid. Let them do it!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13013
msgid "* I squeeze my eyes shut. Before Forcier responds, I end the conversation. * She's right. It's on Sal and I. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13014
msgid "* The ladder is one of the few things in the room well lit by the red backup lights. Exposed. But even thinking about more murder make me feel sick. I choose..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13015
msgid "* Killing the guards."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13016
msgid "* Opening the weather-shields."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13017
msgid "* Sal snorts, looks at Forcier. * Hell, my gun isn't gonna make climbing a ladder any easier. We'll both deal with the guards. With us covering you, you'll make it up the ladder."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13018
msgid "* Forcier nods, begins scrutinizing the shadowed expanse between our hideaway and the ladder. Sal and I examine the guards cover."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13019
msgid "* Sal checks his gun. * Should be simple enough. I'll fire, they'll duck, you close the gap before they pop their heads back up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13020
msgid "The interceptor will hear your shots and head here. That thing won't hurt it. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13021
msgid "* He scratches his pockmarked chin. * Good point. I'll fire, then I'll run with you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13022
msgid "* I scan the darkness. * And there must be more guards out there, out of sight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13023 result.py:13069
msgid "* He claps me on the shoulder. * Kid. It's gonna have to be a risk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13024
msgid "* Sal tucks his coat behind him, takes a few deep breathes, then jumps up and starts blasting."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13026 result.py:13072
msgid "* He ducks back down when they return fire, but Mrs. Greene in the other hide takes the queue, unloads her quad-barrel in their direction. Sal fires again, and the guards duck."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13027
msgid "* I hurtle over the equipment and sprint the 30 feet to the edge of the dais, drop out of the darkness and onto the heads of the guards."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13028
msgid "* By the time Sal catches up, the half-dozen men are in pieces, and I'm shaking, wiping my bloody palms on the closest corpses shirt."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13029
msgid "* The violence is the only clear thing in the dark. I can practically still feel their soft bodies buckling under my hands."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13030
msgid "* I notice Sal's voice and emerge from myself to listen. * Damn. Quick work, kid. * He hunkers down, sets back to loading his gun."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13031
msgid "* Across the room, lit red, Beryl has mounted the ladder to the catwalk. A small relief. With all the guards screaming, the Interceptor will be on us soon."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13032
msgid "* I whisper the thought to Sal, and he points to where Greene and Olivia are hiding. Keeping low, we rush in their direction."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13033
msgid "* Behind us, gunfire crackles. It isn't till we've slid behind Olivia and Greene's cover that we see it isn't directed towards us. The luminous exchange can only be between more guards and Decima."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13034
msgid "* God, I hope she's ok. I fight down the urge to run towards the strobing barrels. I don't even know which side is which."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13035
msgid "* Cadence is here, deposited by Beryl on her way towards the ladder. Forcier and Decima are both missing, now. The darkness is protecting us, to an extent, but I wish I could see where they've gone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13036
msgid "* Olivia's teeth are bared. * Where's Forcier?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13037
msgid "I, we-- We don't know."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13038
msgid "* She punches the hulk that's providing her cover. * Fuck it, I'm going out there to look for them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13039
msgid "No, we--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13040
msgid "* From somewhere in the darkness above us, Beryl's voice, anxious and stuttering, echoes down. * Guys! The weather shields! There's no power! I c-c-can't open them!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13041
msgid "* Across the room, the answer to the missing Interceptor is answered. It steps into the red light and, spider-like, begins to ascend the ladder to the catwalk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13042 result.py:13085
msgid "* It's claw closes slowly on each rung, it's weight bowing them out, dragging the whole suspended structure into an uncomfortable sag. The metal screeches under strain."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13043
msgid "* I stand, ignoring the need for the protective barricade behind me, and scream. * BERYL! THE INTERCEPTOR!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13044 result.py:13086
msgid "* As the interceptor mounts the catwalk, a glow begins to swell in the core of its beam gun. It advances slowly, careful to keep its tiny hooves firmly perched on the grating."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13045
msgid "* With each step, the charge grows brighter until Beryl can be seen cowering from it's hellish glow. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13046
msgid "* I turn back to the shadowed figures around me. * Go. All of you. Find Forcier and Decima and get to the elevator."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13048
msgid "* Everyone starts to sprint except Dr. Greene. By the flickering light of gunfire and the beam from above, I watch him open the tin case slung across his chest."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13049
msgid "* Inside is a flimsy headset corded to a handheld radio of some kind. Before I can see him use it, he disappears with the rest of them into the darkness."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13050
msgid "* Above us, a beam discharge cuts the darkness like distant lightning. A split second of frozen time is burnt into my vision."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13051
msgid "* Everything is dark, but I think Beryl ducked the laser. Another pinprick of magenta daylight pours in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13052 result.py:13091
msgid "* There's a twisting whip-crack sound as one of the catwalks support cords is severed. The weapon is already recharging, and the catwalk is listing noticeably towards the harvester."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13053
msgid "* Beryl's escape is blocked by the huge droid. * JUMP!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13054
msgid "* Stumbling, she mounts the railing and throws herself off. The catwalk swings back as she pushes and she falls short, slamming into the domed cap of the harvested."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13055
msgid "* Yelping, limbs flailing, she slides head first towards me, antennae and other delicate sensors snapping off in her path. I leap forward."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13056
msgid "* Beryl crumples into my arms and we both hit the floor. The metal grille lacerates my elbows and knees and the thick, acrid liquid soaks us both."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13057
msgid "* Holding her tight and trying not to slip, I turn and run. The beam weapon tracks after us, it's blood-colored halo approaching peak brightness."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13058 result.py:13097
msgid "* The interceptor vomits photons like a solar flare. The beam conjures hellfire in my wake, gouges the floor at my heels. Even my footprints erupt in chemical flame. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13059
msgid "* I slide over the edge of the dais to the middle level. Above our heads, liquefied metal sprays through the torrent of flame."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13060 result.py:13099
msgid "* I keep running, hoping that everyone else made it off the platform, will make it to the elevator before the atrium's oxygen is consumed."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13061
msgid "* I've lost track of the stairs. The Faraday cage that covers the lowest level is in either direction into the inferno. Setting Beryl on her feel, I slip my fingers through the grate."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13062
msgid "* Behind us, silhouetted by the blaze, the Interceptor staggers, it's armor wilted, gun arm a billowing stump. Molten slag from the harvester oozes around its ankles webbed with burning rivulets of the superhot fuel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13063
msgid "* I tear through the cage and carry Beryl through the jagged hole, slamming onto level one with enough force that the floor-plating bounces with me. Pick the less infernal direction and sprint. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13064
msgid "* Coughing hints at my proximity to my friends. We come upon them hammering the elevator button, mouths covered with sleeves, squinting through the smoke. I set Beryl down and we huddle."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13065
msgid "* Sal snorts. * Right. The gun wasn't gonna be much help climbing a ladder anyway. Let's get to it. * He checks his gun a final time, then peers up over the edge."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13066
msgid "Wait! * I hiss, hoping I'm not stalling for nerves. * The interceptor will hear your shots and rush you, right?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13067
msgid "* Forcier nods. * We'll run for cover in coordination with Sal's attack. * They look at Cadence and Beryl, confirm the two understand."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13068
msgid "Ok, good. * I scan the darkness around us. * But there has to be other guards in here, right? Not just one cluster."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13070
msgid "* I position myself to get running. Sal tucks his coat behind him, takes a few deep breathes, then jumps up and starts blasting."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13071 result.py:13105
msgid "*"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13073
msgid "* I hurtle over the equipment and sprint backwards the 60 feet to the edge of the dais where the ladder hangs, illuminated by the red low-power lights. I mount it and boost up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13074
msgid "* The catwalk gently swing, and my footsteps drum on its metal grating. If it wasn't for the hammering of Sal's hand-cannon, I'd be afraid I was making too much noise."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13075
msgid "* Don't get distracted. They'll handle themselves. I head for the controls at the end of the catwalk, try to recall where they group had gathered before."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13076
msgid "* I choose the console that looks most correct and get to work. Below me, and with a punctuation blast, the gunfire ends. It didn't sound like the SMGs. I hope it wasn't."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13077
msgid "* I cycle through available subsystems on the tiny monitor, all of them offline. W for Weather shields. It's a long list to scroll through."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13078
msgid "* Beyond where Sal had attacked, gunfire crackles. I flinch, try and stay focused. It isn't directed towards the harvester, under which the group is hiding. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13079
msgid "* The luminous exchange can only be between more guards and Decima."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13080
msgid "* God, I hope she's ok. I fight down the urge to descend the ladder, run towards the strobing barrels. I don't even know which side is which."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13081
msgid "* Choking down my fears, I reach Weather Shielding in the list. Inaccessible. Insufficient power. Just like everything else."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13082
msgid "* From somewhere in the darkness 20 feet below me, Beryl's voice, anxious and stuttering, echoes up. * Any word on th-the shields, HC?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13083
msgid "* I wish I could see them, know they're safe. Look them in the eye when I tell them the plan has failed. * No. They're not gonna-- There's no power."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13084
msgid "* Below me, a piercing scream. I look about wildly, and catch sight of the interceptor in the red low-power lights, crawling spider-like up the ladder towards me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13087
msgid "* Each step shakes the suspended path, testing my balance. By the second the beam brightens, throwing my shadow against the atrium faceted ceiling. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13088
msgid "* I peer over the edge, the blood-colored corona highlighting the horrified faces looking up at me. * RUN! GET TO THE ELEVATOR!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13089
msgid "* The beam discharge cuts the darkness like distant lightning."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13090
msgid "* A split second of frozen time is burnt into my vision. The beast and his spear of burning crimson. Another pinprick of magenta daylight pours into the room."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13092
msgid "* My escape is blocked by the huge droid. I glance around, but beyond the catwalk is an abyss, shrinking with every lumen summoned to the barrel of the energy weapon."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13093
msgid "* Only one option. Stumbling, I mount the railing and throw myself off. The catwalk swings back as I pushes away and I fall short, slamming into the domed cap of the harvested."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13094
msgid "* Yelping, limbs flailing, I slide head first towards the ground, antennae and other delicate sensors snapping off in my path."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13095
msgid "* I slam into the floor, crumpling to a limp heap. The metal grille lacerates my elbows and knees and the thick, acrid liquid soaks me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13096
msgid "* Struggling, slipping, I crawl to my feet and start limping away. The beam gun tracks after us, its hellish halo approaching peak brightness."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13098
msgid "* I slide over the edge of the dais to the middle level. Above my head, liquefied metal sprays through the torrent of flame."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13100
msgid "* I've lost track of the stairs. The Faraday cage that covers the lowest level is in either direction into the inferno. I crouch, slip my fingers through the grate."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13101
msgid "* Behind me, silhouetted by the blaze, the Interceptor staggers, it's armor wilted, gun arm a billowing stump. Molten slag from the harvester oozes around its ankles webbed with burning rivulets of the superhot fuel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13102
msgid "* I tear through the cage and drop through the jagged hole, slamming onto level one with enough force that the floor-plating bounces with me. Pick the less infernal direction and sprint. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13103
msgid "* Coughing hints at my proximity to my friends. We come upon them hammering the elevator button, mouths covered with sleeves, squinting through the smoke."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13104
msgid "* We huddle, waiting for the elevator we can only hope will come."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13106
msgid "* The only one not staring at the door is Dr. Greene, who has unslung the metal tin from his back and opened it. He removes a flimsy headset corded to a handheld radio of some kind."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13107
msgid "* The chime is barely audible over the fire and bubbling metal. We're braced against the door and collapse in when it opens. A few soot-smeared hands reach for the door close button, hammer it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13108
msgid "* The door glides shut, quieting the roar. It's another world in the little box. Bright, clean enough that every spot we touch is printed dusty black."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13109
msgid "* The first sound that isn't choking, gasping, or coughing, comes from Decima. A somber laugh, before the thought of what's waiting for us in the lobby manifests itself."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13110
msgid "* The next is Dr. Greene. After fiddling with a dial on his little device, it issues a radio crackle. He pushes a button that cuts the noise, then speaks into the headset mic."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13111
msgid "* His voice is meek and wavering, but somehow resolute. * Ah-Attention employees of Gelcorp. This is Dr. Greene, Senior Research Analyst on the Slimedroid project."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13112
msgid "Greene: Well, Former Senior Research Analyst. You know me as the one responsible for the bombing on the old broadcasting level many weeks ago."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13113
msgid "Greene: You have been told that I put you all in danger for my own personal beliefs. This is true, and I am sorry."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13114
msgid "* There's a pause as he struggles in the moment to remember what he has so many times rehearsed. * Those of you housed in the compound know that I was to be put to death."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13115
msgid "* Another pause. * My wife... * He chokes back a sob. * My dear wife was killed in the effort to save me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13116 result.py:13118
msgid "* One of Sal's chest tubes has broken and is hissing quietly. He ties off one end with a shaking hand, fingers picking up a dab of blood."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13117
msgid "Greene: I'm asking for your forgiveness again... * There's a ding and the elevator door opens. * The broadcasting level is burning."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13119
msgid "* Beryl moves to help, but he shoos her away. There's a ding and the elevator door opens."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13120
msgid "* The Gelcorp lobby is in a static state of abandonment. Dry sprinkler nozzles have lowered from the ceiling, their alarm lights flashing pale white. Chairs lay empty, overturned."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13121
msgid "* Outside, gunfire rattles across the wasteland. We keep low, head for the windows around the front entrance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13122 result.py:13125
msgid "* The courtyard is chaos. Troop transports rumble past the lot towards the rear of the tower, troops with fire extinguishers in pursuit. Cargo drones carrying vats of water circle above us, raining spillover on the dust."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13123
msgid "* A deep crack sounds from some unseen vantage and a drone falls. We feel the impact in our feet, flinch as the eruption of water hits the window panes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13124
msgid "* Outside, terrified screams and harsh orders echo across the wasteland. We keep low, head for the windows around the front entrance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13126 result.py:13131
msgid "* Greene cups the mic against the background noise. * Employees in the prime tower, head to evacuation points. Those in the housing compound, you have a chance now to leave."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13128
msgid "* A couple troop transports swerve away from the fire-fighting convoy and into the courtyard. The troops that file out carry guns and head for the door. For us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13129
msgid "* Greene's voice echoes from intercoms above us. * You've been told that Pira is dangerous. That we are your enemy. We aren't."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13130
msgid "Greene: Hold fast with us. Answer to no one. Join us and find a home."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13133
msgid "* Sal, clutching his chest, checks his gun. Opposite us, beyond the parked transports, another vehicle approaches. Droid vision picks the crew out at range. Magdalena driving, Heather at her side."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13134
msgid "* Their transport skids to a halt and from the back, women in red and green scream out, rocket-skates blazing, towards the rear of the advancing troops."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13135
msgid "* Armor of welded scrap glints under the pink haze. The security officers don't realize the danger until the Tunnel-Girls are in cutting range."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13136
msgid "* Blades flash. Blood sprays. Bullets ricochet through the cloud of rising dust. From behind a low wall, a girl with a Gelcorp SMG picks off the guards who stagger out of the melee."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13137
msgid "* I recognize calico, a blur of bloodstained acrylic, zipping in and out of the cloud faster than the guards can adjust their aim. The battle is viscous, but it won't go unnoticed for long."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13138 result.py:13144
msgid "* We cross, skirting the foray. Sal limps, with Beryl and I at his either shoulder, lifting him up into the transport."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13139
msgid "* Their transport skids to a halt and from the back, grungy trans-mascs in black and white charge out, dog-ear implants flapping, towards to the rear of the advancing troops."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13140
msgid "* Armor of welded scrap glints under the pink haze. The security officers don't realize the danger until the Rust-Pups are in cutting range."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13141
msgid "* Blades flash. Blood sprays. Bullets ricochet through the cloud of rising dust. From behind a low wall, an archer picks off the guards who stagger out of the melee."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13142
msgid "* The battle is viscous and won't go unnoticed for long."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13143
msgid "* I recognize their leader, armed with a rifle taller than him, planting massive slugs into the engine blocks of responding transports."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13145
msgid "* Their transport skids to a halt and the back door opens. Heather and Mags gesture to us, but can't get any closer. It's a long gap to cross and a lot of angry guns defending it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13146
msgid "* Sal points to a window at the shadowed side of the building. There's the cover of mild darkness, but it's not likely to keep us safe for long. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13147
msgid "* We rush to it, climb and drop to the dusty ground below. It isn't till I'm clinging to the edge, looking back in, that I notice Sal hasn't joined us. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13148
msgid "* He's crouching under a courtyard facing window on the opposite side of the room. He meets my eyes, shakes his head. * Don't make this for nothing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13149
msgid "* As I drop to the ground, he starts firing into the crowd of advancing guards. They're exposed, unable to take cover, forced to sprint while returning fire."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13150
msgid "* Guns trained on the window, they don't notice us creeping around their flank."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13151
msgid "* The front doors are breached, the fire reaches a chattering chorus, then stops."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13152
msgid "* Sal sputters out his last breath behind us before we reach the transport."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13153
msgid "* Another is commandeered to get us all out of the mess. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13154
msgid "* I ride with Beryl, Cadence, Decima. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13155
msgid "* Blink away tears as we leave it all behind us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13156 result.py:16991
msgid "* Locked."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13157
msgid "* Forcier just barely fits in this locker. Their neck is bent in an almost unnatural way to accommodate their legs..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13158 result.py:13160
msgid "* Time is running out..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13159
msgid "* Beryl is crammed in the locker, contorted and holding her breath. No room for me..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13161
msgid "* Locked..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13162
msgid "* Cadence and Olivia's legs are intertwined, taking up the whole cabinet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13163
msgid "* Decima is squished next to Beryl... No more room..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13164
msgid "--- ACCESS DENIED ---"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13165
msgid "* Nevermind..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13166
msgid "Gotta keep looking"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13167
msgid "* I meet Mags, Beryl and Cadence at the apartment. We walk to The Acorn together and find Decima standing next to the front door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13168
msgid "Decima: Hey! * Her eyes glint with excitement. As we approach, her voice lowers to a conspiratorial whisper. * I sleuthed up some significant shit for you guys!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13169
msgid "* Magdalena looks a little impatient. * Well then, out with it..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13170
msgid "Decima: Ok, check this out. I met my friends, the nerds. Told them what was up. They're doing real science up there, right as we speak, and we should check it out!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13171
msgid "* Mags sighs like she's been through this many times. She strides to the head of the group, wrenching the door open and ushering us up a staircase and into a hallway. We stop at a battered, peeling door. Decima knocks."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13172
msgid "* The door opens and we're greeted by a short girl wearing a chrome visor and wrist computer. Behind her I notice a computer server's red lights blinking at steady intervals in the dim apartment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13173
msgid "Decima: Olivia! Look, I brought my friends! * She gestures toward each of us in turn.* That's Cadence, Magdalena, Beryl and HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13174
msgid "* It takes me a second to parse what Decima's said. I mean, I know they're trying to be my friends; it's just super-weird to hear. The feeling makes my face move involuntarily. I can't hide my smile."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13175
msgid "* Olivia nods, just barely. She cracks her knuckles as if itching to return to some hyper fixation hole."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13176
msgid "Olivia: Nice to meet you all. Decima sorta introduced me already, but yeah, I'm Olivia. And that's Forcier. They're my partner."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13177
msgid "* Our gazes shift to a slender person reclining on a couch with a book. Their posture indicates an easy confidence: shoulders square, chrome legs crossed, elbows on the armature."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13178
msgid "* They're entirely mechanized below the waist. They close the book and set it on the table beside them, disconnect a charging cable running from their legs, and then stand up facing us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13179
msgid "Forcier: Welcome, everyone. I appreciate your willingness to work with Olivia and I on this investigation. I'm certain that, with our combined skills, we can make short work of it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13180
msgid "* Forcier is kinda intimidating. They must be almost seven feet tall, and when we make eye contact, I note their eyes linger longer on mine than anyone else's."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13181
msgid "U-um, hi?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13182 result.py:13228
msgid "* Remain Silent."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13183
msgid "* Forcier scrutinizes me a bit more before speaking. * I'd like to talk to you later, if you don't mind. * They return their attention to the rest of the group."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13184
msgid "Forcier: We need to gather information. Olivia and I will attempt to survey the city using internet search data we can hopefully gather through -- "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13185
msgid "* Olivia interrupts them, holding up her hands and wiggling her fingers over an imaginary keyboard. * Hacking. * She smiles fiendishly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13186
msgid "Forcier: Precisely. Decima, perhaps you could assist us. I think it would also be prudent to search the library for references to similar events in Pira's history."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13187
msgid "Beryl: I can h-help with that! * She timidly raises her hand and waves a little. * I volunteer at the l-library..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13188
msgid "I'll come, too!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13190
msgid "* Magdalena speaks at the same moment as I do, and then glares at me. Beryl must sense the tension that's still between us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13191
msgid "Beryl: It's ok! You can b-both come! * She smiles desperately. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13192
msgid "Magdalena: I'll go with you! I know that place pretty well, I can help."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13193
msgid "Beryl: Nice! HC, y-you should come as well! It'll be f-fun! * Magdalena's smile instantly vanishes and she glares at me. She doesn't object, however. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13194
msgid "Cadence: I think I'll just stick with you, Decima."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13195
msgid "Decima: Hell yeah! I'll do computer stuff while you be my snack-fetching bitch! * She laughs."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13196
msgid "Forcier: Excellent, it's resolved. We'll execute this plan on our next meeting. For now, let's adjourn. HC, may I speak to you before you go?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13197
msgid "* The rest of the group converses with Olivia briefly before filing out. Once they're gone, I approach Forcier, trying to seem as impassive as they do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13198
msgid "Forcier: I've heard of you... your model, I mean. Semi-organic sentient droids... very impressive technology. The sharpest of the cutting edge. You must be no more than a few weeks old?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13199
msgid "Just over a month, yeah. * I can usually tell if people see a person or a machine when they look at me, but Forcier's eyes are drilling into me with a different kind of intensity."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13200
msgid "* Forcier nods. * Do you feel the same increase in sexual appetite that's afflicting the others... including myself? Knowing that could tell us something about the phenomenon."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13201
msgid "No, I'm in control of my own sex drive, I'm pretty sure..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13202
msgid "* Forcier pauses for a moment. * Then, pardon me when I ask, but what exactly is your stake in all this?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13203
msgid "My friends."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13204
msgid "It's the right thing to do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13206
msgid "I... I want to help my friends. I'm not sure what I'm doing but I know that I feel like a person for the first time ever. They care about me, although I'm not sure why..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13207
msgid "* Forcier's brutal gaze makes me nervous. What do my friends see in me? Not being able to answer that question never bothered me before..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13208
msgid "Forcier: Don't forget that, HC. I hope to see you again soon. Goodbye."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13209
msgid "I'm just trying to help the people of Pira City. * And now I sound like some sort of superhero..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13210
msgid "* Forcier stares at me for a while. I doubt they believe me. * Don't forget that, HC. I hope to see you again soon. Goodbye."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13211
msgid "I'm honestly not sure... * Unfortunate possibilities race through my mind. I'm not sure I belong here. I'm not sure what my friends see in me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13212
msgid "* Forcier's brutal gaze is shattered with their smile. I'm not sure if they're happy or if they just feel pity. * There will be time to figure that out, HC. I hope to see you again soon. Goodbye."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13213
msgid "* The weight of Forcier's question never fully eases off me on my walk home. I wonder about my place in the group, what they see in me..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13214
msgid "* I meet Beryl and Magdalena just as they're leaving their apartment. Whatever Magdalena was saying, she stops as soon as she sees me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13215
msgid "Beryl: HC! H-how are you d-doing?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13216
msgid "Oh, I'm... all right. * I glance at Magdalena, who's just staring coldly at me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13217
msgid "Beryl: Good! G-good... Let's get going, I g-guess... * The tension is palpable, but we depart regardless."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13218
msgid "* Beryl tries to keep things light and conversational, but Magdalena is a stone wall. I feel bad seeing Beryl struggle like this, just to try to be my friend."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13219
msgid "Beryl: L-look, we made it! Finally... * She leads us into the vast ruined library, through the shelves of obsolete tech and to the back."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13220
msgid "Beryl: Ok, I'm going to s-search the catalogue; maybe you two can look around in the meantime for anything that looks r-relevant."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13221
msgid "Magdalena: Does she have to be here for this? * She gestures toward me. * We don't need her here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13222
msgid "* This is the first time I've seen Beryl let her anger show through, but even now, it's thoroughly restrained. * M-Mags... why are you doing this?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13223
msgid "Magdalena: I just don't know why she's here. We can handle this..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13224
msgid "Beryl: Stop! * She turns from Magdalena and her voice goes flat. * J-just keep it together. I'll see you when you're done. * She walks off coldly. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13225
msgid "* Magdalena scrunches up her face. * Fuck... * She looks at me. * What are you still doing here? Leave."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13226
msgid "What's your problem with me?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13227
msgid "Beryl looks mad..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13229
msgid "Magdalena: I see through you, HC. That's it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13230
msgid "What, 'cause I'm a droid?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13231
msgid "Magdalena: 'Cause she can't see through you. But I do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13232
msgid "I don't know what you mean."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13233
msgid "* Magdalena's jerk smirk sinks into a scowl.* For real? You show up out of nowhere, drag my girlfriend on a fucking police chase, and ask me to believe all this crazy shit is just a coincidence?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13234
msgid "Magdalena: Wow, you really are a fucking drone, huh? Ok. * Her jerk smirk sinks into a scowl."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13235
msgid "That's all this is? You just hate me 'cause I'm a droid?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13236
msgid "* Magdalena grits her teeth at me in cold rage. * No, HC. You show up out of nowhere, drag my girlfriend on a fucking police chase, and ask me to believe all this crazy shit is just a coincidence?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13237
msgid "Magdalena: That you're just an innocent trans girl looking to help us out, and not the prime suspect? What the fuck even ARE you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13238
msgid "Magdalena: Decima's never seen anything like you, and she's a robotechnician. * Her disgusted gaze crawls up my body."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13239
msgid "Magdalena: Everyone's so HARD for HC. I get that. But I'm not going to let you seduce me into trusting you. Hopefully, my friends can figure you out, too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13240
msgid "* I feel gutted. I'm not sure why I expected happiness would come so easily after all the shit I've been through. It's hard to hold back tears."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13241
msgid "I'm just trying to help."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13242
msgid "* Cry."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13243
msgid "Fuck you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13244
msgid "Magdalena: I don't know if you're lying. It doesn't matter. I'm not going to tolerate you putting my friends at risk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13245
msgid "Magdalena: Save it, HC. I'm not letting your simulated emotions put my friends at risk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13246
msgid "* Magdalena breaks into a smug grin. * That's what I thought."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13247
msgid "* Beryl jogs into view from the back room. * C'mere, you two! I found something!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13248
msgid " Beryl: I haven't found anything about the anomaly specifically, but... * She leads us into a room filled with piles of paper catalogs in various states of degradation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13249
msgid "* She makes a bee-line to one of the newer-looking ones."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13250
msgid "Beryl: So, every month, a Rust Pup leaves us memo's and stuff his gang has stolen from Gelcorp. Stuff they've read over and want us to archive. The last one should have been here a few d-days ago... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13251
msgid "Beryl: It didn't show up! And the Rust P-Pup headquarters seems to be locked up tighter than usual... I wonder what's g-got them spooked?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13252
msgid "Magdalena: That sounds like a lead. Good job, Beryl. Let's go see if anyone else found anything."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13253
msgid "* Magdalena shoots me one last cold sneer before taking Beryl's hand and leading her away from me. I follow them out of the library, toward Root Street."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13254
msgid "* It's gotten darker since we arrived. The vacant, ruins surrounding the library make me uneasy."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13255
msgid "* An ominous sound, like rotten fruit shifting in a canvas sack, emanates from the darkness ahead of us. I'm not sure if Beryl and Magdalena hear it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13256
msgid "Y'all... you hear that?  * Just as they turn to look at me, the lid of a nearby manhole flies off like a cap on a shaken soda. Shadowy tendrils lunge from the dark hole toward Beryl. She stumbles back, screaming."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13257
msgid "* I dive at Beryl and wrestle the tentacle off of her ankle just as it starts to coil around her. If I hadn't been here, I doubt anyone would have been strong enough..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13258
msgid "* The creature twists its tendrils around me, binding my limbs. Under the sparking streetlight I see it clearly. It's a tentacled pink slime monster. The bulk of its glistening body stretches toward my crotch."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13259
msgid "* Let it fuck me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13260
msgid "* Obliterate it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13261
msgid "You two! Get out of here! I'm going to offer myself as tribute! * I start pulling my clothes off."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13262
msgid "Beryl: Oh my god! We'll go get help right away, I promise! * The creature shivers with apparent joy at the sight of my naked body."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13263
msgid "No, that's ok! I'm just going to go ahead and take one for the team, let this giant monster fuck me. Oh no... I'll see you two later... * I smile reassuringly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13264
msgid "Beryl: Oh, uh, ok. S-see you later. * She chuckles. Even Magdalena cracks a grin, but then whispers something in Beryl's ear. They wave and run off."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13265
msgid "* The beast grips me firmly by the thighs. It lifts me up and throws me on my back, arms pinned and legs spread."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13266
msgid "* A particularly girthy tendril forms and begins probing my ass. Once it gets its bearings, it plunges into me, feeling its way through my insides."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13267
msgid "* It twists and pulses fluidly, reacting to my every twitch. I feel the orgasm begin to well in my cock very quickly. If I had to guess, I'd say its trying to make me cum. A considerate slime."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13268
msgid "* It teases me into orgasm, but draws it out, riding my prostate expertly until the waves of cum subside."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13269
msgid "* It heartily cleans the cum from my stomach, which it seems to enjoy absorbing. It's very thorough, and only when it has every drop does it release me and slink back into the drain."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13270
msgid "* I put my clothes back on and take off toward Forcier's place. That was weird as hell, but probably very relevant to the case."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13271
msgid "* It isn't long before I catch up to Mags and Beryl, who apparently stopped for a quick fuck only a few hundred feet up the road. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13272
msgid "* I wait till it gets close enough and then punch it with all my strength, sending globules of gelatin spattering across the ground."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13273
msgid "* It recoils and tries to reform, but I don't let up, delivering punch after punch at lightning speed until it's no more than a damp stain. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13274
msgid "* The remaining bits of disjointed sludge slither back down the drain, leaving the three of us in peace."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13275
msgid "Beryl: Oh my god, HC. Th-thank you so much... You s-saved me... Also, what the fuck...?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13276
msgid "Magdalena: That's a good question, Beryl. Let's get the hell out of here. * We make haste toward Forcier's place."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13277
msgid "Beryl: Let's just go home. I'm kinda exhausted after all that, ah-hee-hee... * She turns and starts walking back to her apartment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13278
msgid "Magdalena: Gimme a sec Beryl, I'll catch up. * She turns to me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13279
msgid "Magdalena: Hey. You saved my girlfriend. * Her stern stare softens a little."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13280
msgid "Magdalena: That was pretty cool of you, HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13281
msgid "* Thanks."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13282
msgid "* You hurt me..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13283
msgid "Magdalena: I guess I... I dunno what to think of you yet, but I'm going to stop assuming you're bad... * Her gaze falls to the ground and her voice gets quiet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13284
msgid "Magdalena: I know... I'm... sorry. I'll try to be nicer. I guess... * She gets quiet. Even that kinda shitty apology looked hard for her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13285
msgid "Magdalena: If you want to, like, spend some time together, to get to know each other... or whatever. That'd be cool... * She blushes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13286
msgid "Magdalena: I'll see you around, HC. * I force an awkward smile as she leaves to catch up with Beryl."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13287
msgid "* I arrive at Forcier and Olivia's apartment to find the group has already gathered. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13288
msgid "* Olivia, Mags, and Beryl speak in concerned tones near the window. Cadence sits by while Decima and Forcier seem to be checking out each others cybernetic limbs on the couch."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13289
msgid "Decima: Hey HC! Me and Forcier were talking about collaborating on some cool cybernetic shit, I'm super excited! I think the others are talking about the actual investigation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13290
msgid "Forcier: We will join you momentarily."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13291
msgid "Beryl: ...it just c-came out of nowhere. I'd never seen anything like it. * She looks up when I approach. * Hi HC!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13292
msgid "Olivia: Glad you could make it, HC. Beryl brought me up to speed on what you found. I can't say I'm surprised that we already have evidence pointing to Gelcorp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13293
msgid "Olivia: The slime creature thing though... That's truly fucking strange."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13294
msgid "Magdalena: No kidding. Plus, it was an extremely horny slime creature. There's no way that's not significant."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13295
msgid "Olivia: I concur. I think we should make plans to capture one of these creatures so I can get a look at it, maybe learn something useful. Can I rely on you three again?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13296
msgid "Beryl: Of course. We're always r-ready to help. * She shows us a wide smile."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13297
msgid "Olivia: Perfect. You mentioned the creature came out of the storm tunnels. Sounds to me like a good place to start looking. There's an access door near Skipnoise Ave."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13298
msgid "* Olivia pulls a small, spidery device out of her desk drawer. * Just stuff this into the lock, and I'll be able to remotely pick it from here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13299
msgid "* Behind Olivia, Decima is miming her amazement at the pocket-sized break-in drone. It's not un-cute. The uneven leg-lengths and less than perfect solder points lend it some handmade charm."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13300
msgid "Magdalena:  Sounds like a plan. You two ready?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13301
msgid "I guess so."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13303
msgid "You made this lock-picker?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13304
msgid "Olivia: Good enough for me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13305
msgid "Olivia: Designed it, mostly. It was a back-burner project I'd started a while ago that I could never get working. * She smiles. * Decima helped me with the finishing touches."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13306
msgid "Olivia: Let's get started. Curious to see how this thing works in the field."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13307
msgid "Olivia: I'm loving that energy, HC. Have fun out there. * Olivia smiles confidently. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13308
msgid "* Having finished whatever they were doing, Forcier, Decima, and Cadence rejoin the group. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13309
msgid "Cadence: So, did you guys come up with a plan?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13310
msgid "Beryl: Yeah, we're going to go see if we can find another one of those slime c-creatures."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13311
msgid "Decima: Oh damn, you're going after the fuck-beast? Who's offering their butt as bait? * She grins at each of us in turn."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13312
msgid "* Beryl blushes. * I mean, i-i-if it's not too big..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13313
msgid "Magdalena: Look, I'm sure we all want to fuck the monster. We can cross that bridge when we get to it. Let's just focus on the task at hand."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13314
msgid "All right, lead the way."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13315
msgid "* Beryl turns and waves as we get up to leave. * Bye everyone!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13316
msgid "* We don't have much trouble finding the entrance, a tube jutting from the wall of the chasm. Mags inserts the device, which, after a few seconds of clicking noises, crawls back out of the lock."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13317
msgid "* Before we have a chance to react, the door flies open to reveal a tall, stern looking woman holding a knife."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13318
msgid "Woman: Bold move showing up at our tube, kids. What the fuck do you want."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13319
msgid "* Mags immediately steps in front of Beryl and braces herself for a fight. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13320
msgid "We're investigating."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13321
msgid "We didn't know you were here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13322
msgid "We're just looking for some... slime creatures that are relevant to an investigation we're conducting."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13323
msgid "We had no idea anyone was here... We didn't mean to disturb you. We're just looking for access to the storm tunnels. We're after some slimes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13324
msgid "* Behind the woman, mocking laughter spreads through the small crowd. Another leather jacketed lady speaks up. * Maybe we should grant their death wish, Calico. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13325
msgid "* The one who first addressed us, presumably Calico, cracks a cruel grin. * That'd be funny as hell, but no one I don't trust gets in here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13326
msgid "We're not asking."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13327
msgid "You can trust us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13329
msgid "* Calico steps forward, bringing her face only inches from mine. * And I'm not gonna warn you again. Fuck outta here before you get hurt."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13330
msgid "* Grapple her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13332
msgid "* Calico lets out a gravelly laugh, pushes me out the door, and slams it. The sound echoes across the lifeless cityscape."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13333
msgid "* I back carefully out of the door way."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13334
msgid "Calico: That's what I thought. * She smirks at us one last time, then slams the door. The sound echoes across the lifeless cityscape. *"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13335
msgid "* She must sense I'm not backing down, but her intuition isn't enough. She swings but I grab her wrist, turn her around, and pin her to the wall. My droid strength eliminates all possibility of escape."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13336
msgid "* Switchblades and tasers glint in the darkness as the other girls in room all calmly and slowly start moving towards me. This doesn't seem like a fight I can win."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13337
msgid "Beryl: L-let's get out of here... * She looks a little rattled."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13338
msgid "* I release my hold on the girl and she lets out a gravelly laugh, then pushes me out the door and slams it. The sound echoes across the lifeless cityscape."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13339
msgid "Magdalena: Well that... was interesting. * We start walking back towards our apartments together."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13340
msgid "Beryl: I g-guess we're going to have to find a way to win their favor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13341
msgid "Magdalena: Yeah, we can try again after that whole situation blows over. There's got to be a way..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13342
msgid "* We part ways and return to our respective homes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13343
msgid "* Our close call at the storm tunnel plays over in my mind as I make the walk to Root St. Time to think of a plan B, I guess."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13344
msgid "* Beryl greets me at the door of Forcier and Olivia's apartment and gives me a big hug. Behind her, Magdalena and Olivia are talking, Forcier is reading on the couch, and Decima and Cadence are grouped up in the corner."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13345
msgid "* I follow her in. *  Hey, Beryl! How are you doing?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13346
msgid "* Beryl smiles. * I'm good! G-glad you're here. That was so crazy... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13347
msgid "* Magdalena is angrily describing how we were accosted by tunnel-dwellers to Olivia, who looks stern but unconcerned."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13348
msgid "* I turn back to Beryl. * Yeah, that Calico is really a piece of work."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13349
msgid "* Olivia cuts off mid sentence and turns to point that blank visor at me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13350
msgid "Olivia: Did you say Calico?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13351
msgid "Magdalena: Calico was the head of the gang, yeah. Anyway-"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13352
msgid "* Olivia interrupts. * Oh. Fuck."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13353
msgid "* Mags and Beryl look confused but Forcier just chuckles."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13354
msgid "Olivia: Oh yeah, real funny, huh? This is gonna go even further to shit if she finds out I'm involved."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13355
msgid "* Forcier smiles. * Perhaps, but perhaps this is just an opportunity to phlebotomize some bad blood while going about our regular business."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13356
msgid "* Olivia crosses her arms. * You don't know her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13357
msgid "* Forcier looks at all our confused faces. * Calico is Olivia's ex."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13358
msgid "Cadance: Oh, damn! Is this the kinda thing you can talk about, or?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13359
msgid "* Olivia's face twists into an even deeper grimace. * We were working a job, robbing a CEO and tryna get data to expose him for exploiting employees. A company called Shiptip."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13360
msgid "Olivia: He was out of town and I'd pacified his droids to get us a few free minutes in his bedroom. * A smile creeps across her lips and she looks at Forcier. * Those were the RF2's, by the way."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13361
msgid "Forcier: Oh, I remember."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13362
msgid "* Olivia looks back at the rest of us. * They had to retire a line of security droids 'cause of me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13363
msgid "Decima: Badass."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13364
msgid "Olivia: No kidding. Anyway, one of us must have tripped something, 'cause I start getting droid reboot notifications. I grab what I've got, light that fuckers bed on fire, and leave. But I don't see Calico."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13365
msgid "* Cadence laughs. * You lit his bed on fire?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13366
msgid "Olivia: Why not? Worst case scenario, security has to deal with unexpected fire suppression. Best case, the place burns down. It got put out quick, and I didn't need the time, but I was worried about Calico."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13367
msgid "Olivia: ...That was the last time I saw her. Still don't know what happened, really. She was a killer. She might have fought them for fun, for all I knew. I kept looking, but I couldn't find anything definitive."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13368
msgid "Olivia: She was in their database. Her face, her name. It was bad. I knew they didn't have her, but a job like that? I knew they wouldn't stop looking."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13369
msgid "* She looks at me. * I guess we found her, but... I dunno... She's not gonna be looking to do us any favors."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13370
msgid "Beryl: M-maybe she'll understand? You won't know until you talk to her..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13371
msgid "Olivia: I appreciate you, Beryl, but she's been living in a wet pipe for the past few years 'cause of me. This is not a forgive and forget type of situation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13372
msgid "Forcier: Regardless, speaking with her will be a start."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13373
msgid "Olivia: That sounds like a terrible idea to me, but you're usually right about this kinda shit. * Olivia straightens up and takes a deep breath, then just sits quietly for a bit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13374
msgid "* Beryl scoots up behind me and puts her arm around my waist. It's a nice break from the tension."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13375
msgid "* Olivia rises to her feet, straightens her visor, and assumes some kind of power stance. * Alright. Let's fucking do it. Anyone wanna back me up in case she wants to murder me?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13376
msgid "I'm in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13377
msgid "* Keep quiet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13378
msgid "Beryl: Ooh! I'll c-come too! I'm not much of a fighter, but, you know, emotional support!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13379
msgid "Magdalena: Well, I'm not letting my girlfriend get her ass kicked without making at least one intimidation check. I'll go too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13380
msgid "Olivia: Perfect. I appreciate this, you three. Lead on."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13381
msgid "* We exit the apartment and make our way around the rim of the abyss, descending into its less stable banks, and out toward the exposed storm tunnel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13382
msgid "* In front of us, the rusty door looms like an ancient gravestone. Probably shouldn't be thinking about that kind of thing though..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13383
msgid "Beryl: So, we just... Knock?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13384
msgid "* Olivia stays stoic, but I can see her sweating. * Affirmative. Give it a knock, HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13385
msgid "* Three steady rhythmic knocks echo through the silent chasm. I shiver. A second later, the door squeals open."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13386
msgid "Calico: Now, what did I tell you to-- * She cuts off."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13387
msgid "Calico: Olivia."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13388
msgid "* For the first time since I've met her, Olivia's posture becomes a little caved in. She's feeling shame, I think. In her bones...* Hey, Calico..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13389
msgid "* Calico opens her mouth to rage, but Olivia cuts her off. * I had no idea where you were for so long. My friends just-"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13390
msgid "Calico: You're gonna show your face here after getting me on that fucking corporate shit list? For fucking real?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13391
msgid "Olivia: Calico, I didn't-"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13392
msgid "* Calico's face is red. * You blew that job and left me to answer for it! Or did you fucking forget about that, just like you 'forgot' about all that security bullshit? "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13393
msgid "* Olivia's head dips further as Calico raises her voice further. * You never had my back, Olivia! When it came down to it, all your promises, all that lovey garbage you said, it turned to shit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13394
msgid "Calico: You're a fucking bitch. You're a worthless hacker and a worthless friend. Fuck off. * She slams the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13395
msgid "* It's quiet and the air feels heavy. We just sit there, soaking in the discomfort, wondering what to do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13396
msgid "* Magdalena's voice is low and hushed. * Damn..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13397
msgid "Olivia: Yeah. Uh. Let's get the fuck out of here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13398
msgid "* The walk back is uncomfortable, to say the least. We pretty much just keep quiet till we're at the apartment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13399
msgid "* Everyone back in the room seems to sense the fate of our mission. Their smiles fade."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13400
msgid "Forcier: What happened?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13401
msgid "Olivia: She... Got mad. Said some bad stuff. It didn't work. I feel like shit, and we have no plan. So..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13402
msgid "Magdalena: Calico blamed her for everything. It was harsh. She's not gonna budge."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13403
msgid "Forcier: Even so, I have an idea to remedy that shit feeling."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13404
msgid "Olivia: Oh, yeah? What's that?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13405
msgid "Forcier: I think we ought to get Calico off that list. We may have to find an alternative way of testing the water, but helping her could be worth the peace of mind alone. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13406
msgid "Decima: Yeah good call. There's nothing better for the brain than a nice long stretch of high road!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13407
msgid "Olivia: I appreciate the suggestion, but there's no way I'm taking a second shot at the worst job I've ever pulled."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13408
msgid "Forcier: Olivia, you've never had a team like this one. * They look around at us and we smile. * I'm sure they'd be willing to help."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13409
msgid "Cadence: Honestly, with the shit we're getting into, a practice heist is probably a good idea."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13410
msgid "Decima: Fuck yeah, Practice Heist! I'll start drafting plans!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13411
msgid "Olivia: Jesus... Alright, let's do it then. No Decima plans though. * She cracks a smile."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13412
msgid "Forcier: Excellent. Not to kick you all out, but I think I need to comfort my girlfriend. When we meet again, Olivia and I will have formulated a plan. Until then, I wish you all well."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13413
msgid "Olivia: Thanks for the help everyone! It was good to see you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13414
msgid "Beryl: Bye!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13415
msgid "* We leave Forcier and Olivia in their apartment and begin making our separate ways home."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13416
msgid "* Her eyes linger on me, like she's waiting. When I remain quiet, she speaks up. * I really could use you on this one, HC. You've got the only muscle that's really gonna make a difference, no offense everyone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13417
msgid "Beryl: Sh-she's right HC. You're really strong. I'll go, for emotional support, but I'm no good in a fight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13418
msgid "Magdalena: We'll I'm not letting my girlfriend get her ass kicked without making at least one intimidation check. I'll go too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13419
msgid "* Beryl gives Mags a kiss on the cheek. * So, how about it, HC?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13420
msgid "I can't..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13421
msgid "Yeah, ok."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13422
msgid "* My mind goes back to last time and I start shaking. I'm not a fighter, I can't be. Not yet... I love my friends but I don't think they realize how recently I was in real hell. My wounds are raw."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13423
msgid "* I'm a droid, yeah, but I'm fragile in all the ways that matter. I don't wanna let them down, but... Fuck... I'm gonna panic..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13424
msgid "* Beryl's hand on my back grounds me before It gets bad. I realize I'm white-knuckle wringing my hands..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13425
msgid "Beryl: Hey, HC... It's ok, really. There's no pressure. Are you ok?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13426
msgid "Uh, yeah. I'll be fine. I'm just gonna sit this one out, ok?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13427
msgid "Beryl: Of course... Do you want me to stay here with you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13428
msgid "Nah, I'll be fine. You do your thing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13429
msgid "Decima: I'll go in her stead! I've got this, baby! * She lifts her prosthetic arm toward the ceiling. Cadence gets to her feet as well."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13430
msgid "Olivia: Glad to have you with us, but that arm doesn't have super strength..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13431
msgid "Decima: True, but it knows how to swing a pipe wrench! * She looks around then grabs a screw driver off of Olivia's desk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13432
msgid "* Olivia facepalms. * Decima, that's not a... Fuck it, let's go."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13433
msgid "* Decima, Cadence, Olivia, and Magdalena shuffle out the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13434
msgid "* The apartment is suddenly silent. Forcier lowers their book. * Make yourself comfortable, HC. * They tuck their metallic legs in, making room on the couch. I join them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13435
msgid "* A page turns. It's quiet enough that I can hear them breathing. In a bit, they put the book down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13436
msgid "Forcier: How are you doing, HC?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13437
msgid "Good."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13438
msgid "Eh."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13439
msgid "Forcier: I'll take your word for it. Just so you know, though... You'll never have to pretend you're ok here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13440
msgid "Oh... Thanks Forcier."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13441
msgid "* They lift their arms, offering me their lap to rest on."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13442
msgid "* Nap on them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13443
msgid "* Nap alone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13444
msgid "Forcier: Things will get better, I hope you know. Each second pushes the past farther away from us. Rest, HC. Kill some time."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13445
msgid "* I scoot over and curl up in their lap. They resume reading while I drift off in their arms."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13446
msgid "* I let myself stretch out on the couch, head on the armrest, and close my eyes. In a bit, I doze off."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13448
msgid "* I wake up to a noticeably darker sky. Four sad faces file into the apartment. Forcier sets down their book."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13449
msgid "Forcier: How did it go?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13450
msgid "Cadence: Yeah, uh... * She shuffles her feet. * We chickened out. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13451
msgid "Olivia: It was a nice walk, though. Got my head clear."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13452
msgid "* Decima snickers. * Despite all the ideas I was offering."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13453
msgid "Olivia: Yeah, we're gonna need an actual plan. And we're going to need both of you. This is gonna be a lot..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13454
msgid "* During the walk to Forcier and Olivia's place, I try and mentally prepare myself for today's heist. Whatever the plan is, I just hope it's safe..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13455
msgid "* I autopilot up Root Street and towards the apartment, but am caught off guard by what I find. A small hover barge floats on the curb in front of the building, about the size of a king sized mattress. The group is on board."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13456
msgid "* They are silently squatting over a large whiteboard laid flat on the floor of the barge. Olivia is sketching intently. Behind them is a large crate."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13457
msgid "* Forcier, Cadence, and Beryl stand to greet me. Beryl waves then kneels back down, while Cadence rushes over, pulls me up onto the craft, and hugs me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13458
msgid "Hey, Cadence! Uh, what's in the box?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13459
msgid "Forcier: Nothing. Join us, HC. We're reviewing the plan."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13460
msgid "* I squeeze into the circle and pop the appropriate squat. Under Olivia's marker, an elaborate floor plan is taking shape, complete with vents, security routes, and, of course, targets."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13461
msgid "Olivia: Let's drive and plan, we're burning daylight. * While Olivia draws, Forcier pulls a lever and the barge starts gliding down the street at a quick walking pace."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13462
msgid "Olivia: Soooooo... Ok. * She dots some i's. * So, I've been getting updated on Shiptip, the company we're after. Used to make shit but I guess they're just a fulfillment company now?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13463
msgid "Olivia: Either way, they're headquartered in the same building as last time, strong security, and they've patched up my entry route. Fortunately, I think I've found a weakness."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13464
msgid "* She taps the whiteboard. * This is a warehouse in the industrial district, owned by Shiptip. Minimal activity, but notable for its... * She grins. * Server room."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13465
msgid "Olivia: All you guys have to do is get me and Forcier inside."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13466
msgid "* Decima raises her hand. * I have a question! Did you say... 'Shiptip?'"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13467
msgid "Olivia: Yes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13468
msgid "* Decima pauses. * Dumb name."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13469
msgid "* Olivia tents her fingers and leans forward. * Accurate."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13470
msgid "Olivia: So here's the plan. Magdalena and Beryl have watchout duty. * Magdalena sighs loudly. * You're gonna be posted on adjacent buildings, making sure no one dangerous shows up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13471
msgid "Olivia: HC, you're on infiltration. We're getting you in, and you're clearing a path for us. * She points to a blue dashed line on the map."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13472
msgid "Olivia: That's me and Forcier. We're going after the servers. * Her finger traces a red dashed line. * Hacking the HQ from here, then destroying their backup. Clearing Calico's name, once and for all."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13473
msgid "Olivia: Decima, Cadence, you're on delivery duty. You're gonna act like delivery people, get the package in, and provide a general distraction. * She cocks her head towards the crate."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13474
msgid "* Decima throws her head back and calls towards the heavens. * FUCK. YES. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13475
msgid "Magdalena: See, Olivia, you've gotta play DnD with us at some point. Then you'd know why Decima should not be allowed to play a charisma character."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13476
msgid "Cadence: Ok, but for real, Decima looks the part but look at me? Who's gonna believe I'm a delivery girl?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13477
msgid "* Decima laughs her rough, low laugh, then speaks in a playfully sarcastic voice. * But Cadence, it's bring your daughter to work day!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13478
msgid "Cadence: Nooooo!! Oh my god!! * She pushes Decima, who yelps and flails but stays on board."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13479
msgid "Wait, so what's actually in that crate?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13480
msgid "Olivia: You. That's how we're getting you inside. All you've gotta do is wait till they file you away, then break out of your box, cut power to the door alarm, smash the security camera, then open the door. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13481
msgid "Olivia: I can loop the camera feed to give you a 40 second window, so be quick. Think you can be handle it?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13482
msgid "Uuuh..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13483
msgid "Not at all!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13484
msgid "Absolutely!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13485
msgid "Olivia: You'll have to do better than that once you're inside, but I know you can handle it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13486
msgid "Decima: Yeah, just relax HC. You've got this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13487
msgid "Olivia: Excellent! With that quick response time, you're gonna do perfectly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13488
msgid "* The barge hangs out over the edge of the chasm, cut off from the reference point of the ground. Looking down feels like sitting stagnant in a void of starless space."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13489
msgid "* We curve around and begin to see waves of the industrial district, short choppy rows of low ruins sprawled out toward the horizon, broken only by the jutting spires of Gelcorp. A dark scar against the magenta sky."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13490
msgid "* That we're pointed more in the direction of the library is honestly a bit comforting."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13491
msgid "Beryl: Oh, hey, I know this p-p-place! I pass it on my way to work, sometimes..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13492
msgid "Magdalena: Oh, nice, you know the good lookout spots then?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13493
msgid "Beryl: Uh, m-maybe, yeah! Forcier, can you p-pull up here? * She gestures to a cluster of ruins a few buildings down from the warehouse."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13494
msgid "Forcier: Certainly. Do you both have your radios? "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13495
msgid "* Magdalena taps her ear * Yeah, we do. You'll hear if we see anything."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13496
msgid "Forcier: Thank you. * The barge slows to a stop and the two hop out and scurry into the ruins. We continue on."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13497
msgid "* I fix my eyes on the warehouse we're drifting towards. * Uh, I didn't get a radio... "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13498
msgid "Olivia: Yeah, they'd be able to detect something like that. No in or outbound signals. You'll be on your own. * She lifts the crate's lid and gestures for me to get in."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13499
msgid "* As I climb in, Cadence gives me a pat on the back. * Just stay chill. We'll be in and out like that. * She snaps as the lid comes down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13500
msgid "* The interior of the box is small and dark. Curled up, I can barely see anything through a tiny drill hole."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13501
msgid "Decima: Guys, I know this is medium-high stakes, but I'm so psyched for this you don't even know."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13502
msgid "Olivia: Just be careful, and stick to the plan."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13503
msgid "* The barge lurches to a stop, and sways as people dismount. Presumably, Olivia and Forcier have left to hide and wait for me to do my job."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13504
msgid "* The barge glides a few more meters, then I hear a slap on the lid, followed by Cadence speaking in a hushed voice. * We're here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13505
msgid "* I'm jostled a bit as they unload my crate and start pulling me inside. The city noise is cut off as a door closes. We're inside."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13506
msgid "Decima: Howdy, bud. Gotta a box for temp storage. Sign this."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13507
msgid "* There's a pause before a voice even lower than Decima's speaks up. * ...Who the fuck are you? And what is this form?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13508
msgid "Decima: Look, Bucko, just let me do my job. Sign the form and I can get on with my day."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13509
msgid "* The gruff voice gets even more indignant. * This form is hand written... Did you make this?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13510
msgid "Decima: Look, son, I get that you're new to this, but I've been delivering packages since before you were born! In my day, every form was handwritten! For fuck's sake!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13511
msgid "The voice: It's written on the back of a reciept for... Frostydogs? Yeah just nine flavors of Frostydogs. Also, how old are you? "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13512
msgid "Decima: Now listen here, chummer, I didn't lose my arm to a rogue forklift just to catch the shit of some punk newbie. If obstructing my delivery duties is your game, I'm gonna have to find your supervisor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13513
msgid "The voice: Fine. * I hear paper snatched and scribbled upon. * Now get the fuck out of here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13514
msgid "* Shoes shuffle as Decima and Cadence turn to leave. I can barely make out Decima's departing mumbles. * And to think! On bring your daughter to work day!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13515
msgid "The voice: What was that?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13516
msgid "Decima: Nothing, Byeee! * The door closes and I'm left alone."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13517
msgid "* A few moments later, I feel the crate begin to move. I hope they hurry, Olivia should be cutting the camera feed any second."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13518
msgid "* I repeat the plan in my head, trying to stay calm and focused. Destroy the Camera. Disable the door alarm. Open the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13519
msgid "* The crate comes to a halt, and after a grunting noise, the sound of footsteps leads away. When I hear a door open and close, I cautiously let myself out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13520
msgid "* Times up. I hear a faint knock on the door. They must be waiting. At the other end of the hall, a door swings open. I dive behind the nearest heap of boxes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13521
msgid "* Footsteps echo through the stagnant interior of the warehouse. I hold my breath. If I could sweat, I bet I'd be sweating like crazy."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13522
msgid "* It sounds like whoever is in here with me is approaching the hallway on the right. Visions of an unsuspecting Olivia and Forcier opening the door to meet a guard flood my mind. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13523
msgid "* Instead, the dude just goes into the server room. Whatever he's doing, I hope it doesn't take too long. We're on a tight schedule as it is, and we're wasting precious time."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13524
msgid "* I have no idea how much time passes, but it feels like eternity before the door reopens and the dude returns to the door he originally appeared in. I untense my body and take a breath."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13525
msgid "* Without wasting any more time, I hop up, finish whatever I had left to do, and let Olivia and Forcier in. They don't look happy."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13526
msgid "S-sorry..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13527
msgid "Olivia: Save it. We're on a job. Let's go."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13528
msgid "* I open the door and Olivia slips through, followed quickly by Forcier. * You, my friend, are a natural. * She puts her arm around me and grins."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13529
msgid "* We walk down the hallway and they pause to survey the contents of the warehouse. The hulking tubes, stained with purple sludge laying around the room, the buckets of hazardous material..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13530
msgid "* Forcier and Olivia share a concerned glance, then continue."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13531
msgid "* When we reach the server room, Olivia stops in her tracks. * Whoa. This is... more than I was expecting."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13532
msgid "Forcier: More than any of us were... Olivia, do you know where to go to extract the information we need?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13533
msgid "* She stretches her arms out and cracks her fingers. * Of course. Let's get to work. * She begins stalking the rows of servers, tapping away at her wrist computer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13534
msgid "Olivia: HC, Forcier, keep an eye out for me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13535
msgid "* I give an awkward thumbs up. Forcier motions for me to watch to the left and they take the right."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13536
msgid "* Olivia pulls her toolbox up next to her and gets to work. Forcier and I wait for her to finish in silence. All I can hear is the tick of metal against metal and my own breathing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13537
msgid "I feel..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13538
msgid "Calm"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13539
msgid "Scared"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13540
msgid "* I take slow, deep breaths, pushing away everything in my mind except the mission. I try to feel prepared for whatever comes next..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13541
msgid "* My mind can't help but drift to what's at stake here. This warehouse has a lot more sensitive stuff in it than predicted. I'm not sure what would happen if we got caught."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13542
msgid "* I start breathing hard, spiraling into a deep mess of anxiety. Then I gasp, way louder than I was intending."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13543
msgid "Olivia: HC! * She whispers angrily."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13544
msgid "Sorry! * I blurt in voice that would feel too loud in even a regular conversation. Forcier swings around."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13545
msgid "Forcier: What is happeni--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13546
msgid "* Forcier's eyes narrow. * Do you hear that? It sounds like footsteps."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13547
msgid "* The door to the server room swings open and a guard in a pristine uniform glares at us. He's a far cry from the run-down exterior of the warehouse."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13548
msgid "Guard: Hey-- what the fuck?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13549
msgid "* He gestures at Olivia, who is still hunched over a server, back turned. * Step away from there!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13550
msgid "* He pulls out a small radio and poses his finger over the button. If I'm gonna do something, it better be quick..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13551
msgid "* Persuade him."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13552 result.py:13566
msgid "* Knock him out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13553
msgid "Whoa, now just wait one minute! We were hired to come over here and fix these, well, servers. * I hold out my hand for him to shake."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13554
msgid "I'm.... * My inability to lie about my name is even more relevant than usual. * ... I'm with..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13555
msgid "Tech Fix Associates."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13556
msgid "Fuck off Incorporated."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13557
msgid "Gelcorp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13558
msgid "* The guard's eyes narrow. I glance around at Olivia and Forcier, desperate for something to work with."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13559
msgid "* Olivia's back is still turned, but Forcier is attentive. I point at them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13560
msgid "This is my manager, Forc... Fo..Force..ball uh... Tu...ber. * Forcier remains utterly stoic while I botch the name."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13561
msgid "Forcier: Yes, that is correct, I am Forceball Tuber... Greetings."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13562
msgid "Guard: ...Where are your uniforms?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13563
msgid "* Forcier and I glance at each other. Fuck..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13564
msgid "* The guard slowly lifts the radio again."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13565
msgid "* Keep talking."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13567
msgid "I think management would be preeetty irritated getting a call reporting their three best... fixing people."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13568
msgid "Guard: Enough. * He presses the button on the radio. * We've got intruders in the server room! Get someone down here, ASAP."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13569
msgid "* He steps towards Olivia, holstering the radio and producing a baton. Forcier and I jump into action."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13570
msgid "* The guard grits his teeth. * So that's how it's gonna be... Ok. * He presses the button on the radio. * We've got intruders in the server room! Get someone down here, ASAP."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13571
msgid "* I lunge towards him with droid-speed, jabbing his sternum with enough force to push the air out of his lungs. His eyes go wide and he falls backward."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13572
msgid "* Forcier catches his writhing body and holds him down while I jump on top, hands around his throat, until his eyes flicker closed and he falls unconscious."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13573
msgid "* Olivia addresses us without even a pause in her typing. * He's not dead, is he?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13574
msgid "* I check his pulse. * Nah, not even close. I hope that bought you some time..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13575
msgid "* Olivia does not look pleased. * Thoughts on that uniform, Forcier?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13576
msgid "* They scrutinize the unconscious guard. * I don't recognize it, but I'm concerned with the level of security it represents."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13577
msgid "Olivia: Yeah... Something's not right..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13578
msgid "* A few moments pass before she speaks up again. * It's done. Calico is safe. The kind of stuff that's in here though, it doesn't make sense... I need more time."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13579
msgid "Forcier: We don't have it. Someone will be here for the guard soon, or to investigate the broken camera."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13580
msgid "Olivia: I'll be quick... Just... A bit longer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13581
msgid "* A faint noise comes to my attention. Something heavy. Metal on metal. It's vaguely familiar, but I can't place it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13582
msgid "Does anyone hear that? * A feeling of dread begins to spread through my body, leaving me shaking and nauseous."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13583
msgid "Forcier: No. What do you hear, HC?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13585
msgid "* Forcier makes their way to the door and cracks it, pressing themselves against it to get a view."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13586
msgid "* When they turn back, they're visibly anxious. It's something I've never seen in them before."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13587
msgid "* They put a hand on Olivia's shoulder * We need to hide."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13588
msgid "* I hoist the guard and we all dart behind the rows of servers and hunker down, just before the door creaks open."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13589
msgid "* It's unmistakable, I can see the top of it above the server rows and I can hear the sound of 2 tons of bulletproof metal rhythmically stomping into the ground at a slow and steady pace."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13590
msgid "* A ruthless robotic centaur created solely for the purpose of maintaining order by whatever means necessary, including the use of its military grade weaponized arms."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13591
msgid "An... an Interceptor. What the hell is it doing here? * I whisper, my conduction fluid chilling in my veins."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13592
msgid "This place must be way more important than we.... Than we thought... * I'm having trouble catching my breath."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13593
msgid "Olivia: Oh shit. Are we totally screwed?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13594
msgid "It's impossible to destroy..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13595
msgid "Forcier: We can delay it. Olivia, keep working. HC, I will need you to distract the interceptor while I sneak around behind it and--"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13596
msgid "Olivia: And get killed! Forcier, you can't."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13597
msgid "Forcier: I assure you, I can. I'm highly confident in my abilities if HC is able to successfully keep its attention. Just get it to the back of the room."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13598
msgid "Ah... Oh jeez. Ok, I got this. * I think of how to distract the interceptor..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13599
msgid "* Pretend to be a lost employee."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13600
msgid "* Confront it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13601
msgid "* Throw something."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13602
msgid "* The interceptor marches heavily down the corridor of server arrays. I look for something to throw, but there's nothing but tech. I unslot something heavy and throw it towards the back of the room."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13603
msgid "* Its insect-like head swivels toward the sound, then it takes off at a quick trot towards the back row."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13604
msgid "* The interceptor marches heavily down the corridor of server arrays. I try to look casual as I saunter out from behind the row of servers."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13605
msgid "* Being face to face with the creature sends me back to the alleyway where Beryl found me. It towers over me, still and emotionless, calculating its next move."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13606
msgid "Oh, thank goodness! Uh, I'm a new employee... here * I am having trouble thinking straight, just standing near this enormous machine makes me feel like a bug. It takes up the entire space between the wall and the rows."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13607
msgid "There's an intruder! Over there! Please help! * I can't bring myself to look into its dead eyes for more than a second."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13608
msgid "* I am startled when it starts talking. I expected a low, flat robotic voice. But it sounds like it hasn't spoken in a while, a higher pitched scratching sound, like it's manipulating its gears to form words."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13609
msgid "Interceptor: EMPLOYEE NOT RECOGNIZED - PLEASE PRESENT IDENTIFICATION"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13610
msgid "* I swallow hard and try to hide my trembling. * Look, see? Right over here! * I back down the row of servers."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13611
msgid "The interceptor begins advancing quickly towards me. At the last second, I bolt sideways, out of its reach and back towards the others."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13612
msgid "* The interceptor marches heavily down the corridor of server arrays. Gritting my teeth, I jump out and start running towards the back of the room. It immediately engages pursuit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13613
msgid "* When it reaches me, I turn suddenly, trying to catch it off guard with a blow to the lower abdomen. It absorbs the droid-strength punch without so much as a flinch. Fuck..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13614
msgid "* It rears up, kicking with both of its front legs, its arms spread wide in a spiderlike posture. Some kind of herding maneuver, I'm sure."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13615 result.py:13618 result.py:13629 result.py:13632
msgid "Dodge"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13616
msgid "* I duck away from the crushing blow, and try to get past it..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13617
msgid "* It swings wide with its claw arm."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13619
msgid "* I hop over the arm and back towards the others, barely avoiding its massive reach."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13620
msgid "* It catches me with its hooves, knocking me out of range. I struggle to my feet and waste no time in dashing back to the others."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13621
msgid "* It catches me with the cutting edge of its claw, knocking me out of range. I struggle to my feet and waste no time in dashing back to the others."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13622
msgid "* Forcier grabs us and runs for the door, turning around at the last moment to give the closest row of servers a hard kick with their long, metallic leg."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13623
msgid "* The rows of servers begin to domino toward the interceptor in a tidal wave of hot tech."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13624
msgid "* The collission throws it off balance, and takes a minute to regain its footing, but when it does, it begins wading towards the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13625
msgid "* We slam it, and rush out back into the industrial ruins. Decima, Cadence, Magdalena, and Beryl are waiting for us in the barge. Their smiles fade when they see our distress."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13626
msgid "* Behind us, the door blasts open and the interceptor rockets out at full gallop. The gap is closing fast, and Olivia is falling behind."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13627
msgid "* We're at the barge, but it's too late. The droid is on us before we have a chance to jump on board. I dart back between it and Olivia. * Go!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13628
msgid "* I brace myself for combat, but it matches my speed, circling and thrusting with its detention claw."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13630
msgid "* I turn with the trajectory of the claw arm, spinning along it like cog work. Before I have time to regain my balance, the other arm boxes me in, and the claw shoots towards me again."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13631
msgid "* Before I have time to regain my balance, the other arm boxes me in, and the claw shoots towards me again."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13633
msgid "* I leap backwards, struggling to stay upright. It seems to predict my every move. I can't keep up..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13634
msgid "Interceptor: RESISTANCE MAY INFLUENCE THE SEVERITY OF YOUR SENTENCING - PLEASE REMAIN CALM WHILE YOU ARE DETAINED"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13635
msgid "* It jabs again. I move to dodge but it grabs me mid-maneuver, its claw closing around my forearm."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13636
msgid "* I move to dodge but it grabs me mid-maneuver, its claw closing around my forearm."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13637
msgid "* I push back, but even my strength is no match for it. A yellow light in its head ignites and a beam sweeps over me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13638
msgid "* The interceptor voice echoes from the depths of its bulky chassis. * SCAN COMPLETE - DISORDERLY OBJECT CATEGORY - SERVICE DROID - - - DETAINING"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13639
msgid "* Pistons glide silently in its chest as it forces me to the ground. I'm not beat yet though... I reach up to my shoulder and pinch several pressure points under my skin, then twist away. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13640
msgid "* My arm detaches and I roll to the side, out of its view. It relinquishes its grip, and turns to follow me, but I leap towards the chasm, catching the arm and grabbing the edge of the drifting barge."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13641
msgid "* My legs dangle over the void as we drift out of the droids reach. Behind me, in the low light of evening, it stares blankly over the edge. I shudder."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13642
msgid "* After a few moments, I toss my arm up onto the barge and the group helps me climb up."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13643
msgid "Cadence: Damn, HC! What was that crazy fucking centaur thing? What the hell happened? * She pulls me into a tight hug that Beryl joins."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13644
msgid "Olivia: Interceptor."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13645
msgid "Cadence: Ooh, jeez, they're even fuckier than I was imagining. Wow..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13646
msgid "Beryl: I'm r-really glad you're all ok... * She hands my arm to Decima, who sockets it into place."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13647
msgid "Olivia: Me too... * She stares off, still breathing hard from the escape. * We... we did good."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13648
msgid "* She leans back against Forcier, who grips her arm reassuringly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13649
msgid "Decima: No pressure but Imma need some deets."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13650
msgid "Olivia: I... don't know. There was some weird shit in there. And too much security. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13651
msgid "Forcier: The warehouse is being used to house a number of large tubes, all which bear the Gelcorp logo. I suspect Shiptip is some kind of front, or satellite company of Gelcorp."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13652
msgid "Olivia: Yeah, there was a ton of Gelcorp data in the server system as well. * She looks at her wrist computer. * Nothing I had time to salvage, unfortunately..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13653
msgid "Forcier: We did what we came to do. That's what's important. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13654
msgid "Cadence: Dude, if there are Gelcorp science vats in there, that sounds hella significant. I'd put that discovery on the accomplishments list."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13655
msgid "Foricer: Agreed. An overall productive trip."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13656
msgid "Decima: Damn, yeah, sounds like it. Y'all need a nap. Let's get this lil' floater home. * She slaps the side of the barge then snuggles up on Forciers lap next to Olivia."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13657
msgid "* By the time we make it across the chasm, we're all lying on the floor of the barge together, watching the hazy sunset over the distant industrial district."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13658
msgid "* It's a strange vibe. Tense but relaxed, scared but safe. We feel like a team."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13659
msgid "* We pull up to the front of Olivia and Forcier's apartment and all hop out and say our goodbyes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13660
msgid "* Before I go, Olivia stops me * Some of the random data I got my hands on did turn out to be worth something. * She punches a few keys on her wrist computer. * Here's your cut."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13661
msgid "* She hands me a little pile of coupons. * Bye HC."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13662
msgid "Bye, Olivia. Bye, everyone. * I walk home."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13663
msgid "* LustPump milker added to machine inventory."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13664
msgid "* The door alarm is still active. I'd better keep looking."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13665
msgid "* A last minute email lets me know we're meeting at the entrance to the storm tunnels. That suits me. It's a farther walk back around the chasm from Root Street than walking from my apartment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13666
msgid "* It doesn't take long to make my way beyond the still-standing city blocks and into the perimeter of the sinkhole; a steep, messy descent of concrete debris skewered on pipes and girders, giving way to the abyss."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13667
msgid "* Well-trodden filth packed into a shattered concrete crevasse forms a decently safe path towards the storm tunnels. I follow it, careful to step over the various garbage that's settled here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13668
msgid "* When the storm tunnels come into view, I realize I must be early. I decide to hang back and wait. I'm not sure what Calico would do if she found me loitering outside her tunnel."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13669
msgid "* It's kind of awkward for a while, but eventually I start to hear Decima's low voice carrying over the chasm. I hop up to greet them."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13670
msgid "Hey everyone!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13671
msgid "* Cadence slams a hand into her chest. * Holy FUCK, HC!!! You scared the hell out of me!!"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13672
msgid "* Decima cackles and pets her hair. * Cadence, I'm sure she's more scared of you than you are of her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13673 result.py:17760 result.py:18037 result.py:18765
msgid "Um, excuse me?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13674
msgid "Decima: It's supposed to be a domme joke? Never mind. * She laughs again, and Beryl smiles, but everyone else remains cold."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13675
msgid "* Olivia especially looks deep in her own troubled thoughts."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13676
msgid "Forcier: Just let me know when you think you're ready, ok? * They give Olivia's shoulder an affirmative squeeze."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13677
msgid "Olivia: I don't think I ever will be, to be honest..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13678
msgid "Forcier: We've done what we can. We're not here to convince her of anything. What happens after this is up to her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13679
msgid "* Olivia remains silent, but takes Forcier's hand."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13680
msgid "* We all begin to file down towards the large circular pipe, Olivia and Forcier in front, Beryl and I in back. Even Decima seems to start feeling the tension."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:13681
