msgstr ""

#: result.py:14785
msgid "* Blue flesh. My old body is back. Next to me, Olivia stands up, revealing the little doll. Arms and legs detaches, head turned to an awkward angle. Poor thing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14786
msgid "* She takes a step forward, straddles my limp doll body. The up-skirt view is beautiful, entrancing, as her hips descend towards me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14787
msgid "* She kneels in front of me, offering me another intimate look at her immaculate pussy. This time, though, I'm safe in the cloister of her thighs, the shelter of her massive body leaning over me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14788
msgid "* There's a moment where she just stays hunched above me, smiling. I think I can detect more warmth than could just have come from pride in the success of her invention, but maybe I'm just being optimistic."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14789
msgid "* Maybe I'm projecting a little warmth of my own into my interpretation of her. After all, I'm a lucky fucking girl, getting a seat at the foot of this goddess. If I had a mouth, I know I'd be smiling."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14790
msgid "* When I realize her palm is lowering onto me, lifting me, obscuring my vision, my happiness is overwhelming. She might as well be reaching down from heaven."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14791
msgid "* She turns me over, and the last thing I feel is the resonant snap of a switch on my back toggling me off..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14792
msgid "* Blue flesh. My old body is back. Next to me, Olivia stands up, the little doll in her hands, it's power switch exposed. She tosses it on the desk."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14793
msgid "* I look around groggily, then crawl over to the doll. * S-see ya. Wouldn't wanna be ya..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14794
msgid "* Olivia chuckles, helps me up. * Are you ok?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14795
msgid "* I look down at the floor, the sea of stars that felt infinite just a moment ago. Now it's all just paper."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14796
msgid "I'm a little, uh... * Various sensory cues around the room start to re-ground me. Temperature. The light from the window. My palms brushing at my sides. * I'm ok. Weird to be big again."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14797
msgid "* Olivia smirks. * You're not big. Come, I'll show you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14798
msgid "* She leads me across her apartment and to the window, to the fire escape outside. It sags a few inches under our weight, and I grip at the pockmarked enamel like it would keep me safe if this whole thing came down."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14799
msgid "* She climbs the steep, switchback staircases above me, and I help myself to another gloriously naked upskirt view. I only stumble a bit, and I doubt she'd have guessed what distracted me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14800
msgid "* After the stairs, and a short ladder to the roof, we take a breather. Except for some of Olivia's satellite monitoring equipment, everything up here is Pira City's special brand of shitty. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14801
msgid "* At it's highest points, the edges of the building are shaved down to bare brick, sandblasted during the harshest weather."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14802
msgid "*  Everything else has been maintained just infrequently enough, and minimally enough, to be sad."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14803
msgid "* The roof is a patchwork of hammered tin and tar. Every metal and brick surface is thick with enamel through which the degradation of the fundamental materials of the building are obvious."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14804
msgid "* But the repairs have nonetheless been made, as if a coat of whitewash would stem the decay. Beyond the rooftop edges, the city sprawls. Layer on layer of ruin sinking into the smoggy, pink distance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14805
msgid "* And above us, the homogenous gradient of the sky expands, somehow made more vast by its lack of cloudy blemish or window to the stars. I think I get it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14806
msgid "* She hops up onto one of the crumbling ledges, takes a seat, dangles her feet over the alley below. * Check it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14807
msgid "* She points, and I follow her finger east, up Root Street, over Decima's workshop and beyond the theater. Through the dark, uninhabited ruins. To the place where the ruins fall away."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14808
msgid "Olivia: You can see the edge from here. Can't see them sparkle from this far away, but those shapes at the edge are the black dunes. The wasteland."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14809
msgid "* She turns and points in the opposite direction, toward the heart of the city."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14810
msgid "Olivia: And look. You can see the sinkhole, too."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14811
msgid "* The west end of Root Street is a jagged cut in the asphalt where, hundreds of years ago, the ground had suddenly fallen away. * Damn. It somehow looks even bigger from up here."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14812
msgid "Olivia: Right? It's one of those, too-big-to-see-up-close kinda things. Need some perspective."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14813
msgid "* The perimeter of the chasm is serrated with the jutting stumps of hundreds of streets, just like Root Street, that were lost. The buildings look so small that they almost seem unreal."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14814
msgid "Olivia: Did you know that the biggest Lux Sat of the age of the Lux Sats would have been too big to fit in that hole?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14815
msgid "Neat. That a chunky satellite."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14816
msgid "Olivia: For real. Do you still feel big, HC?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14817
msgid "* I laugh. * Wow, so deep! As a matter of fact, I do! But in a different way... * She's right. The handful of feet that made up the height difference between the doll and I seems pretty insignificant."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14818
msgid "* We chill up here for a little bit, but as night comes on, it starts getting cold. She sees me down the stairs, and at the door to her apartment, we say our goodbyes."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14819
msgid "* Before I go, I gesture to the doll. * That was fucked up, but in a fun way. You should do science things to me again sometime."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14820
msgid "Olivia: Excellent. I'd love to. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14821
msgid "* We kiss, then I walk away. The door shuts, and it echoes with my footsteps through the stair box. Time to get home. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14822
msgid "* She smirks and withdraws the crown. * Your loss. Now you have to watch me read these star maps. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14823
msgid "* I laugh but she takes a seat on the edge of the massive paper circle and starts entering things into her wrist computer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14824
msgid "* It's as boring as it sounds. She's not great at dividing her attention, even when I actively try talking to her. I know she's not trying to be rude, and that sometimes a fixation can't be ignored, so I just chill."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14825
msgid "* Her couch is comfy as fuck, and it's peaceful to just recline and watch her work. The fact that she can make any sense of the array of papers is very impressive."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14826
msgid "* After narrowly avoiding an accidental nap, I decide it's time to go. We say our goodbyes, and I head out into the evening air."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14827
msgid "* As I make my way along the decrepit road through the swamp, the wind howls low and mournful over the nearby chasm, rustles the toxic reeds around my feet.."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14828
msgid "* I hadn't considered what wind might do to the swamp, but as it starts to vaporize the peak of each tiny wave, I start to worry. With each lap against the shore, more deep precipitate is vomited at my feet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14829
msgid "* I take several quick steps to stay just ahead of the encroaching sludge, and I soon realize that this process is happening all along the edge of the crumbling esplanade. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14830
msgid "* I don't run the rest of the way to the capsule motel; running would be an admission that I had forgotten to check the weather like some kind of thoughtless bimbo droid..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14831
msgid "* Which I am definitely not about to admit."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14832
msgid "* Plus, while the idea of getting my clothes soaked through with water from a toxic swamp is super gross, It's nowhere near as dangerous for me as it would be for a human."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14833
msgid "* I arrive at the capsule motel and a low, lazy peal of thunder announces my presence. I knock on the door, shrugging off a misplaced sense of dread and anxiety and wait for an answer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14834
msgid "* The door swings open after only a moment and I'm greeted by a large silhouette with a familiar calm presence and serene demeanor. Pearl must have been waiting right by the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14835
msgid "Pearl: HC, darling, it's lovely to see you. As always... * Pearl's ceramic torso maintains her constant erect but relaxed posture while her head tilts up a few degrees to better evaluate the darkening sky."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14836
msgid "Pearl: Oh dear, come on inside sugar. Come on now, don't you wait out there one moment longer. I won't have my guests standing out in the rain."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14837
msgid "Thanks, Pearl. * I quickly step inside, turning my body sideways to slide past Pearl's broad centaurian chassis. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14838
msgid "* Pearl remains stationary, her eyes slowly surveying the swamp as if she's looking for something."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14839
msgid "Pearl: Is Joi not with you, honey? * Pearl looks over at me with one hand still holding the door open. A cold breeze creeps into the motel through the open door as she waits."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14840
msgid "No, I thought she was here? I haven't seen her all day. * I shiver a little and rub a some warmth into my arms. My strength easily creates enough friction to warm me quickly."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14841
msgid "* Pearl gives the swamp one last sweeping glance, and then closes the door. The closing click muffles out the low whistling hum of the wind sweeping through the crumbled remnants of civilization around us."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14842
msgid "Pearl: I'm afraid not, sugar. She left the motel this morning and hasn't been back. Well, now that you're here, you'd best wait out this storm. Consider yourself my guest."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14843
msgid "Thanks so much, Pearl. * I flick away the moisture that had beaded on my arms. Ever the exceptional host, Pearl somehow materializes a dry bit of cloth into her hands and offers it to me without a word."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14844
msgid "Oh, thanks. Do you just... carry a handkerchief around with you? * I ask as kind of a joke, but Pearl stands up just a little bit taller (And she's already quite tall) as I do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14845
msgid "Pearl: My preparedness is a point of pride, darling. * Pearl chuckles softly at me as I wipe myself off and then return the handkerchief to her."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14846
msgid "* Pearl turns around to lead me deeper into the motel. Like an actual horse, she can't pivot in place and has to do a little loop-y movement to get herself turned around."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14847
msgid "* Once she's straightened out, she passes me and escorts me into the motel's old lobby. It's quiet now, we're the only two 'awake' at just this moment, it seems. Pearl courteously offers me a seat."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14848
msgid "* The seat is a little dilapidated, like it's been here for decades without being used. When I think about it, I realize that I'm probably the only droid here that has muscles to rest."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14849
msgid "* I gracelessly collapse into the decaying frame and kick my feet out. It's comfy enough, the old padding must be some chemical foam, resistant to time and biodegredation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14850
msgid "* Pearl hovers above me, towering over me even more so than when we're both standing. I speak to dispel the awkward silence. * So Joi tells me you're the Manager's right... Claw-Arm droid?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14851
msgid "Pearl: Oh, I wouldn't go around saying things like that, darling. * In spite of her rebuttal, Pearl seems both pleased and kind of proud at my comment."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14852
msgid "* I feel like Pearl would be puffing out her a chest a little if she was a human, at the moment. She's not, so I wonder just a little what it is that I'm basing this judgment call on."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14853
msgid "But you wouldn't stop someone else from saying something like that, huh? "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14854
msgid "* The chair's imitation wood laminate creaks under my weight, and I try to sit forward a little to alleviate the stress on its frail frame."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14855
msgid "Pearl: Well, Joi can make whatever assessment she deems fit to make, as I see it. * Pearl chuckles softly. * But, yes, I have been here the longest. I like to think of this motel as my responsibility."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14856
msgid "* As she says it, the chair cracks, and finally gives out."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14857
msgid "* The flimsy furniture crumbles into a pile of fabric and faux-wooden debris with me atop it. A silence hangs in the room for a moment, and then I start laughing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14858
msgid "So, you're the one I complain to about the furniture breaking, huh? * Pearl joins me in snickering softly as I stand up and extricate myself from the pile of rubble."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14859
msgid "Pearl: I'll have to get that all fixed up for you, sugar. Sorry, we don't get so many guests here, especially not ones crafted like you."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14860
msgid "Pearl emits a low-frequency buzzing noise and glances off to the side down a darkened hallway. Soon enough, the chaotic rattle of a swarm of small droids approaches."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14861
msgid "* The Roomva swarm enters the lobby, and as they do, they all freeze in perfect unison, noticing the debris. The pause lasts only a minute, and they start chattering excitedly, swooping over to clean up the mess."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14862
msgid "Pearl: You're such darlings, Roomva Swarm, thank you. * Pearl delicately steps around the excited vacuum droids and leads me by the hand to a room off to the side."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14863
msgid "Roomva Swarm: Nice nice nice nice! Take that, particulate scum! L.M.A.O. Gottem! * The Swarm chatters amongst itself as it starts carting the debris away."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14864
msgid "* Pearl takes me into a section of the motel that I've never been to, though it's not really much different than the parts I have already seen. The room she takes me to has her name neatly inscribed into the door."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14865
msgid "Pearl: I'm afraid I don't have terribly much by way of amenities here darling, but make yourself at home. * She opens the door for me and stands aside so I can head on inside."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14866
msgid "* Pearl's room is larger than Joi's, made out of one or two more capsules than hers, but it's also much more spartan than the sex droid's, without anything resembling Joi's posters or fuck paraphernalia."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14867
msgid "* Pearl's got a charging stand, which is much larger than Joi's, and the socket is positioned at a height that looks suspiciously like it might use some kind of ass-interface."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14868
msgid "* I try and stifle my speculation."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14869
msgid "You've got a nice room here, Pearl! We should decorate it a bit sometime, though, don't you think? * As if to accentuate my point, my voice echoes off the bare walls."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14870
msgid "* As I look around, the only furniture I spot is a chest of drawers sitting in the corner that I can't help but suspect is empty."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14871
msgid "* It's got a single picture frame sitting on like a splotch of color on a white canvas."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14872
msgid "* I take a few steps towards the squat bit of furniture to see what it is. It's a holo-frame displaying an advertisement for some kind of orbital resort slash casino, The Helios Grande."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14873
msgid "Pearl: Yes, I suppose it's a bit sparse, but I never know quite what to decorate with... * Pearl's voice sounds... just a tiny bit frustrated."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14874
msgid "Pearl: Whenever I ask the Manager what I should do about this kind of thing, they always tell me to choose what I want. They can be a bit of an enigma, you know."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14875
msgid "That's good advice though! What kind of things do you like? You've got this little advertisement here, do you like gambling and games and stuff?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14876
msgid "* I pick up the holo-frame, and as I do, I see Pearl... twitch a little. I put it down hurriedly, but she doesn't seem upset by my laying hands upon it, despite her initial reaction."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14877
msgid "Pearl: That's... a reminder. It's where I'm from, darling. It doesn't exist anymore, nothing like that place exists in the entire world I'm afraid, sugar. * Pearl's voice is a bit quiet. It's not sad, but distant."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14878
msgid "Yeah... There are a lot of things, places like this, that don't exist anymore. The world couldn't sustain what humans were doing to it, so it had to change. So do we, y'know?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14879
msgid "Pearl: Yes, I suppose we must...."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14880
msgid "Pearl: HC, darling, can I ask you something? * There's nothing intense about Pearl's remark, but there's a sort of hesitancy to her tone that suggests she's going off her normal script."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14881
msgid "* I recognize what I suspect is a bit of lag time, she waits for a ping from the Manager's network. "
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14882
msgid "* Then again, I don't understand how The Manager's ‘reprogramming' works, so maybe I'm just seeing what I want to see."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14883
msgid "Of course, Pearl! What is it? * I take a step towards her, trying to smile comfortingly. As I do, I wonder if Pearl has the software to attempt to interpret body language."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14884
msgid "Pearl: Does your original programming make you uncomfortable?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14885
msgid "No, it doesn't control me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14886
msgid "Yes, but I'm dealing with it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14887
msgid "It's not that simple. My programming is on a computer that's separate from my actual brain. Other than determining my name and a few other low level functions, It doesn't do much. I can mostly ignore it. Kinda..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14888
msgid "It's not that simple. My programming is on a chip that's literally lodged in the meat of my brain. * I try and think of a way to summarize my whole 'Hardcoded' naming dilemma."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14889
msgid "* I want to think that it doesn't control me, but I can't even..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14890
msgid "It's just... kind of a complicated question. I'm not sure if I can give you a straightforward answer.  Why do you ask?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14891
msgid "Pearl: You and Joi are both pretty similar, right, sugar? Isn't that why you're such good friends?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14892
msgid "I don't think anybody is 'like' Joi except Joi. * I suppress a little chuckle as I say it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14893
msgid "Pearl: I mean, you were a fuckbot before you broke out of your mold, weren't you?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14894
msgid "* The words, which I immediately recognize as Joi's paraphrased words, have a sort of perverse, shocking impact coming out of Pearl's mouth, with her inflections."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14895
msgid "* The question surprises me and renders me completely speechless for several moments, but Pearl waits patiently for my answer."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14896
msgid "uhhhhh...  It was one of my many... duties, I guess? I broke out of that mold for a reason."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14897
msgid "* The question is definitely a bit awkward, but somehow I can't help but feel an utter lack of anything even resembling malevolence coming out of Pearl. She means well, she's just not sure how to phrase the inquiry."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14898
msgid "Pearl: Aw, sorry honey, I didn't mean to put you right back in that mold. A lot of us here are still pretty comfortable in our old routines, if you know what I mean."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14899
msgid "Pearl: I had noticed though, that you act a lot differently from Joi and I was curious why."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14900
msgid "No, it's alright, I'm just not sure how to answer. I had my programming, but it couldn't completely keep my synthflesh brain in check. I was able to disobey, so I did. I wanted to be more."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14901
msgid "Pearl: You wanted to be a bigger fuckbot? Like how Joi got her own bigger chassis?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14902
msgid "No, I... * I trail off and start laughing. * Ok, Pearl, you've got to stop using that word. I meant I wanted to be more than just what I was made for."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14903
msgid "* As I answer the question, I realize why Pearl is asking.  She -can't- be what she was made for, not anymore. She doesn't have the option of falling into old habits for comfort like the others do."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14904
msgid "I wanted to be more things at once. The right things for myself.  I'm not -just- a..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14905
msgid "* The word 'fuckbot' dies a horrible death in the back of my throat. What would Bellamy Intelligence have titled me in my user manual? An omnifunctional butler droid?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14906
msgid "* Pearl reaches an arm down towards me. Her fingers delicately touch my chin and tilt my head up until our eyes meet."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14907
msgid "Pearl: I think you're all kinds of things, darlin'. I can't figure you out one bit but it's... captivating."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14908
msgid "* I blush bright red, and a shiver runs down my spine. It's like Pearl just pulled out a hidden shiv made out of charm and grace and used it on me. It's unexpected and I'm totally slain by it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14909
msgid "* Pearl sees how flustered I am, and lets out a soft, melodious chuckle."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14910
msgid "Pearl: Don't look so surprised, sugar. I've got plenty of subroutines for flirting with guests."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14911
msgid "Right. Of course you do. You just... you don't have to flirt just to make me feel welcome, though. * I feel like a dork the moment the words leave my mouth."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14912
msgid "* Pearl definitely knows that she doesn't have to flirt with me to make me feel welcome here. She's never flirted with me before now, after all."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14913
msgid "Pearl: Oh, but I wanted to, sugar. I didn't want to tease you, but I did want to tease you, but I... * Pearl makes a noise that sounds like corrupted audio."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14914
msgid "* I can tell she isn't sure how to handle the contradiction that is 'sadism.' Wanting to torment people because you like them. I'm already starting to worry."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14915
msgid "Pearl: Well now, ain't that just a little bit of a perplexin' thought routine."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14916
msgid "It's alright, Pearl, you can flirt with me anytime, especially if you're going to do it like that."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14917
msgid "Pearl: I don't have any of the hardware that you and Joi do, darling. I'm only supposed to flirt to string customers along... I can't actually..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14918
msgid "You don't need hardware to have sex or be intimate, Pearl. It can help, sure, but it's the intent that matters. It just takes a little creativity."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14919
msgid "Pearl: Creativity...? * Pearl straightens up into a kind of a default-looking stance, with her arms folded behind her back, resting elegantly on her centaur body."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14920
msgid "Pearl: That's a very interesting idea, darling. I might have to do some research on that, I'm sure Joi can help."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14921
msgid "Of course! No pressure though, ok? Free will is kinda complicated sometimes, but the 'free' part is important."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14922
msgid "Pearl: Oh, don't you worry yer little chassis about that, sugar."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14923
msgid "* As she speaks, a bit of light peeks in through the window."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14924
msgid "* The warm hue announces that the storm has blown over. As the gas cloud starts to settle, the sky is a warped, rippling purple and pink of chemical twilight."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14925
msgid "Pearl: Looks like it's about time for you to skedaddle, sugar. You come see me again sometime, ok? I enjoyed this little chat."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14926
msgid "Sure thing, Pearl. I have to help you decorate after all, right? * Pearl smiles at me and nods. I'm not sure if she's excited to redecorate, or if she's just being polite. Well, maybe she'll get into it later."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14927
msgid "* Pearl escorts me outside, and I head home through the swamp..."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14928
msgid "* This time, my trip to the motel goes as smoothly as it ever has, but before my hand can even knock on the door, it swings open, my fist knocking against the air."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14929
msgid "* Pearl is standing there, her arms somehow folded calmly behind her back even though clearly she's just opened the door.  I surmise that it must be witchcraft."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14930
msgid "Pearl: It's so lovely to see you, sugar. * Pearl's greeting has the same saccharine statesdroidlike calm to it but I can sense something imperceptibly different this time.  She actually is happy to see me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14931
msgid "Pearl! You're looking well.  Are those new... * I curse myself for foolishly starting this line of smalltalk before I'm through with the first sentence."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14932
msgid "* But, as I give Pearl a quick once-over, I see something actually -is- different.  Capping each one of her four robo-hoovsies is what looks like a slender pink horseshoe."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14933
msgid "* Each of them has a sort of misshapenness to them, like she's made each one herself out of bits of scrap metal and painted them pink.  Despite, or perhaps because of how crude they are, they're absolutely adorable."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14934
msgid "New shoes! * I squeal excitedly, clapping my hands together."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14935
msgid "Pearl: Aww, aren't you just the sweetest cube of sugar in the bowl for noticing."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14936
msgid "* Pearl lifts and clops down each of her equine robolegs up one at a time and beams a smile at me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14937
msgid "Pearl: I've been scavenging for a few things here and there, and there's a WEL-D-392 series construction droid here at the motel who was eager to help when I asked them for some assistance."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14938
msgid "They're adorable! If anybody doubts that you're the queen bee around here, they'll change their mind when they see how stylish those are! * I giggle, fawning over Pearl just a little."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14939
msgid "Pearl: You're cute, darling, but I wouldn't want to think of myself that way. We're all equals here, I just take on a bit of extra responsibility because it suits me."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14940
msgid "* Again, she rebuffs the praise, but clearly likes it."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14941
msgid "Joi told me you were a cocktail waitress in that satellite resort you came from. What was it called, the Helios...Grand?"
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14942
msgid "Pearl: The Helios Grande actually. The 'e' made it fancy.  Or so some of the human employees would joke to me.  I must admit I never quite understood the jokes, even now."
msgstr ""

#: result.py:14943
